 44     /*\
 45      * Raphael
 46      [ method ]
 47      **
 48      * Creates a canvas object on which to draw.
 49      * You must do this first, as all future calls to drawing methods
 50      * from this instance will be bound to this canvas.
 51      > Parameters
 52      **
 53      - container (HTMLElement|string) DOM element or its ID which is going to be a parent for drawing surface
 54      - width (number)
 55      - height (number)
 56      - callback (function) #optional callback function which is going to be executed in the context of newly created paper
 57      * or
 58      - x (number)
 59      - y (number)
 60      - width (number)
 61      - height (number)
 62      - callback (function) #optional callback function which is going to be executed in the context of newly created paper
 63      * or
 64      - all (array) (first 3 or 4 elements in the array are equal to [containerID, width, height] or [x, y, width, height]. The rest are element descriptions in format {type: type, <attributes>}). See @Paper.add.
 65      - callback (function) #optional callback function which is going to be executed in the context of newly created paper
 66      * or
 67      - onReadyCallback (function) function that is going to be called on DOM ready event. You can also subscribe to this event via Eve’s “DOMLoad” event. In this case method returns `undefined`.
 68      = (object) @Paper
 69      > Usage
 70      | // Each of the following examples create a canvas
 71      | // that is 320px wide by 200px high.
 72      | // Canvas is created at the viewport’s 10,50 coordinate.
 73      | var paper = Raphael(10, 50, 320, 200);
 74      | // Canvas is created at the top left corner of the #notepad element
 75      | // (or its top right corner in dir="rtl" elements)
 76      | var paper = Raphael(document.getElementById("notepad"), 320, 200);
 77      | // Same as above
 78      | var paper = Raphael("notepad", 320, 200);
 79      | // Image dump
 80      | var set = Raphael(["notepad", 320, 200, {
 81      |     type: "rect",
 82      |     x: 10,
 83      |     y: 10,
 84      |     width: 25,
 85      |     height: 25,
 86      |     stroke: "#f00"
 87      | }, {
 88      |     type: "text",
 89      |     x: 30,
 90      |     y: 40,
 91      |     text: "Dump"
 92      | }]);
 93     \*/
 94     function R(first) {
 95         if (R.is(first, "function")) {
 96             return loaded ? first() : eve.on("raphael.DOMload", first);
 97         } else if (R.is(first, array)) {
 98             return R._engine.create[apply](R, first.splice(0, 3 + R.is(first[0], nu))).add(first);
 99         } else {
100             var args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments, 0);
101             if (R.is(args[args.length - 1], "function")) {
102                 var f = args.pop();
103                 return loaded ? f.call(R._engine.create[apply](R, args)) : eve.on("raphael.DOMload", function () {
104                     f.call(R._engine.create[apply](R, args));
105                 });
106             } else {
107                 return R._engine.create[apply](R, arguments);
108             }
109         }

282         rectPath = R._rectPath = function (x, y, w, h, r) {
283             if (r) {
284                 return [["M", x + r, y], ["l", w - r * 2, 0], ["a", r, r, 0, 0, 1, r, r], ["l", 0, h - r * 2], ["a", r, r, 0, 0, 1, -r, r], ["l", r * 2 - w, 0], ["a", r, r, 0, 0, 1, -r, -r], ["l", 0, r * 2 - h], ["a", r, r, 0, 0, 1, r, -r], ["z"]];
285             }
286             return [["M", x, y], ["l", w, 0], ["l", 0, h], ["l", -w, 0], ["z"]];
287         },

293         },

323         /*\
324          * Raphael.mapPath
325          [ method ]
326          **
327          * Transform the path string with given matrix.
328          > Parameters
329          - path (string) path string
330          - matrix (object) see @Matrix
331          = (string) transformed path string
332         \*/
333         mapPath = R.mapPath = function (path, matrix) {
334             if (!matrix) {
335                 return path;
336             }
337             var x, y, i, j, ii, jj, pathi;
338             path = path2curve(path);
339             for (i = 0, ii = path.length; i < ii; i++) {
340                 pathi = path[i];
341                 for (j = 1, jj = pathi.length; j < jj; j += 2) {
342                     x = matrix.x(pathi[j], pathi[j + 1]);
343                     y = matrix.y(pathi[j], pathi[j + 1]);
344                     pathi[j] = x;
345                     pathi[j + 1] = y;
346                 }
347             }
348             return path;
349         };

384     /*\
385      * Raphael.fn
386      [ property (object) ]
387      **
388      * You can add your own method to the canvas. For example if you want to draw a pie chart,
389      * you can create your own pie chart function and ship it as a Raphaël plugin. To do this
390      * you need to extend the `Raphael.fn` object. You should modify the `fn` object before a
391      * Raphaël instance is created, otherwise it will take no effect. Please note that the
392      * ability for namespaced plugins was removed in Raphael 2.0. It is up to the plugin to
393      * ensure any namespacing ensures proper context.
394      > Usage
395      | Raphael.fn.arrow = function (x1, y1, x2, y2, size) {
396      |     return this.path( ... );
397      | };
398      | // or create namespace
399      | Raphael.fn.mystuff = {
400      |     arrow: function () {…},
401      |     star: function () {…},
402      |     // etc…
403      | };
404      | var paper = Raphael(10, 10, 630, 480);
405      | // then use it
406      | paper.arrow(10, 10, 30, 30, 5).attr({fill: "#f00"});
407      | paper.mystuff.arrow();
408      | paper.mystuff.star();
409     \*/

413     /*\
414      * Raphael.is
415      [ method ]
416      **
417      * Handful of replacements for `typeof` operator.
418      > Parameters
419      - o (…) any object or primitive
420      - type (string) name of the type, i.e. “string”, “function”, “number”, etc.
421      = (boolean) is given value is of given type
422     \*/
423     R.is = function (o, type) {
424         type = lowerCase.call(type);
425         if (type == "finite") {
426             return !isnan[has](+o);
427         }
428         if (type == "array") {
429             return o instanceof Array;
430         }
431         return  (type == "null" && o === null) ||
432                 (type == typeof o && o !== null) ||
433                 (type == "object" && o === Object(o)) ||
434                 (type == "array" && Array.isArray && Array.isArray(o)) ||
435                 objectToString.call(o).slice(8, -1).toLowerCase() == type;
436     };
437 
438     function clone(obj) {
439         if (typeof obj == "function" || Object(obj) !== obj) {
440             return obj;
441         }
442         var res = new obj.constructor;
443         for (var key in obj) if (obj[has](key)) {
444             res[key] = clone(obj[key]);
445         }
446         return res;
447     }

449     /*\
450      * Raphael.angle
451      [ method ]
452      **
453      * Returns angle between two or three points
454      > Parameters
455      - x1 (number) x coord of first point
456      - y1 (number) y coord of first point
457      - x2 (number) x coord of second point
458      - y2 (number) y coord of second point
459      - x3 (number) #optional x coord of third point
460      - y3 (number) #optional y coord of third point
461      = (number) angle in degrees.
462     \*/
463     R.angle = function (x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3) {
464         if (x3 == null) {
465             var x = x1 - x2,
466                 y = y1 - y2;
467             if (!x && !y) {
468                 return 0;
469             }
470             return (180 + math.atan2(-y, -x) * 180 / PI + 360) % 360;
471         } else {
472             return R.angle(x1, y1, x3, y3) - R.angle(x2, y2, x3, y3);
473         }
474     };
475     /*\
476      * Raphael.rad
477      [ method ]
478      **
479      * Transform angle to radians
480      > Parameters
481      - deg (number) angle in degrees
482      = (number) angle in radians.
483     \*/
484     R.rad = function (deg) {
485         return deg % 360 * PI / 180;
486     };
487     /*\
488      * Raphael.deg
489      [ method ]
490      **
491      * Transform angle to degrees
492      > Parameters
493      - rad (number) angle in radians
494      = (number) angle in degrees.
495     \*/
496     R.deg = function (rad) {
497         return Math.round ((rad * 180 / PI% 360)* 1000) / 1000;
498     };
499     /*\
500      * Raphael.snapTo
501      [ method ]
502      **
503      * Snaps given value to given grid.
504      > Parameters
505      - values (array|number) given array of values or step of the grid
506      - value (number) value to adjust
507      - tolerance (number) #optional tolerance for snapping. Default is `10`.
508      = (number) adjusted value.
509     \*/
510     R.snapTo = function (values, value, tolerance) {
511         tolerance = R.is(tolerance, "finite") ? tolerance : 10;
512         if (R.is(values, array)) {
513             var i = values.length;
514             while (i--) if (abs(values[i] - value) <= tolerance) {
515                 return values[i];
516             }
517         } else {
518             values = +values;
519             var rem = value % values;
520             if (rem < tolerance) {
521                 return value - rem;
522             }
523             if (rem > values - tolerance) {
524                 return value - rem + values;
525             }
526         }
527         return value;
528     };

531      * Raphael.createUUID
532      [ method ]
533      **
534      * Returns RFC4122, version 4 ID
535     \*/
536     var createUUID = R.createUUID = (function (uuidRegEx, uuidReplacer) {
537         return function () {
538             return "xxxxxxxx-xxxx-4xxx-yxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx".replace(uuidRegEx, uuidReplacer).toUpperCase();
539         };
540     })(/[xy]/g, function (c) {
541         var r = math.random() * 16 | 0,
542             v = c == "x" ? r : (r & 3 | 8);
543         return v.toString(16);
544     });

546     /*\
547      * Raphael.setWindow
548      [ method ]
549      **
550      * Used when you need to draw in `<iframe>`. Switched window to the iframe one.
551      > Parameters
552      - newwin (window) new window object
553     \*/
554     R.setWindow = function (newwin) {
555         eve("raphael.setWindow", R, g.win, newwin);
556         g.win = newwin;

562     var toHex = function (color) {
563         if (R.vml) {
564             // http://dean.edwards.name/weblog/2009/10/convert-any-colour-value-to-hex-in-msie/
565             var trim = /^\s+|\s+$/g;
566             var bod;
567             try {
568                 var docum = new ActiveXObject("htmlfile");
569                 docum.write("<body>");
570                 docum.close();
571                 bod = docum.body;
572             } catch(e) {
573                 bod = createPopup().document.body;
574             }
575             var range = bod.createTextRange();
576             toHex = cacher(function (color) {
577                 try {
578                     bod.style.color = Str(color).replace(trim, E);
579                     var value = range.queryCommandValue("ForeColor");
580                     value = ((value & 255) << 16) | (value & 65280) | ((value & 16711680) >>> 16);
581                     return "#" + ("000000" + value.toString(16)).slice(-6);
582                 } catch(e) {
583                     return "none";
584                 }
585             });
586         } else {
587             var i = g.doc.createElement("i");
588             i.title = "Rapha\xebl Colour Picker";
589             i.style.display = "none";
590             g.doc.body.appendChild(i);
591             toHex = cacher(function (color) {
592                 i.style.color = color;
593                 return g.doc.defaultView.getComputedStyle(i, E).getPropertyValue("color");
594             });
595         }
596         return toHex(color);
597     },
598     hsbtoString = function () {
599         return "hsb(" + [this.h, this.s, this.b] + ")";
600     },
601     hsltoString = function () {
602         return "hsl(" + [this.h, this.s, this.l] + ")";
603     },
604     rgbtoString = function () {
605         return this.hex;
606     },
607     prepareRGB = function (r, g, b) {
608         if (g == null && R.is(r, "object") && "r" in r && "g" in r && "b" in r) {
609             b = r.b;
610             g = r.g;
611             r = r.r;
612         }
613         if (g == null && R.is(r, string)) {
614             var clr = R.getRGB(r);
615             r = clr.r;
616             g = clr.g;
617             b = clr.b;
618         }
619         if (r > 1 || g > 1 || b > 1) {
620             r /= 255;
621             g /= 255;
622             b /= 255;
623         }
624 
625         return [r, g, b];
626     },
627     packageRGB = function (r, g, b, o) {
628         r *= 255;
629         g *= 255;
630         b *= 255;
631         var rgb = {
632             r: r,
633             g: g,
634             b: b,
635             hex: R.rgb(r, g, b),
636             toString: rgbtoString
637         };
638         R.is(o, "finite") && (rgb.opacity = o);
639         return rgb;
640     };
641 
642     /*\
643      * Raphael.color
644      [ method ]
645      **
646      * Parses the color string and returns object with all values for the given color.
647      > Parameters
648      - clr (string) color string in one of the supported formats (see @Raphael.getRGB)
649      = (object) Combined RGB & HSB object in format:
650      o {
651      o     r (number) red,
652      o     g (number) green,
653      o     b (number) blue,
654      o     hex (string) color in HTML/CSS format: #••••••,
655      o     error (boolean) `true` if string can’t be parsed,
656      o     h (number) hue,
657      o     s (number) saturation,
658      o     v (number) value (brightness),
659      o     l (number) lightness
660      o }
661     \*/
662     R.color = function (clr) {
663         var rgb;
664         if (R.is(clr, "object") && "h" in clr && "s" in clr && "b" in clr) {
665             rgb = R.hsb2rgb(clr);
666             clr.r = rgb.r;
667             clr.g = rgb.g;
668             clr.b = rgb.b;
669             clr.hex = rgb.hex;
670         } else if (R.is(clr, "object") && "h" in clr && "s" in clr && "l" in clr) {
671             rgb = R.hsl2rgb(clr);
672             clr.r = rgb.r;
673             clr.g = rgb.g;
674             clr.b = rgb.b;
675             clr.hex = rgb.hex;
676         } else {
677             if (R.is(clr, "string")) {
678                 clr = R.getRGB(clr);
679             }
680             if (R.is(clr, "object") && "r" in clr && "g" in clr && "b" in clr) {
681                 rgb = R.rgb2hsl(clr);
682                 clr.h = rgb.h;
683                 clr.s = rgb.s;
684                 clr.l = rgb.l;
685                 rgb = R.rgb2hsb(clr);
686                 clr.v = rgb.b;
687             } else {
688                 clr = {hex: "none"};
689                 clr.r = clr.g = clr.b = clr.h = clr.s = clr.v = clr.l = -1;
690             }
691         }
692         clr.toString = rgbtoString;
693         return clr;
694     };
695     /*\
696      * Raphael.hsb2rgb
697      [ method ]
698      **
699      * Converts HSB values to RGB object.
700      > Parameters
701      - h (number) hue
702      - s (number) saturation
703      - v (number) value or brightness
704      = (object) RGB object in format:
705      o {
706      o     r (number) red,
707      o     g (number) green,
708      o     b (number) blue,
709      o     hex (string) color in HTML/CSS format: #••••••
710      o }
711     \*/
712     R.hsb2rgb = function (h, s, v, o) {
713         if (this.is(h, "object") && "h" in h && "s" in h && "b" in h) {
714             v = h.b;
715             s = h.s;
716             o = h.o;
717             h = h.h;
718         }
719         h *= 360;
720         var R, G, B, X, C;
721         h = (h % 360) / 60;
722         C = v * s;
723         X = C * (1 - abs(h % 2 - 1));
724         R = G = B = v - C;
725 
726         h = ~~h;
727         R += [C, X, 0, 0, X, C][h];
728         G += [X, C, C, X, 0, 0][h];
729         B += [0, 0, X, C, C, X][h];
730         return packageRGB(R, G, B, o);
731     };
732     /*\
733      * Raphael.hsl2rgb
734      [ method ]
735      **
736      * Converts HSL values to RGB object.
737      > Parameters
738      - h (number) hue
739      - s (number) saturation
740      - l (number) luminosity
741      = (object) RGB object in format:
742      o {
743      o     r (number) red,
744      o     g (number) green,
745      o     b (number) blue,
746      o     hex (string) color in HTML/CSS format: #••••••
747      o }
748     \*/
749     R.hsl2rgb = function (h, s, l, o) {
750         if (this.is(h, "object") && "h" in h && "s" in h && "l" in h) {
751             l = h.l;
752             s = h.s;
753             h = h.h;
754         }
755         if (h > 1 || s > 1 || l > 1) {
756             h /= 360;
757             s /= 100;
758             l /= 100;
759         }
760         h *= 360;
761         var R, G, B, X, C;
762         h = (h % 360) / 60;
763         C = 2 * s * (l < .5 ? l : 1 - l);
764         X = C * (1 - abs(h % 2 - 1));
765         R = G = B = l - C / 2;
766 
767         h = ~~h;
768         R += [C, X, 0, 0, X, C][h];
769         G += [X, C, C, X, 0, 0][h];
770         B += [0, 0, X, C, C, X][h];
771         return packageRGB(R, G, B, o);
772     };
773     /*\
774      * Raphael.rgb2hsb
775      [ method ]
776      **
777      * Converts RGB values to HSB object.
778      > Parameters
779      - r (number) red
780      - g (number) green
781      - b (number) blue
782      = (object) HSB object in format:
783      o {
784      o     h (number) hue
785      o     s (number) saturation
786      o     b (number) brightness
787      o }
788     \*/
789     R.rgb2hsb = function (r, g, b) {
790         b = prepareRGB(r, g, b);
791         r = b[0];
792         g = b[1];
793         b = b[2];
794 
795         var H, S, V, C;
796         V = mmax(r, g, b);
797         C = V - mmin(r, g, b);
798         H = (C == 0 ? null :
799              V == r ? (g - b) / C :
800              V == g ? (b - r) / C + 2 :
801                       (r - g) / C + 4
802             );
803         H = ((H + 360) % 6) * 60 / 360;
804         S = C == 0 ? 0 : C / V;
805         return {h: H, s: S, b: V, toString: hsbtoString};
806     };
807     /*\
808      * Raphael.rgb2hsl
809      [ method ]
810      **
811      * Converts RGB values to HSL object.
812      > Parameters
813      - r (number) red
814      - g (number) green
815      - b (number) blue
816      = (object) HSL object in format:
817      o {
818      o     h (number) hue
819      o     s (number) saturation
820      o     l (number) luminosity
821      o }
822     \*/
823     R.rgb2hsl = function (r, g, b) {
824         b = prepareRGB(r, g, b);
825         r = b[0];
826         g = b[1];
827         b = b[2];
828 
829         var H, S, L, M, m, C;
830         M = mmax(r, g, b);
831         m = mmin(r, g, b);
832         C = M - m;
833         H = (C == 0 ? null :
834              M == r ? (g - b) / C :
835              M == g ? (b - r) / C + 2 :
836                       (r - g) / C + 4);
837         H = ((H + 360) % 6) * 60 / 360;
838         L = (M + m) / 2;
839         S = (C == 0 ? 0 :
840              L < .5 ? C / (2 * L) :
841                       C / (2 - 2 * L));
842         return {h: H, s: S, l: L, toString: hsltoString};
843     };
844     R._path2string = function () {
845         return this.join(",").replace(p2s, "$1");
846     };
847     function repush(array, item) {
848         for (var i = 0, ii = array.length; i < ii; i++) if (array[i] === item) {
849             return array.push(array.splice(i, 1)[0]);
850         }
851     }
852     function cacher(f, scope, postprocessor) {
853         function newf() {
854             var arg = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments, 0),
855                 args = arg.join("\u2400"),
856                 cache = newf.cache = newf.cache || {},
857                 count = newf.count = newf.count || [];
858             if (cache[has](args)) {
859                 repush(count, args);
860                 return postprocessor ? postprocessor(cache[args]) : cache[args];
861             }
862             count.length >= 1e3 && delete cache[count.shift()];
863             count.push(args);
864             cache[args] = f[apply](scope, arg);
865             return postprocessor ? postprocessor(cache[args]) : cache[args];
866         }
867         return newf;
868     }

870     var preload = R._preload = function (src, f) {
871         var img = g.doc.createElement("img");
872         img.style.cssText = "position:absolute;left:-9999em;top:-9999em";
873         img.onload = function () {
874             f.call(this);
875             this.onload = null;
876             g.doc.body.removeChild(this);
877         };
878         img.onerror = function () {
879             g.doc.body.removeChild(this);
880         };
881         g.doc.body.appendChild(img);
882         img.src = src;
883     };

889     /*\
890      * Raphael.getRGB
891      [ method ]
892      **
893      * Parses colour string as RGB object
894      > Parameters
895      - colour (string) colour string in one of formats:
896      # <ul>
897      #     <li>Colour name (“<code>red</code>”, “<code>green</code>”, “<code>cornflowerblue</code>”, etc)</li>
898      #     <li>#••• — shortened HTML colour: (“<code>#000</code>”, “<code>#fc0</code>”, etc)</li>
899      #     <li>#•••••• — full length HTML colour: (“<code>#000000</code>”, “<code>#bd2300</code>”)</li>
900      #     <li>rgb(•••, •••, •••) — red, green and blue channels’ values: (“<code>rgb(200, 100, 0)</code>”)</li>
901      #     <li>rgb(•••%, •••%, •••%) — same as above, but in %: (“<code>rgb(100%, 175%, 0%)</code>”)</li>
902      #     <li>hsb(•••, •••, •••) — hue, saturation and brightness values: (“<code>hsb(0.5, 0.25, 1)</code>”)</li>
903      #     <li>hsb(•••%, •••%, •••%) — same as above, but in %</li>
904      #     <li>hsl(•••, •••, •••) — same as hsb</li>
905      #     <li>hsl(•••%, •••%, •••%) — same as hsb</li>
906      # </ul>
907      = (object) RGB object in format:
908      o {
909      o     r (number) red,
910      o     g (number) green,
911      o     b (number) blue
912      o     hex (string) color in HTML/CSS format: #••••••,
913      o     error (boolean) true if string can’t be parsed
914      o }
915     \*/
916     R.getRGB = cacher(function (colour) {
917         if (!colour || !!((colour = Str(colour)).indexOf("-") + 1)) {
918             return {r: -1, g: -1, b: -1, hex: "none", error: 1, toString: clrToString};
919         }
920         if (colour == "none") {
921             return {r: -1, g: -1, b: -1, hex: "none", toString: clrToString};
922         }
923         !(hsrg[has](colour.toLowerCase().substring(0, 2)) || colour.charAt() == "#") && (colour = toHex(colour));
924         var res,
925             red,
926             green,
927             blue,
928             opacity,
929             t,
930             values,
931             rgb = colour.match(colourRegExp);
932         if (rgb) {
933             if (rgb[2]) {
934                 blue = toInt(rgb[2].substring(5), 16);
935                 green = toInt(rgb[2].substring(3, 5), 16);
936                 red = toInt(rgb[2].substring(1, 3), 16);
937             }
938             if (rgb[3]) {
939                 blue = toInt((t = rgb[3].charAt(3)) + t, 16);
940                 green = toInt((t = rgb[3].charAt(2)) + t, 16);
941                 red = toInt((t = rgb[3].charAt(1)) + t, 16);
942             }
943             if (rgb[4]) {
944                 values = rgb[4][split](commaSpaces);
945                 red = toFloat(values[0]);
946                 values[0].slice(-1) == "%" && (red *= 2.55);
947                 green = toFloat(values[1]);
948                 values[1].slice(-1) == "%" && (green *= 2.55);
949                 blue = toFloat(values[2]);
950                 values[2].slice(-1) == "%" && (blue *= 2.55);
951                 rgb[1].toLowerCase().slice(0, 4) == "rgba" && (opacity = toFloat(values[3]));
952                 values[3] && values[3].slice(-1) == "%" && (opacity /= 100);
953             }
954             if (rgb[5]) {
955                 values = rgb[5][split](commaSpaces);
956                 red = toFloat(values[0]);
957                 values[0].slice(-1) == "%" && (red *= 2.55);
958                 green = toFloat(values[1]);
959                 values[1].slice(-1) == "%" && (green *= 2.55);
960                 blue = toFloat(values[2]);
961                 values[2].slice(-1) == "%" && (blue *= 2.55);
962                 (values[0].slice(-3) == "deg" || values[0].slice(-1) == "\xb0") && (red /= 360);
963                 rgb[1].toLowerCase().slice(0, 4) == "hsba" && (opacity = toFloat(values[3]));
964                 values[3] && values[3].slice(-1) == "%" && (opacity /= 100);
965                 return R.hsb2rgb(red, green, blue, opacity);
966             }
967             if (rgb[6]) {
968                 values = rgb[6][split](commaSpaces);
969                 red = toFloat(values[0]);
970                 values[0].slice(-1) == "%" && (red *= 2.55);
971                 green = toFloat(values[1]);
972                 values[1].slice(-1) == "%" && (green *= 2.55);
973                 blue = toFloat(values[2]);
974                 values[2].slice(-1) == "%" && (blue *= 2.55);
975                 (values[0].slice(-3) == "deg" || values[0].slice(-1) == "\xb0") && (red /= 360);
976                 rgb[1].toLowerCase().slice(0, 4) == "hsla" && (opacity = toFloat(values[3]));
977                 values[3] && values[3].slice(-1) == "%" && (opacity /= 100);
978                 return R.hsl2rgb(red, green, blue, opacity);
979             }
980             rgb = {r: red, g: green, b: blue, toString: clrToString};
981             rgb.hex = "#" + (16777216 | blue | (green << 8) | (red << 16)).toString(16).slice(1);
982             R.is(opacity, "finite") && (rgb.opacity = opacity);
983             return rgb;
984         }
985         return {r: -1, g: -1, b: -1, hex: "none", error: 1, toString: clrToString};
986     }, R);
987     /*\
988      * Raphael.hsb
989      [ method ]
990      **
991      * Converts HSB values to hex representation of the colour.
992      > Parameters
993      - h (number) hue
994      - s (number) saturation
995      - b (number) value or brightness
996      = (string) hex representation of the colour.
997     \*/
998     R.hsb = cacher(function (h, s, b) {
999         return R.hsb2rgb(h, s, b).hex;
1000     });
1001     /*\
1002      * Raphael.hsl
1003      [ method ]
1004      **
1005      * Converts HSL values to hex representation of the colour.
1006      > Parameters
1007      - h (number) hue
1008      - s (number) saturation
1009      - l (number) luminosity
1010      = (string) hex representation of the colour.
1011     \*/
1012     R.hsl = cacher(function (h, s, l) {
1013         return R.hsl2rgb(h, s, l).hex;
1014     });
1015     /*\
1016      * Raphael.rgb
1017      [ method ]
1018      **
1019      * Converts RGB values to hex representation of the colour.
1020      > Parameters
1021      - r (number) red
1022      - g (number) green
1023      - b (number) blue
1024      = (string) hex representation of the colour.
1025     \*/
1026     R.rgb = cacher(function (r, g, b) {
1027         return "#" + (16777216 | b | (g << 8) | (r << 16)).toString(16).slice(1);
1028     });
1029     /*\
1030      * Raphael.getColor
1031      [ method ]
1032      **
1033      * On each call returns next colour in the spectrum. To reset it back to red call @Raphael.getColor.reset
1034      > Parameters
1035      - value (number) #optional brightness, default is `0.75`
1036      = (string) hex representation of the colour.
1037     \*/
1038     R.getColor = function (value) {
1039         var start = this.getColor.start = this.getColor.start || {h: 0, s: 1, b: value || .75},
1040             rgb = this.hsb2rgb(start.h, start.s, start.b);
1041         start.h += .075;
1042         if (start.h > 1) {
1043             start.h = 0;
1044             start.s -= .2;
1045             start.s <= 0 && (this.getColor.start = {h: 0, s: 1, b: start.b});
1046         }
1047         return rgb.hex;
1048     };
1049     /*\

1051      [ method ]
1052      **
1053      * Resets spectrum position for @Raphael.getColor back to red.
1054     \*/
1055     R.getColor.reset = function () {
1056         delete this.start;
1057     };
