1059     // http://schepers.cc/getting-to-the-point
1060     function catmullRom2bezier(crp, z) {
1061         var d = [];
1062         for (var i = 0, iLen = crp.length; iLen - 2 * !z > i; i += 2) {
1063             var p = [
1064                         {x: +crp[i - 2], y: +crp[i - 1]},
1065                         {x: +crp[i],     y: +crp[i + 1]},
1066                         {x: +crp[i + 2], y: +crp[i + 3]},
1067                         {x: +crp[i + 4], y: +crp[i + 5]}
1068                     ];
1069             if (z) {
1070                 if (!i) {
1071                     p[0] = {x: +crp[iLen - 2], y: +crp[iLen - 1]};
1072                 } else if (iLen - 4 == i) {
1073                     p[3] = {x: +crp[0], y: +crp[1]};
1074                 } else if (iLen - 2 == i) {
1075                     p[2] = {x: +crp[0], y: +crp[1]};
1076                     p[3] = {x: +crp[2], y: +crp[3]};
1077                 }
1078             } else {
1079                 if (iLen - 4 == i) {
1080                     p[3] = p[2];
1081                 } else if (!i) {
1082                     p[0] = {x: +crp[i], y: +crp[i + 1]};
1083                 }
1084             }
1085             d.push(["C",
1086                   (-p[0].x + 6 * p[1].x + p[2].x) / 6,
1087                   (-p[0].y + 6 * p[1].y + p[2].y) / 6,
1088                   (p[1].x + 6 * p[2].x - p[3].x) / 6,
1089                   (p[1].y + 6*p[2].y - p[3].y) / 6,
1090                   p[2].x,
1091                   p[2].y
1092             ]);
1093         }
1094 
1095         return d;
1096     }
1097     /*\
1098      * Raphael.parsePathString
1099      [ method ]
1100      **
1101      * Utility method
1102      **
1103      * Parses given path string into an array of arrays of path segments.
1104      > Parameters
1105      - pathString (string|array) path string or array of segments (in the last case it will be returned straight away)
1106      = (array) array of segments.
1107     \*/
1108     R.parsePathString = function (pathString) {
1109         if (!pathString) {
1110             return null;
1111         }
1112         var pth = paths(pathString);
1113         if (pth.arr) {
1114             return pathClone(pth.arr);
1115         }
1116 
1117         var paramCounts = {a: 7, c: 6, h: 1, l: 2, m: 2, r: 4, q: 4, s: 4, t: 2, v: 1, z: 0},
1118             data = [];
1119         if (R.is(pathString, array) && R.is(pathString[0], array)) { // rough assumption
1120             data = pathClone(pathString);
1121         }
1122         if (!data.length) {
1123             Str(pathString).replace(pathCommand, function (a, b, c) {
1124                 var params = [],
1125                     name = b.toLowerCase();
1126                 c.replace(pathValues, function (a, b) {
1127                     b && params.push(+b);
1128                 });
1129                 if (name == "m" && params.length > 2) {
1130                     data.push([b][concat](params.splice(0, 2)));
1131                     name = "l";
1132                     b = b == "m" ? "l" : "L";
1133                 }
1134                 if (name == "r") {
1135                     data.push([b][concat](params));
1136                 } else while (params.length >= paramCounts[name]) {
1137                     data.push([b][concat](params.splice(0, paramCounts[name])));
1138                     if (!paramCounts[name]) {
1139                         break;
1140                     }
1141                 }
1142             });
1143         }
1144         data.toString = R._path2string;
1145         pth.arr = pathClone(data);
1146         return data;
1147     };
1148     /*\
1149      * Raphael.parseTransformString
1150      [ method ]
1151      **
1152      * Utility method
1153      **
1154      * Parses given path string into an array of transformations.
1155      > Parameters
1156      - TString (string|array) transform string or array of transformations (in the last case it will be returned straight away)
1157      = (array) array of transformations.
1158     \*/
1159     R.parseTransformString = cacher(function (TString) {
1160         if (!TString) {
1161             return null;
1162         }
1163         var paramCounts = {r: 3, s: 4, t: 2, m: 6},
1164             data = [];
1165         if (R.is(TString, array) && R.is(TString[0], array)) { // rough assumption
1166             data = pathClone(TString);
1167         }
1168         if (!data.length) {
1169             Str(TString).replace(tCommand, function (a, b, c) {
1170                 var params = [],
1171                     name = lowerCase.call(b);
1172                 c.replace(pathValues, function (a, b) {
1173                     b && params.push(+b);
1174                 });
1175                 data.push([b][concat](params));
1176             });
1177         }
1178         data.toString = R._path2string;
1179         return data;
1180     });
1181     // PATHS
1182     var paths = function (ps) {
1183         var p = paths.ps = paths.ps || {};
1184         if (p[ps]) {
1185             p[ps].sleep = 100;
1186         } else {
1187             p[ps] = {
1188                 sleep: 100
1189             };
1190         }
1191         setTimeout(function () {
1192             for (var key in p) if (p[has](key) && key != ps) {
1193                 p[key].sleep--;
1194                 !p[key].sleep && delete p[key];
1195             }
1196         });
1197         return p[ps];
1198     };
1199     /*\
1200      * Raphael.findDotsAtSegment
1201      [ method ]
1202      **
1203      * Utility method
1204      **
1205      * Find dot coordinates on the given cubic bezier curve at the given t.
1206      > Parameters
1207      - p1x (number) x of the first point of the curve
1208      - p1y (number) y of the first point of the curve
1209      - c1x (number) x of the first anchor of the curve
1210      - c1y (number) y of the first anchor of the curve
1211      - c2x (number) x of the second anchor of the curve
1212      - c2y (number) y of the second anchor of the curve
1213      - p2x (number) x of the second point of the curve
1214      - p2y (number) y of the second point of the curve
1215      - t (number) position on the curve (0..1)
1216      = (object) point information in format:
1217      o {
1218      o     x: (number) x coordinate of the point
1219      o     y: (number) y coordinate of the point
1220      o     m: {
1221      o         x: (number) x coordinate of the left anchor
1222      o         y: (number) y coordinate of the left anchor
1223      o     }
1224      o     n: {
1225      o         x: (number) x coordinate of the right anchor
1226      o         y: (number) y coordinate of the right anchor
1227      o     }
1228      o     start: {
1229      o         x: (number) x coordinate of the start of the curve
1230      o         y: (number) y coordinate of the start of the curve
1231      o     }
1232      o     end: {
1233      o         x: (number) x coordinate of the end of the curve
1234      o         y: (number) y coordinate of the end of the curve
1235      o     }
1236      o     alpha: (number) angle of the curve derivative at the point
1237      o }
1238     \*/
1239     R.findDotsAtSegment = function (p1x, p1y, c1x, c1y, c2x, c2y, p2x, p2y, t) {
1240         var t1 = 1 - t,
1241             t13 = pow(t1, 3),
1242             t12 = pow(t1, 2),
1243             t2 = t * t,
1244             t3 = t2 * t,
1245             x = t13 * p1x + t12 * 3 * t * c1x + t1 * 3 * t * t * c2x + t3 * p2x,
1246             y = t13 * p1y + t12 * 3 * t * c1y + t1 * 3 * t * t * c2y + t3 * p2y,
1247             mx = p1x + 2 * t * (c1x - p1x) + t2 * (c2x - 2 * c1x + p1x),
1248             my = p1y + 2 * t * (c1y - p1y) + t2 * (c2y - 2 * c1y + p1y),
1249             nx = c1x + 2 * t * (c2x - c1x) + t2 * (p2x - 2 * c2x + c1x),
1250             ny = c1y + 2 * t * (c2y - c1y) + t2 * (p2y - 2 * c2y + c1y),
1251             ax = t1 * p1x + t * c1x,
1252             ay = t1 * p1y + t * c1y,
1253             cx = t1 * c2x + t * p2x,
1254             cy = t1 * c2y + t * p2y,
1255             alpha = (90 - math.atan2(mx - nx, my - ny) * 180 / PI);
1256         (mx > nx || my < ny) && (alpha += 180);
1257         return {
1258             x: x,
1259             y: y,
1260             m: {x: mx, y: my},
1261             n: {x: nx, y: ny},
1262             start: {x: ax, y: ay},
1263             end: {x: cx, y: cy},
1264             alpha: alpha
1265         };
1266     };
1267     /*\
1268      * Raphael.bezierBBox
1269      [ method ]
1270      **
1271      * Utility method
1272      **
1273      * Return bounding box of a given cubic bezier curve
1274      > Parameters
1275      - p1x (number) x of the first point of the curve
1276      - p1y (number) y of the first point of the curve
1277      - c1x (number) x of the first anchor of the curve
1278      - c1y (number) y of the first anchor of the curve
1279      - c2x (number) x of the second anchor of the curve
1280      - c2y (number) y of the second anchor of the curve
1281      - p2x (number) x of the second point of the curve
1282      - p2y (number) y of the second point of the curve
1283      * or
1284      - bez (array) array of six points for bezier curve
1285      = (object) point information in format:
1286      o {
1287      o     min: {
1288      o         x: (number) x coordinate of the left point
1289      o         y: (number) y coordinate of the top point
1290      o     }
1291      o     max: {
1292      o         x: (number) x coordinate of the right point
1293      o         y: (number) y coordinate of the bottom point
1294      o     }
1295      o }
1296     \*/
1297     R.bezierBBox = function (p1x, p1y, c1x, c1y, c2x, c2y, p2x, p2y) {
1298         if (!R.is(p1x, "array")) {
1299             p1x = [p1x, p1y, c1x, c1y, c2x, c2y, p2x, p2y];
1300         }
1301         var bbox = curveDim.apply(null, p1x);
1302         return {
1303             x: bbox.min.x,
1304             y: bbox.min.y,
1305             x2: bbox.max.x,
1306             y2: bbox.max.y,
1307             width: bbox.max.x - bbox.min.x,
1308             height: bbox.max.y - bbox.min.y
1309         };
1310     };
1311     /*\
1312      * Raphael.isPointInsideBBox
1313      [ method ]
1314      **
1315      * Utility method
1316      **
1317      * Returns `true` if given point is inside bounding boxes.
1318      > Parameters
1319      - bbox (string) bounding box
1320      - x (string) x coordinate of the point
1321      - y (string) y coordinate of the point
1322      = (boolean) `true` if point inside
1323     \*/
1324     R.isPointInsideBBox = function (bbox, x, y) {
1325         return x >= bbox.x && x <= bbox.x2 && y >= bbox.y && y <= bbox.y2;
1326     };
1327     /*\
1328      * Raphael.isBBoxIntersect
1329      [ method ]
1330      **
1331      * Utility method
1332      **
1333      * Returns `true` if two bounding boxes intersect
1334      > Parameters
1335      - bbox1 (string) first bounding box
1336      - bbox2 (string) second bounding box
1337      = (boolean) `true` if they intersect
1338     \*/
1339     R.isBBoxIntersect = function (bbox1, bbox2) {
1340         var i = R.isPointInsideBBox;
1341         return i(bbox2, bbox1.x, bbox1.y)
1342             || i(bbox2, bbox1.x2, bbox1.y)
1343             || i(bbox2, bbox1.x, bbox1.y2)
1344             || i(bbox2, bbox1.x2, bbox1.y2)
1345             || i(bbox1, bbox2.x, bbox2.y)
1346             || i(bbox1, bbox2.x2, bbox2.y)
1347             || i(bbox1, bbox2.x, bbox2.y2)
1348             || i(bbox1, bbox2.x2, bbox2.y2)
1349             || (bbox1.x < bbox2.x2 && bbox1.x > bbox2.x || bbox2.x < bbox1.x2 && bbox2.x > bbox1.x)
1350             && (bbox1.y < bbox2.y2 && bbox1.y > bbox2.y || bbox2.y < bbox1.y2 && bbox2.y > bbox1.y);
1351     };
1352     function base3(t, p1, p2, p3, p4) {
1353         var t1 = -3 * p1 + 9 * p2 - 9 * p3 + 3 * p4,
1354             t2 = t * t1 + 6 * p1 - 12 * p2 + 6 * p3;
1355         return t * t2 - 3 * p1 + 3 * p2;
1356     }
1357     function bezlen(x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3, x4, y4, z) {
1358         if (z == null) {
1359             z = 1;
1360         }
1361         z = z > 1 ? 1 : z < 0 ? 0 : z;
1362         var z2 = z / 2,
1363             n = 12,
1364             Tvalues = [-0.1252,0.1252,-0.3678,0.3678,-0.5873,0.5873,-0.7699,0.7699,-0.9041,0.9041,-0.9816,0.9816],
1365             Cvalues = [0.2491,0.2491,0.2335,0.2335,0.2032,0.2032,0.1601,0.1601,0.1069,0.1069,0.0472,0.0472],
1366             sum = 0;
1367         for (var i = 0; i < n; i++) {
1368             var ct = z2 * Tvalues[i] + z2,
1369                 xbase = base3(ct, x1, x2, x3, x4),
1370                 ybase = base3(ct, y1, y2, y3, y4),
1371                 comb = xbase * xbase + ybase * ybase;
1372             sum += Cvalues[i] * math.sqrt(comb);
1373         }
1374         return z2 * sum;
1375     }
1376     function getTatLen(x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3, x4, y4, ll) {
1377         if (ll < 0 || bezlen(x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3, x4, y4) < ll) {
1378             return;
1379         }
1380         var t = 1,
1381             step = t / 2,
1382             t2 = t - step,
1383             l,
1384             e = .01;
1385         l = bezlen(x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3, x4, y4, t2);
1386         while (abs(l - ll) > e) {
1387             step /= 2;
1388             t2 += (l < ll ? 1 : -1) * step;
1389             l = bezlen(x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3, x4, y4, t2);
1390         }
1391         return t2;
1392     }
1393     function intersect(x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3, x4, y4) {
1394         if (
1395             mmax(x1, x2) < mmin(x3, x4) ||
1396             mmin(x1, x2) > mmax(x3, x4) ||
1397             mmax(y1, y2) < mmin(y3, y4) ||
1398             mmin(y1, y2) > mmax(y3, y4)
1399         ) {
1400             return;
1401         }
1402         var nx = (x1 * y2 - y1 * x2) * (x3 - x4) - (x1 - x2) * (x3 * y4 - y3 * x4),
1403             ny = (x1 * y2 - y1 * x2) * (y3 - y4) - (y1 - y2) * (x3 * y4 - y3 * x4),
1404             denominator = (x1 - x2) * (y3 - y4) - (y1 - y2) * (x3 - x4);
1405 
1406         if (!denominator) {
1407             return;
1408         }
1409         var px = nx / denominator,
1410             py = ny / denominator,
1411             px2 = +px.toFixed(2),
1412             py2 = +py.toFixed(2);
1413         if (
1414             px2 < +mmin(x1, x2).toFixed(2) ||
1415             px2 > +mmax(x1, x2).toFixed(2) ||
1416             px2 < +mmin(x3, x4).toFixed(2) ||
1417             px2 > +mmax(x3, x4).toFixed(2) ||
1418             py2 < +mmin(y1, y2).toFixed(2) ||
1419             py2 > +mmax(y1, y2).toFixed(2) ||
1420             py2 < +mmin(y3, y4).toFixed(2) ||
1421             py2 > +mmax(y3, y4).toFixed(2)
1422         ) {
1423             return;
1424         }
1425         return {x: px, y: py};
1426     }
1427     function inter(bez1, bez2) {
1428         return interHelper(bez1, bez2);
1429     }
1430     function interCount(bez1, bez2) {
1431         return interHelper(bez1, bez2, 1);
1432     }
1433     function interHelper(bez1, bez2, justCount) {
1434         var bbox1 = R.bezierBBox(bez1),
1435             bbox2 = R.bezierBBox(bez2);
1436         if (!R.isBBoxIntersect(bbox1, bbox2)) {
1437             return justCount ? 0 : [];
1438         }
1439         var l1 = bezlen.apply(0, bez1),
1440             l2 = bezlen.apply(0, bez2),
1441             n1 = mmax(~~(l1 / 5), 1),
1442             n2 = mmax(~~(l2 / 5), 1),
1443             dots1 = [],
1444             dots2 = [],
1445             xy = {},
1446             res = justCount ? 0 : [];
1447         for (var i = 0; i < n1 + 1; i++) {
1448             var p = R.findDotsAtSegment.apply(R, bez1.concat(i / n1));
1449             dots1.push({x: p.x, y: p.y, t: i / n1});
1450         }
1451         for (i = 0; i < n2 + 1; i++) {
1452             p = R.findDotsAtSegment.apply(R, bez2.concat(i / n2));
1453             dots2.push({x: p.x, y: p.y, t: i / n2});
1454         }
1455         for (i = 0; i < n1; i++) {
1456             for (var j = 0; j < n2; j++) {
1457                 var di = dots1[i],
1458                     di1 = dots1[i + 1],
1459                     dj = dots2[j],
1460                     dj1 = dots2[j + 1],
1461                     ci = abs(di1.x - di.x) < .001 ? "y" : "x",
1462                     cj = abs(dj1.x - dj.x) < .001 ? "y" : "x",
1463                     is = intersect(di.x, di.y, di1.x, di1.y, dj.x, dj.y, dj1.x, dj1.y);
1464                 if (is) {
1465                     if (xy[is.x.toFixed(4)] == is.y.toFixed(4)) {
1466                         continue;
1467                     }
1468                     xy[is.x.toFixed(4)] = is.y.toFixed(4);
1469                     var t1 = di.t + abs((is[ci] - di[ci]) / (di1[ci] - di[ci])) * (di1.t - di.t),
1470                         t2 = dj.t + abs((is[cj] - dj[cj]) / (dj1[cj] - dj[cj])) * (dj1.t - dj.t);
1471                     if (t1 >= 0 && t1 <= 1.001 && t2 >= 0 && t2 <= 1.001) {
1472                         if (justCount) {
1473                             res++;
1474                         } else {
1475                             res.push({
1476                                 x: is.x,
1477                                 y: is.y,
1478                                 t1: mmin(t1, 1),
1479                                 t2: mmin(t2, 1)
1480                             });
1481                         }
1482                     }
1483                 }
1484             }
1485         }
1486         return res;
1487     }
1488     /*\
1489      * Raphael.pathIntersection
1490      [ method ]
1491      **
1492      * Utility method
1493      **
1494      * Finds intersections of two paths
1495      > Parameters
1496      - path1 (string) path string
1497      - path2 (string) path string
1498      = (array) dots of intersection
1499      o [
1500      o     {
1501      o         x: (number) x coordinate of the point
1502      o         y: (number) y coordinate of the point
1503      o         t1: (number) t value for segment of path1
1504      o         t2: (number) t value for segment of path2
1505      o         segment1: (number) order number for segment of path1
1506      o         segment2: (number) order number for segment of path2
1507      o         bez1: (array) eight coordinates representing beziér curve for the segment of path1
1508      o         bez2: (array) eight coordinates representing beziér curve for the segment of path2
1509      o     }
1510      o ]
1511     \*/
1512     R.pathIntersection = function (path1, path2) {
1513         return interPathHelper(path1, path2);
1514     };
1515     R.pathIntersectionNumber = function (path1, path2) {
1516         return interPathHelper(path1, path2, 1);
1517     };
1518     function interPathHelper(path1, path2, justCount) {
1519         path1 = R._path2curve(path1);
1520         path2 = R._path2curve(path2);
1521         var x1, y1, x2, y2, x1m, y1m, x2m, y2m, bez1, bez2,
1522             res = justCount ? 0 : [];
1523         for (var i = 0, ii = path1.length; i < ii; i++) {
1524             var pi = path1[i];
1525             if (pi[0] == "M") {
1526                 x1 = x1m = pi[1];
1527                 y1 = y1m = pi[2];
1528             } else {
1529                 if (pi[0] == "C") {
1530                     bez1 = [x1, y1].concat(pi.slice(1));
1531                     x1 = bez1[6];
1532                     y1 = bez1[7];
1533                 } else {
1534                     bez1 = [x1, y1, x1, y1, x1m, y1m, x1m, y1m];
1535                     x1 = x1m;
1536                     y1 = y1m;
1537                 }
1538                 for (var j = 0, jj = path2.length; j < jj; j++) {
1539                     var pj = path2[j];
1540                     if (pj[0] == "M") {
1541                         x2 = x2m = pj[1];
1542                         y2 = y2m = pj[2];
1543                     } else {
1544                         if (pj[0] == "C") {
1545                             bez2 = [x2, y2].concat(pj.slice(1));
1546                             x2 = bez2[6];
1547                             y2 = bez2[7];
1548                         } else {
1549                             bez2 = [x2, y2, x2, y2, x2m, y2m, x2m, y2m];
1550                             x2 = x2m;
1551                             y2 = y2m;
1552                         }
1553                         var intr = interHelper(bez1, bez2, justCount);
1554                         if (justCount) {
1555                             res += intr;
1556                         } else {
1557                             for (var k = 0, kk = intr.length; k < kk; k++) {
1558                                 intr[k].segment1 = i;
1559                                 intr[k].segment2 = j;
1560                                 intr[k].bez1 = bez1;
1561                                 intr[k].bez2 = bez2;
1562                             }
1563                             res = res.concat(intr);
1564                         }
1565                     }
1566                 }
1567             }
1568         }
1569         return res;
1570     }
1571     /*\
1572      * Raphael.isPointInsidePath
1573      [ method ]
1574      **
1575      * Utility method
1576      **
1577      * Returns `true` if given point is inside a given closed path.
1578      > Parameters
1579      - path (string) path string
1580      - x (number) x of the point
1581      - y (number) y of the point
1582      = (boolean) true, if point is inside the path
1583     \*/
1584     R.isPointInsidePath = function (path, x, y) {
1585         var bbox = R.pathBBox(path);
1586         return R.isPointInsideBBox(bbox, x, y) &&
1587                interPathHelper(path, [["M", x, y], ["H", bbox.x2 + 10]], 1) % 2 == 1;
1588     };
1589     R._removedFactory = function (methodname) {
1590         return function () {
1591             eve("raphael.log", null, "Rapha\xebl: you are calling to method \u201c" + methodname + "\u201d of removed object", methodname);
1592         };
1593     };
1594     /*\
1595      * Raphael.pathBBox
1596      [ method ]
1597      **
1598      * Utility method
1599      **
1600      * Return bounding box of a given path
1601      > Parameters
1602      - path (string) path string
1603      = (object) bounding box
1604      o {
1605      o     x: (number) x coordinate of the left top point of the box
1606      o     y: (number) y coordinate of the left top point of the box
1607      o     x2: (number) x coordinate of the right bottom point of the box
1608      o     y2: (number) y coordinate of the right bottom point of the box
1609      o     width: (number) width of the box
1610      o     height: (number) height of the box
1611      o     cx: (number) x coordinate of the center of the box
1612      o     cy: (number) y coordinate of the center of the box
1613      o }
1614     \*/
1615     var pathDimensions = R.pathBBox = function (path) {
1616         var pth = paths(path);
1617         if (pth.bbox) {
1618             return clone(pth.bbox);
1619         }
1620         if (!path) {
1621             return {x: 0, y: 0, width: 0, height: 0, x2: 0, y2: 0};
1622         }
1623         path = path2curve(path);
1624         var x = 0,
1625             y = 0,
1626             X = [],
1627             Y = [],
1628             p;
1629         for (var i = 0, ii = path.length; i < ii; i++) {
1630             p = path[i];
1631             if (p[0] == "M") {
1632                 x = p[1];
1633                 y = p[2];
1634                 X.push(x);
1635                 Y.push(y);
1636             } else {
1637                 var dim = curveDim(x, y, p[1], p[2], p[3], p[4], p[5], p[6]);
1638                 X = X[concat](dim.min.x, dim.max.x);
1639                 Y = Y[concat](dim.min.y, dim.max.y);
1640                 x = p[5];
1641                 y = p[6];
1642             }
1643         }
1644         var xmin = mmin[apply](0, X),
1645             ymin = mmin[apply](0, Y),
1646             xmax = mmax[apply](0, X),
1647             ymax = mmax[apply](0, Y),
1648             width = xmax - xmin,
1649             height = ymax - ymin,
1650                 bb = {
1651                 x: xmin,
1652                 y: ymin,
1653                 x2: xmax,
1654                 y2: ymax,
1655                 width: width,
1656                 height: height,
1657                 cx: xmin + width / 2,
1658                 cy: ymin + height / 2
1659             };
1660         pth.bbox = clone(bb);
1661         return bb;
1662     },
1663         pathClone = function (pathArray) {
1664             var res = clone(pathArray);
1665             res.toString = R._path2string;
1666             return res;
1667         },
1668         pathToRelative = R._pathToRelative = function (pathArray) {
1669             var pth = paths(pathArray);
1670             if (pth.rel) {
1671                 return pathClone(pth.rel);
1672             }
1673             if (!R.is(pathArray, array) || !R.is(pathArray && pathArray[0], array)) { // rough assumption
1674                 pathArray = R.parsePathString(pathArray);
1675             }
1676             var res = [],
1677                 x = 0,
1678                 y = 0,
1679                 mx = 0,
1680                 my = 0,
1681                 start = 0;
1682             if (pathArray[0][0] == "M") {
1683                 x = pathArray[0][1];
1684                 y = pathArray[0][2];
1685                 mx = x;
1686                 my = y;
1687                 start++;
1688                 res.push(["M", x, y]);
1689             }
1690             for (var i = start, ii = pathArray.length; i < ii; i++) {
1691                 var r = res[i] = [],
1692                     pa = pathArray[i];
1693                 if (pa[0] != lowerCase.call(pa[0])) {
1694                     r[0] = lowerCase.call(pa[0]);
1695                     switch (r[0]) {
1696                         case "a":
1697                             r[1] = pa[1];
1698                             r[2] = pa[2];
1699                             r[3] = pa[3];
1700                             r[4] = pa[4];
1701                             r[5] = pa[5];
1702                             r[6] = +(pa[6] - x).toFixed(3);
1703                             r[7] = +(pa[7] - y).toFixed(3);
1704                             break;
1705                         case "v":
1706                             r[1] = +(pa[1] - y).toFixed(3);
1707                             break;
1708                         case "m":
1709                             mx = pa[1];
1710                             my = pa[2];
1711                         default:
1712                             for (var j = 1, jj = pa.length; j < jj; j++) {
1713                                 r[j] = +(pa[j] - ((j % 2) ? x : y)).toFixed(3);
1714                             }
1715                     }
1716                 } else {
1717                     r = res[i] = [];
1718                     if (pa[0] == "m") {
1719                         mx = pa[1] + x;
1720                         my = pa[2] + y;
1721                     }
1722                     for (var k = 0, kk = pa.length; k < kk; k++) {
1723                         res[i][k] = pa[k];
1724                     }
1725                 }
1726                 var len = res[i].length;
1727                 switch (res[i][0]) {
1728                     case "z":
1729                         x = mx;
1730                         y = my;
1731                         break;
1732                     case "h":
1733                         x += +res[i][len - 1];
1734                         break;
1735                     case "v":
1736                         y += +res[i][len - 1];
1737                         break;
1738                     default:
1739                         x += +res[i][len - 2];
1740                         y += +res[i][len - 1];
1741                 }
1742             }
1743             res.toString = R._path2string;
1744             pth.rel = pathClone(res);
1745             return res;
1746         },
1747         pathToAbsolute = R._pathToAbsolute = function (pathArray) {
1748             var pth = paths(pathArray);
1749             if (pth.abs) {
1750                 return pathClone(pth.abs);
1751             }
1752             if (!R.is(pathArray, array) || !R.is(pathArray && pathArray[0], array)) { // rough assumption
1753                 pathArray = R.parsePathString(pathArray);
1754             }
1755             if (!pathArray || !pathArray.length) {
1756                 return [["M", 0, 0]];
1757             }
1758             var res = [],
1759                 x = 0,
1760                 y = 0,
1761                 mx = 0,
1762                 my = 0,
1763                 start = 0;
1764             if (pathArray[0][0] == "M") {
1765                 x = +pathArray[0][1];
1766                 y = +pathArray[0][2];
1767                 mx = x;
1768                 my = y;
1769                 start++;
1770                 res[0] = ["M", x, y];
1771             }
1772             var crz = pathArray.length == 3 && pathArray[0][0] == "M" && pathArray[1][0].toUpperCase() == "R" && pathArray[2][0].toUpperCase() == "Z";
1773             for (var r, pa, i = start, ii = pathArray.length; i < ii; i++) {
1774                 res.push(r = []);
1775                 pa = pathArray[i];
1776                 if (pa[0] != upperCase.call(pa[0])) {
1777                     r[0] = upperCase.call(pa[0]);
1778                     switch (r[0]) {
1779                         case "A":
1780                             r[1] = pa[1];
1781                             r[2] = pa[2];
1782                             r[3] = pa[3];
1783                             r[4] = pa[4];
1784                             r[5] = pa[5];
1785                             r[6] = +(pa[6] + x);
1786                             r[7] = +(pa[7] + y);
1787                             break;
1788                         case "V":
1789                             r[1] = +pa[1] + y;
1790                             break;
1791                         case "H":
1792                             r[1] = +pa[1] + x;
1793                             break;
1794                         case "R":
1795                             var dots = [x, y][concat](pa.slice(1));
1796                             for (var j = 2, jj = dots.length; j < jj; j++) {
1797                                 dots[j] = +dots[j] + x;
1798                                 dots[++j] = +dots[j] + y;
1799                             }
1800                             res.pop();
1801                             res = res[concat](catmullRom2bezier(dots, crz));
1802                             break;
1803                         case "M":
1804                             mx = +pa[1] + x;
1805                             my = +pa[2] + y;
1806                         default:
1807                             for (j = 1, jj = pa.length; j < jj; j++) {
1808                                 r[j] = +pa[j] + ((j % 2) ? x : y);
1809                             }
1810                     }
1811                 } else if (pa[0] == "R") {
1812                     dots = [x, y][concat](pa.slice(1));
1813                     res.pop();
1814                     res = res[concat](catmullRom2bezier(dots, crz));
1815                     r = ["R"][concat](pa.slice(-2));
1816                 } else {
1817                     for (var k = 0, kk = pa.length; k < kk; k++) {
1818                         r[k] = pa[k];
1819                     }
1820                 }
1821                 switch (r[0]) {
1822                     case "Z":
1823                         x = mx;
1824                         y = my;
1825                         break;
1826                     case "H":
1827                         x = r[1];
1828                         break;
1829                     case "V":
1830                         y = r[1];
1831                         break;
1832                     case "M":
1833                         mx = r[r.length - 2];
1834                         my = r[r.length - 1];
1835                     default:
1836                         x = r[r.length - 2];
1837                         y = r[r.length - 1];
1838                 }
1839             }
1840             res.toString = R._path2string;
1841             pth.abs = pathClone(res);
1842             return res;
1843         },
1844         l2c = function (x1, y1, x2, y2) {
1845             return [x1, y1, x2, y2, x2, y2];
1846         },
1847         q2c = function (x1, y1, ax, ay, x2, y2) {
1848             var _13 = 1 / 3,
1849                 _23 = 2 / 3;
1850             return [
1851                     _13 * x1 + _23 * ax,
1852                     _13 * y1 + _23 * ay,
1853                     _13 * x2 + _23 * ax,
1854                     _13 * y2 + _23 * ay,
1855                     x2,
1856                     y2
1857                 ];
1858         },
1859         a2c = function (x1, y1, rx, ry, angle, large_arc_flag, sweep_flag, x2, y2, recursive) {
1860             // for more information of where this math came from visit:
1861             // http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG11/implnote.html#ArcImplementationNotes
1862             var _120 = PI * 120 / 180,
1863                 rad = PI / 180 * (+angle || 0),
1864                 res = [],
1865                 xy,
1866                 rotate = cacher(function (x, y, rad) {
1867                     var X = x * math.cos(rad) - y * math.sin(rad),
1868                         Y = x * math.sin(rad) + y * math.cos(rad);
1869                     return {x: X, y: Y};
1870                 });
1871             if (!recursive) {
1872                 xy = rotate(x1, y1, -rad);
1873                 x1 = xy.x;
1874                 y1 = xy.y;
1875                 xy = rotate(x2, y2, -rad);
1876                 x2 = xy.x;
1877                 y2 = xy.y;
1878                 var cos = math.cos(PI / 180 * angle),
1879                     sin = math.sin(PI / 180 * angle),
1880                     x = (x1 - x2) / 2,
1881                     y = (y1 - y2) / 2;
1882                 var h = (x * x) / (rx * rx) + (y * y) / (ry * ry);
1883                 if (h > 1) {
1884                     h = math.sqrt(h);
1885                     rx = h * rx;
1886                     ry = h * ry;
1887                 }
1888                 var rx2 = rx * rx,
1889                     ry2 = ry * ry,
1890                     k = (large_arc_flag == sweep_flag ? -1 : 1) *
1891                         math.sqrt(abs((rx2 * ry2 - rx2 * y * y - ry2 * x * x) / (rx2 * y * y + ry2 * x * x))),
1892                     cx = k * rx * y / ry + (x1 + x2) / 2,
1893                     cy = k * -ry * x / rx + (y1 + y2) / 2,
1894                     f1 = math.asin(((y1 - cy) / ry).toFixed(9)),
1895                     f2 = math.asin(((y2 - cy) / ry).toFixed(9));
1896 
1897                 f1 = x1 < cx ? PI - f1 : f1;
1898                 f2 = x2 < cx ? PI - f2 : f2;
1899                 f1 < 0 && (f1 = PI * 2 + f1);
1900                 f2 < 0 && (f2 = PI * 2 + f2);
1901                 if (sweep_flag && f1 > f2) {
1902                     f1 = f1 - PI * 2;
1903                 }
1904                 if (!sweep_flag && f2 > f1) {
1905                     f2 = f2 - PI * 2;
1906                 }
1907             } else {
1908                 f1 = recursive[0];
1909                 f2 = recursive[1];
1910                 cx = recursive[2];
1911                 cy = recursive[3];
1912             }
1913             var df = f2 - f1;
1914             if (abs(df) > _120) {
1915                 var f2old = f2,
1916                     x2old = x2,
1917                     y2old = y2;
1918                 f2 = f1 + _120 * (sweep_flag && f2 > f1 ? 1 : -1);
1919                 x2 = cx + rx * math.cos(f2);
1920                 y2 = cy + ry * math.sin(f2);
1921                 res = a2c(x2, y2, rx, ry, angle, 0, sweep_flag, x2old, y2old, [f2, f2old, cx, cy]);
1922             }
1923             df = f2 - f1;
1924             var c1 = math.cos(f1),
1925                 s1 = math.sin(f1),
1926                 c2 = math.cos(f2),
1927                 s2 = math.sin(f2),
1928                 t = math.tan(df / 4),
1929                 hx = 4 / 3 * rx * t,
1930                 hy = 4 / 3 * ry * t,
1931                 m1 = [x1, y1],
1932                 m2 = [x1 + hx * s1, y1 - hy * c1],
1933                 m3 = [x2 + hx * s2, y2 - hy * c2],
1934                 m4 = [x2, y2];
1935             m2[0] = 2 * m1[0] - m2[0];
1936             m2[1] = 2 * m1[1] - m2[1];
1937             if (recursive) {
1938                 return [m2, m3, m4][concat](res);
1939             } else {
1940                 res = [m2, m3, m4][concat](res).join()[split](",");
1941                 var newres = [];
1942                 for (var i = 0, ii = res.length; i < ii; i++) {
1943                     newres[i] = i % 2 ? rotate(res[i - 1], res[i], rad).y : rotate(res[i], res[i + 1], rad).x;
1944                 }
1945                 return newres;
1946             }
1947         },
1948         findDotAtSegment = function (p1x, p1y, c1x, c1y, c2x, c2y, p2x, p2y, t) {
1949             var t1 = 1 - t;
1950             return {
1951                 x: pow(t1, 3) * p1x + pow(t1, 2) * 3 * t * c1x + t1 * 3 * t * t * c2x + pow(t, 3) * p2x,
1952                 y: pow(t1, 3) * p1y + pow(t1, 2) * 3 * t * c1y + t1 * 3 * t * t * c2y + pow(t, 3) * p2y
1953             };
1954         },
1955         curveDim = cacher(function (p1x, p1y, c1x, c1y, c2x, c2y, p2x, p2y) {
1956             var a = (c2x - 2 * c1x + p1x) - (p2x - 2 * c2x + c1x),
1957                 b = 2 * (c1x - p1x) - 2 * (c2x - c1x),
1958                 c = p1x - c1x,
1959                 t1 = (-b + math.sqrt(b * b - 4 * a * c)) / 2 / a,
1960                 t2 = (-b - math.sqrt(b * b - 4 * a * c)) / 2 / a,
1961                 y = [p1y, p2y],
1962                 x = [p1x, p2x],
1963                 dot;
1964             abs(t1) > "1e12" && (t1 = .5);
1965             abs(t2) > "1e12" && (t2 = .5);
1966             if (t1 > 0 && t1 < 1) {
1967                 dot = findDotAtSegment(p1x, p1y, c1x, c1y, c2x, c2y, p2x, p2y, t1);
1968                 x.push(dot.x);
1969                 y.push(dot.y);
1970             }
1971             if (t2 > 0 && t2 < 1) {
1972                 dot = findDotAtSegment(p1x, p1y, c1x, c1y, c2x, c2y, p2x, p2y, t2);
1973                 x.push(dot.x);
1974                 y.push(dot.y);
1975             }
1976             a = (c2y - 2 * c1y + p1y) - (p2y - 2 * c2y + c1y);
1977             b = 2 * (c1y - p1y) - 2 * (c2y - c1y);
1978             c = p1y - c1y;
1979             t1 = (-b + math.sqrt(b * b - 4 * a * c)) / 2 / a;
1980             t2 = (-b - math.sqrt(b * b - 4 * a * c)) / 2 / a;
1981             abs(t1) > "1e12" && (t1 = .5);
1982             abs(t2) > "1e12" && (t2 = .5);
1983             if (t1 > 0 && t1 < 1) {
1984                 dot = findDotAtSegment(p1x, p1y, c1x, c1y, c2x, c2y, p2x, p2y, t1);
1985                 x.push(dot.x);
1986                 y.push(dot.y);
1987             }
1988             if (t2 > 0 && t2 < 1) {
1989                 dot = findDotAtSegment(p1x, p1y, c1x, c1y, c2x, c2y, p2x, p2y, t2);
1990                 x.push(dot.x);
1991                 y.push(dot.y);
1992             }
1993             return {
1994                 min: {x: mmin[apply](0, x), y: mmin[apply](0, y)},
1995                 max: {x: mmax[apply](0, x), y: mmax[apply](0, y)}
1996             };
1997         }),
1998         path2curve = R._path2curve = cacher(function (path, path2) {
1999             var pth = !path2 && paths(path);
2000             if (!path2 && pth.curve) {
2001                 return pathClone(pth.curve);
2002             }
2003             var p = pathToAbsolute(path),
2004                 p2 = path2 && pathToAbsolute(path2),
2005                 attrs = {x: 0, y: 0, bx: 0, by: 0, X: 0, Y: 0, qx: null, qy: null},
2006                 attrs2 = {x: 0, y: 0, bx: 0, by: 0, X: 0, Y: 0, qx: null, qy: null},
2007                 processPath = function (path, d, pcom) {
2008                     var nx, ny, tq = {T:1, Q:1};
2009                     if (!path) {
2010                         return ["C", d.x, d.y, d.x, d.y, d.x, d.y];
2011                     }
2012                     !(path[0] in tq) && (d.qx = d.qy = null);
2013                     switch (path[0]) {
2014                         case "M":
2015                             d.X = path[1];
2016                             d.Y = path[2];
2017                             break;
2018                         case "A":
2019                             path = ["C"][concat](a2c[apply](0, [d.x, d.y][concat](path.slice(1))));
2020                             break;
2021                         case "S":
2022                             if (pcom == "C" || pcom == "S") { // In "S" case we have to take into account, if the previous command is C/S.
2023                                 nx = d.x * 2 - d.bx;          // And reflect the previous
2024                                 ny = d.y * 2 - d.by;          // command's control point relative to the current point.
2025                             }
2026                             else {                            // or some else or nothing
2027                                 nx = d.x;
2028                                 ny = d.y;
2029                             }
2030                             path = ["C", nx, ny][concat](path.slice(1));
2031                             break;
2032                         case "T":
2033                             if (pcom == "Q" || pcom == "T") { // In "T" case we have to take into account, if the previous command is Q/T.
2034                                 d.qx = d.x * 2 - d.qx;        // And make a reflection similar
2035                                 d.qy = d.y * 2 - d.qy;        // to case "S".
2036                             }
2037                             else {                            // or something else or nothing
2038                                 d.qx = d.x;
2039                                 d.qy = d.y;
2040                             }
2041                             path = ["C"][concat](q2c(d.x, d.y, d.qx, d.qy, path[1], path[2]));
2042                             break;
2043                         case "Q":
2044                             d.qx = path[1];
2045                             d.qy = path[2];
2046                             path = ["C"][concat](q2c(d.x, d.y, path[1], path[2], path[3], path[4]));
2047                             break;
2048                         case "L":
2049                             path = ["C"][concat](l2c(d.x, d.y, path[1], path[2]));
2050                             break;
2051                         case "H":
2052                             path = ["C"][concat](l2c(d.x, d.y, path[1], d.y));
2053                             break;
2054                         case "V":
2055                             path = ["C"][concat](l2c(d.x, d.y, d.x, path[1]));
2056                             break;
2057                         case "Z":
2058                             path = ["C"][concat](l2c(d.x, d.y, d.X, d.Y));
2059                             break;
2060                     }
2061                     return path;
2062                 },
2063                 fixArc = function (pp, i) {
2064                     if (pp[i].length > 7) {
2065                         pp[i].shift();
2066                         var pi = pp[i];
2067                         while (pi.length) {
2068                             pcoms1[i]="A"; // if created multiple C:s, their original seg is saved
2069                             p2 && (pcoms2[i]="A"); // the same as above
2070                             pp.splice(i++, 0, ["C"][concat](pi.splice(0, 6)));
2071                         }
2072                         pp.splice(i, 1);
2073                         ii = mmax(p.length, p2 && p2.length || 0);
2074                     }
2075                 },
2076                 fixM = function (path1, path2, a1, a2, i) {
2077                     if (path1 && path2 && path1[i][0] == "M" && path2[i][0] != "M") {
2078                         path2.splice(i, 0, ["M", a2.x, a2.y]);
2079                         a1.bx = 0;
2080                         a1.by = 0;
2081                         a1.x = path1[i][1];
2082                         a1.y = path1[i][2];
2083                         ii = mmax(p.length, p2 && p2.length || 0);
2084                     }
2085                 },
2086                 pcoms1 = [], // path commands of original path p
2087                 pcoms2 = [], // path commands of original path p2
2088                 pfirst = "", // temporary holder for original path command
2089                 pcom = ""; // holder for previous path command of original path
2090             for (var i = 0, ii = mmax(p.length, p2 && p2.length || 0); i < ii; i++) {
2091                 p[i] && (pfirst = p[i][0]); // save current path command
2092 
2093                 if (pfirst != "C") // C is not saved yet, because it may be result of conversion
2094                 {
2095                     pcoms1[i] = pfirst; // Save current path command
2096                     i && ( pcom = pcoms1[i-1]); // Get previous path command pcom
2097                 }
2098                 p[i] = processPath(p[i], attrs, pcom); // Previous path command is inputted to processPath
2099 
2100                 if (pcoms1[i] != "A" && pfirst == "C") pcoms1[i] = "C"; // A is the only command
2101                 // which may produce multiple C:s
2102                 // so we have to make sure that C is also C in original path
2103 
2104                 fixArc(p, i); // fixArc adds also the right amount of A:s to pcoms1
2105 
2106                 if (p2) { // the same procedures is done to p2
2107                     p2[i] && (pfirst = p2[i][0]);
2108                     if (pfirst != "C")
2109                     {
2110                         pcoms2[i] = pfirst;
2111                         i && (pcom = pcoms2[i-1]);
2112                     }
2113                     p2[i] = processPath(p2[i], attrs2, pcom);
2114 
2115                     if (pcoms2[i]!="A" && pfirst=="C") pcoms2[i]="C";
2116 
2117                     fixArc(p2, i);
2118                 }
2119                 fixM(p, p2, attrs, attrs2, i);
2120                 fixM(p2, p, attrs2, attrs, i);
2121                 var seg = p[i],
2122                     seg2 = p2 && p2[i],
2123                     seglen = seg.length,
2124                     seg2len = p2 && seg2.length;
2125                 attrs.x = seg[seglen - 2];
2126                 attrs.y = seg[seglen - 1];
2127                 attrs.bx = toFloat(seg[seglen - 4]) || attrs.x;
2128                 attrs.by = toFloat(seg[seglen - 3]) || attrs.y;
2129                 attrs2.bx = p2 && (toFloat(seg2[seg2len - 4]) || attrs2.x);
2130                 attrs2.by = p2 && (toFloat(seg2[seg2len - 3]) || attrs2.y);
2131                 attrs2.x = p2 && seg2[seg2len - 2];
2132                 attrs2.y = p2 && seg2[seg2len - 1];
2133             }
2134             if (!p2) {
2135                 pth.curve = pathClone(p);
2136             }
2137             return p2 ? [p, p2] : p;
2138         }, null, pathClone),
2139         parseDots = R._parseDots = cacher(function (gradient) {
2140             var dots = [];
2141             for (var i = 0, ii = gradient.length; i < ii; i++) {
2142                 var dot = {},
2143                     par = gradient[i].match(/^([^:]*):?([\d\.]*)/);
2144                 dot.color = R.getRGB(par[1]);
2145                 if (dot.color.error) {
2146                     return null;
2147                 }
2148                 dot.color = dot.color.hex;
2149                 par[2] && (dot.offset = par[2] + "%");
2150                 dots.push(dot);
2151             }
2152             for (i = 1, ii = dots.length - 1; i < ii; i++) {
2153                 if (!dots[i].offset) {
2154                     var start = toFloat(dots[i - 1].offset || 0),
2155                         end = 0;
2156                     for (var j = i + 1; j < ii; j++) {
2157                         if (dots[j].offset) {
2158                             end = dots[j].offset;
2159                             break;
2160                         }
2161                     }
2162                     if (!end) {
2163                         end = 100;
2164                         j = ii;
2165                     }
2166                     end = toFloat(end);
2167                     var d = (end - start) / (j - i + 1);
2168                     for (; i < j; i++) {
2169                         start += d;
2170                         dots[i].offset = start + "%";
2171                     }
2172                 }
2173             }
2174             return dots;
2175         }),
2176         tear = R._tear = function (el, paper) {
2177             el == paper.top && (paper.top = el.prev);
2178             el == paper.bottom && (paper.bottom = el.next);
2179             el.next && (el.next.prev = el.prev);
2180             el.prev && (el.prev.next = el.next);
2181         },
2182         tofront = R._tofront = function (el, paper) {
2183             if (paper.top === el) {
2184                 return;
2185             }
2186             tear(el, paper);
2187             el.next = null;
2188             el.prev = paper.top;
2189             paper.top.next = el;
2190             paper.top = el;
2191         },
2192         toback = R._toback = function (el, paper) {
2193             if (paper.bottom === el) {
2194                 return;
2195             }
2196             tear(el, paper);
2197             el.next = paper.bottom;
2198             el.prev = null;
2199             paper.bottom.prev = el;
2200             paper.bottom = el;
2201         },
2202         insertafter = R._insertafter = function (el, el2, paper) {
2203             tear(el, paper);
2204             el2 == paper.top && (paper.top = el);
2205             el2.next && (el2.next.prev = el);
2206             el.next = el2.next;
2207             el.prev = el2;
2208             el2.next = el;
2209         },
2210         insertbefore = R._insertbefore = function (el, el2, paper) {
2211             tear(el, paper);
2212             el2 == paper.bottom && (paper.bottom = el);
2213             el2.prev && (el2.prev.next = el);
2214             el.prev = el2.prev;
2215             el2.prev = el;
2216             el.next = el2;
2217         },
2218         /*\
2219          * Raphael.toMatrix
2220          [ method ]
2221          **
2222          * Utility method
2223          **
2224          * Returns matrix of transformations applied to a given path
2225          > Parameters
2226          - path (string) path string
2227          - transform (string|array) transformation string
2228          = (object) @Matrix
2229         \*/
2230         toMatrix = R.toMatrix = function (path, transform) {
2231             var bb = pathDimensions(path),
2232                 el = {
2233                     _: {
2234                         transform: E
2235                     },
2236                     getBBox: function () {
2237                         return bb;
2238                     }
2239                 };
2240             extractTransform(el, transform);
2241             return el.matrix;
2242         },
2243         /*\
2244          * Raphael.transformPath
2245          [ method ]
2246          **
2247          * Utility method
2248          **
2249          * Returns path transformed by a given transformation
2250          > Parameters
2251          - path (string) path string
2252          - transform (string|array) transformation string
2253          = (string) path
2254         \*/
2255         transformPath = R.transformPath = function (path, transform) {
2256             return mapPath(path, toMatrix(path, transform));
2257         },
2258         extractTransform = R._extractTransform = function (el, tstr) {
2259             if (tstr == null) {
2260                 return el._.transform;
2261             }
2262             tstr = Str(tstr).replace(/\.{3}|\u2026/g, el._.transform || E);
2263             var tdata = R.parseTransformString(tstr),
2264                 deg = 0,
2265                 dx = 0,
2266                 dy = 0,
2267                 sx = 1,
2268                 sy = 1,
2269                 _ = el._,
2270                 m = new Matrix;
2271             _.transform = tdata || [];
2272             if (tdata) {
2273                 for (var i = 0, ii = tdata.length; i < ii; i++) {
2274                     var t = tdata[i],
2275                         tlen = t.length,
2276                         command = Str(t[0]).toLowerCase(),
2277                         absolute = t[0] != command,
2278                         inver = absolute ? m.invert() : 0,
2279                         x1,
2280                         y1,
2281                         x2,
2282                         y2,
2283                         bb;
2284                     if (command == "t" && tlen == 3) {
2285                         if (absolute) {
2286                             x1 = inver.x(0, 0);
2287                             y1 = inver.y(0, 0);
2288                             x2 = inver.x(t[1], t[2]);
2289                             y2 = inver.y(t[1], t[2]);
2290                             m.translate(x2 - x1, y2 - y1);
2291                         } else {
2292                             m.translate(t[1], t[2]);
2293                         }
2294                     } else if (command == "r") {
2295                         if (tlen == 2) {
2296                             bb = bb || el.getBBox(1);
2297                             m.rotate(t[1], bb.x + bb.width / 2, bb.y + bb.height / 2);
2298                             deg += t[1];
2299                         } else if (tlen == 4) {
2300                             if (absolute) {
2301                                 x2 = inver.x(t[2], t[3]);
2302                                 y2 = inver.y(t[2], t[3]);
2303                                 m.rotate(t[1], x2, y2);
2304                             } else {
2305                                 m.rotate(t[1], t[2], t[3]);
2306                             }
2307                             deg += t[1];
2308                         }
2309                     } else if (command == "s") {
2310                         if (tlen == 2 || tlen == 3) {
2311                             bb = bb || el.getBBox(1);
2312                             m.scale(t[1], t[tlen - 1], bb.x + bb.width / 2, bb.y + bb.height / 2);
2313                             sx *= t[1];
2314                             sy *= t[tlen - 1];
2315                         } else if (tlen == 5) {
2316                             if (absolute) {
2317                                 x2 = inver.x(t[3], t[4]);
2318                                 y2 = inver.y(t[3], t[4]);
2319                                 m.scale(t[1], t[2], x2, y2);
2320                             } else {
2321                                 m.scale(t[1], t[2], t[3], t[4]);
2322                             }
2323                             sx *= t[1];
2324                             sy *= t[2];
2325                         }
2326                     } else if (command == "m" && tlen == 7) {
2327                         m.add(t[1], t[2], t[3], t[4], t[5], t[6]);
2328                     }
2329                     _.dirtyT = 1;
2330                     el.matrix = m;
2331                 }
2332             }
2333 
2334             /*\
2335              * Element.matrix
2336              [ property (object) ]
2337              **
2338              * Keeps @Matrix object, which represents element transformation
2339             \*/
2340             el.matrix = m;
2341 
2342             _.sx = sx;
2343             _.sy = sy;
2344             _.deg = deg;
2345             _.dx = dx = m.e;
2346             _.dy = dy = m.f;
2347 
2348             if (sx == 1 && sy == 1 && !deg && _.bbox) {
2349                 _.bbox.x += +dx;
2350                 _.bbox.y += +dy;
2351             } else {
2352                 _.dirtyT = 1;
2353             }
2354         },
2355         getEmpty = function (item) {
2356             var l = item[0];
2357             switch (l.toLowerCase()) {
2358                 case "t": return [l, 0, 0];
2359                 case "m": return [l, 1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0];
2360                 case "r": if (item.length == 4) {
2361                     return [l, 0, item[2], item[3]];
2362                 } else {
2363                     return [l, 0];
2364                 }
2365                 case "s": if (item.length == 5) {
2366                     return [l, 1, 1, item[3], item[4]];
2367                 } else if (item.length == 3) {
2368                     return [l, 1, 1];
2369                 } else {
2370                     return [l, 1];
2371                 }
2372             }
2373         },
2374         equaliseTransform = R._equaliseTransform = function (t1, t2) {
2375             t2 = Str(t2).replace(/\.{3}|\u2026/g, t1);
2376             t1 = R.parseTransformString(t1) || [];
2377             t2 = R.parseTransformString(t2) || [];
2378             var maxlength = mmax(t1.length, t2.length),
2379                 from = [],
2380                 to = [],
2381                 i = 0, j, jj,
2382                 tt1, tt2;
2383             for (; i < maxlength; i++) {
2384                 tt1 = t1[i] || getEmpty(t2[i]);
2385                 tt2 = t2[i] || getEmpty(tt1);
2386                 if ((tt1[0] != tt2[0]) ||
2387                     (tt1[0].toLowerCase() == "r" && (tt1[2] != tt2[2] || tt1[3] != tt2[3])) ||
2388                     (tt1[0].toLowerCase() == "s" && (tt1[3] != tt2[3] || tt1[4] != tt2[4]))
2389                     ) {
2390                     return;
2391                 }
2392                 from[i] = [];
2393                 to[i] = [];
2394                 for (j = 0, jj = mmax(tt1.length, tt2.length); j < jj; j++) {
2395                     j in tt1 && (from[i][j] = tt1[j]);
2396                     j in tt2 && (to[i][j] = tt2[j]);
2397                 }
2398             }
2399             return {
2400                 from: from,
2401                 to: to
2402             };
2403         };
2404     R._getContainer = function (x, y, w, h) {
2405         var container;
2406         container = h == null && !R.is(x, "object") ? g.doc.getElementById(x) : x;
2407         if (container == null) {
2408             return;
2409         }
2410         if (container.tagName) {
2411             if (y == null) {
2412                 return {
2413                     container: container,
2414                     width: container.style.pixelWidth || container.offsetWidth,
2415                     height: container.style.pixelHeight || container.offsetHeight
2416                 };
2417             } else {
2418                 return {
2419                     container: container,
2420                     width: y,
2421                     height: w
2422                 };
2423             }
2424         }
2425         return {
2426             container: 1,
2427             x: x,
2428             y: y,
2429             width: w,
2430             height: h
2431         };
2432     };

2458     /*\
2459      * Raphael.matrix
2460      [ method ]
2461      **
2462      * Utility method
2463      **
2464      * Returns matrix based on given parameters.
2465      > Parameters
2466      - a (number)
2467      - b (number)
2468      - c (number)
2469      - d (number)
2470      - e (number)
2471      - f (number)
2472      = (object) @Matrix
2473     \*/
2474     R.matrix = function (a, b, c, d, e, f) {
2475         return new Matrix(a, b, c, d, e, f);
2476     };
2477     function Matrix(a, b, c, d, e, f) {
2478         if (a != null) {
2479             this.a = +a;
2480             this.b = +b;
2481             this.c = +c;
2482             this.d = +d;
2483             this.e = +e;
2484             this.f = +f;
2485         } else {
2486             this.a = 1;
2487             this.b = 0;
2488             this.c = 0;
2489             this.d = 1;
2490             this.e = 0;
2491             this.f = 0;
2492         }
2493     }
2494     (function (matrixproto) {
2495         /*\
2496          * Matrix.add
2497          [ method ]
2498          **
2499          * Adds given matrix to existing one.
2500          > Parameters
2501          - a (number)
2502          - b (number)
2503          - c (number)
2504          - d (number)
2505          - e (number)
2506          - f (number)
2507          or
2508          - matrix (object) @Matrix
2509         \*/
2510         matrixproto.add = function (a, b, c, d, e, f) {
2511             var out = [[], [], []],
2512                 m = [[this.a, this.c, this.e], [this.b, this.d, this.f], [0, 0, 1]],
2513                 matrix = [[a, c, e], [b, d, f], [0, 0, 1]],
2514                 x, y, z, res;
2515 
2516             if (a && a instanceof Matrix) {
2517                 matrix = [[a.a, a.c, a.e], [a.b, a.d, a.f], [0, 0, 1]];
2518             }
2519 
2520             for (x = 0; x < 3; x++) {
2521                 for (y = 0; y < 3; y++) {
2522                     res = 0;
2523                     for (z = 0; z < 3; z++) {
2524                         res += m[x][z] * matrix[z][y];
2525                     }
2526                     out[x][y] = res;
2527                 }
2528             }
2529             this.a = out[0][0];
2530             this.b = out[1][0];
2531             this.c = out[0][1];
2532             this.d = out[1][1];
2533             this.e = out[0][2];
2534             this.f = out[1][2];
2535         };
2536         /*\
2537          * Matrix.invert
2538          [ method ]
2539          **
2540          * Returns inverted version of the matrix
2541          = (object) @Matrix
2542         \*/
2543         matrixproto.invert = function () {
2544             var me = this,
2545                 x = me.a * me.d - me.b * me.c;
2546             return new Matrix(me.d / x, -me.b / x, -me.c / x, me.a / x, (me.c * me.f - me.d * me.e) / x, (me.b * me.e - me.a * me.f) / x);
2547         };
2548         /*\
2549          * Matrix.clone
2550          [ method ]
2551          **
2552          * Returns copy of the matrix
2553          = (object) @Matrix
2554         \*/
2555         matrixproto.clone = function () {
2556             return new Matrix(this.a, this.b, this.c, this.d, this.e, this.f);
2557         };
2558         /*\
2559          * Matrix.translate
2560          [ method ]
2561          **
2562          * Translate the matrix
2563          > Parameters
2564          - x (number)
2565          - y (number)
2566         \*/
2567         matrixproto.translate = function (x, y) {
2568             this.add(1, 0, 0, 1, x, y);
2569         };
2570         /*\
2571          * Matrix.scale
2572          [ method ]
2573          **
2574          * Scales the matrix
2575          > Parameters
2576          - x (number)
2577          - y (number) #optional
2578          - cx (number) #optional
2579          - cy (number) #optional
2580         \*/
2581         matrixproto.scale = function (x, y, cx, cy) {
2582             y == null && (y = x);
2583             (cx || cy) && this.add(1, 0, 0, 1, cx, cy);
2584             this.add(x, 0, 0, y, 0, 0);
2585             (cx || cy) && this.add(1, 0, 0, 1, -cx, -cy);
2586         };
2587         /*\
2588          * Matrix.rotate
2589          [ method ]
2590          **
2591          * Rotates the matrix
2592          > Parameters
2593          - a (number)
2594          - x (number)
2595          - y (number)
2596         \*/
2597         matrixproto.rotate = function (a, x, y) {
2598             a = R.rad(a);
2599             x = x || 0;
2600             y = y || 0;
2601             var cos = +math.cos(a).toFixed(9),
2602                 sin = +math.sin(a).toFixed(9);
2603             this.add(cos, sin, -sin, cos, x, y);
2604             this.add(1, 0, 0, 1, -x, -y);
2605         };
2606         /*\
2607          * Matrix.x
2608          [ method ]
2609          **
2610          * Return x coordinate for given point after transformation described by the matrix. See also @Matrix.y
2611          > Parameters
2612          - x (number)
2613          - y (number)
2614          = (number) x
2615         \*/
2616         matrixproto.x = function (x, y) {
2617             return x * this.a + y * this.c + this.e;
2618         };
2619         /*\
2620          * Matrix.y
2621          [ method ]
2622          **
2623          * Return y coordinate for given point after transformation described by the matrix. See also @Matrix.x
2624          > Parameters
2625          - x (number)
2626          - y (number)
2627          = (number) y
2628         \*/
2629         matrixproto.y = function (x, y) {
2630             return x * this.b + y * this.d + this.f;
2631         };
2632         matrixproto.get = function (i) {
2633             return +this[Str.fromCharCode(97 + i)].toFixed(4);
2634         };
2635         matrixproto.toString = function () {
2636             return R.svg ?
2637                 "matrix(" + [this.get(0), this.get(1), this.get(2), this.get(3), this.get(4), this.get(5)].join() + ")" :
2638                 [this.get(0), this.get(2), this.get(1), this.get(3), 0, 0].join();
2639         };
2640         matrixproto.toFilter = function () {
2641             return "progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.Matrix(M11=" + this.get(0) +
2642                 ", M12=" + this.get(2) + ", M21=" + this.get(1) + ", M22=" + this.get(3) +
2643                 ", Dx=" + this.get(4) + ", Dy=" + this.get(5) + ", sizingmethod='auto expand')";
2644         };
2645         matrixproto.offset = function () {
2646             return [this.e.toFixed(4), this.f.toFixed(4)];
2647         };
2648         function norm(a) {
2649             return a[0] * a[0] + a[1] * a[1];
2650         }
2651         function normalize(a) {
2652             var mag = math.sqrt(norm(a));
2653             a[0] && (a[0] /= mag);
2654             a[1] && (a[1] /= mag);
2655         }
2656         /*\
2657          * Matrix.split
2658          [ method ]
2659          **
2660          * Splits matrix into primitive transformations
2661          = (object) in format:
2662          o dx (number) translation by x
2663          o dy (number) translation by y
2664          o scalex (number) scale by x
2665          o scaley (number) scale by y
2666          o shear (number) shear
2667          o rotate (number) rotation in deg
2668          o isSimple (boolean) could it be represented via simple transformations
2669         \*/
2670         matrixproto.split = function () {
2671             var out = {};
2672             // translation
2673             out.dx = this.e;
2674             out.dy = this.f;
2675 
2676             // scale and shear
2677             var row = [[this.a, this.c], [this.b, this.d]];
2678             out.scalex = math.sqrt(norm(row[0]));
2679             normalize(row[0]);
2680 
2681             out.shear = row[0][0] * row[1][0] + row[0][1] * row[1][1];
2682             row[1] = [row[1][0] - row[0][0] * out.shear, row[1][1] - row[0][1] * out.shear];
2683 
2684             out.scaley = math.sqrt(norm(row[1]));
2685             normalize(row[1]);
2686             out.shear /= out.scaley;
2687 
2688             // rotation
2689             var sin = -row[0][1],
2690                 cos = row[1][1];
2691             if (cos < 0) {
2692                 out.rotate = R.deg(math.acos(cos));
2693                 if (sin < 0) {
2694                     out.rotate = 360 - out.rotate;
2695                 }
2696             } else {
2697                 out.rotate = R.deg(math.asin(sin));
2698             }
2699 
2700             out.isSimple = !+out.shear.toFixed(9) && (out.scalex.toFixed(9) == out.scaley.toFixed(9) || !out.rotate);
2701             out.isSuperSimple = !+out.shear.toFixed(9) && out.scalex.toFixed(9) == out.scaley.toFixed(9) && !out.rotate;
2702             out.noRotation = !+out.shear.toFixed(9) && !out.rotate;
2703             return out;
2704         };
2705         /*\
2706          * Matrix.toTransformString
2707          [ method ]
2708          **
2709          * Return transform string that represents given matrix
2710          = (string) transform string
2711         \*/
2712         matrixproto.toTransformString = function (shorter) {
2713             var s = shorter || this[split]();
2714             if (s.isSimple) {
2715                 s.scalex = +s.scalex.toFixed(4);
2716                 s.scaley = +s.scaley.toFixed(4);
2717                 s.rotate = +s.rotate.toFixed(4);
2718                 return  (s.dx || s.dy ? "t" + [s.dx, s.dy] : E) +
2719                         (s.scalex != 1 || s.scaley != 1 ? "s" + [s.scalex, s.scaley, 0, 0] : E) +
2720                         (s.rotate ? "r" + [s.rotate, 0, 0] : E);
2721             } else {
2722                 return "m" + [this.get(0), this.get(1), this.get(2), this.get(3), this.get(4), this.get(5)];
2723             }
2724         };
2725     })(Matrix.prototype);

2768     addEvent = (function () {
2769         if (g.doc.addEventListener) {
2770             return function (obj, type, fn, element) {
2771                 var f = function (e) {
2772                     var pos = getEventPosition(e);
2773                     return fn.call(element, e, pos.x, pos.y);
2774                 };

3127      * Element.data
3128      [ method ]
3129      **
3130      * Adds or retrieves given value asociated with given key.
3131      **
3132      * See also @Element.removeData
3133      > Parameters
3134      - key (string) key to store data
3135      - value (any) #optional value to store
3136      = (object) @Element
3137      * or, if value is not specified:
3138      = (any) value
3139      * or, if key and value are not specified:
3140      = (object) Key/value pairs for all the data associated with the element.
3141      > Usage
3142      | for (var i = 0, i < 5, i++) {
3143      |     paper.circle(10 + 15 * i, 10, 10)
3144      |          .attr({fill: "#000"})

3146      |          .click(function () {
3147      |             alert(this.data("i"));
3148      |          });
3149      | }
3150     \*/
3151     elproto.data = function (key, value) {
3152         var data = eldata[this.id] = eldata[this.id] || {};
3153         if (arguments.length == 0) {
3154             return data;
3155         }
3156         if (arguments.length == 1) {
3157             if (R.is(key, "object")) {
3158                 for (var i in key) if (key[has](i)) {
3159                     this.data(i, key[i]);
3160                 }
3161                 return this;
3162             }
3163             eve("raphael.data.get." + this.id, this, data[key], key);
3164             return data[key];
3165         }
3166         data[key] = value;
3167         eve("raphael.data.set." + this.id, this, value, key);
3168         return this;
3169     };

3227     /*\
3228      * Element.drag
3229      [ method ]
3230      **
3231      * Adds event handlers for drag of the element.
3232      > Parameters
3233      - onmove (function) handler for moving
3234      - onstart (function) handler for drag start
3235      - onend (function) handler for drag end
3236      - mcontext (object) #optional context for moving handler
3237      - scontext (object) #optional context for drag start handler
3238      - econtext (object) #optional context for drag end handler
3239      * Additionaly following `drag` events will be triggered: `drag.start.<id>` on start,
3240      * `drag.end.<id>` on end and `drag.move.<id>` on every move. When element will be dragged over another element
3241      * `drag.over.<id>` will be fired as well.
3242      *
3243      * Start event and start handler will be called in specified context or in context of the element with following parameters:
3244      o x (number) x position of the mouse
3245      o y (number) y position of the mouse
3246      o event (object) DOM event object
3247      * Move event and move handler will be called in specified context or in context of the element with following parameters:
3248      o dx (number) shift by x from the start point
3249      o dy (number) shift by y from the start point
3250      o x (number) x position of the mouse
3251      o y (number) y position of the mouse
3252      o event (object) DOM event object
3253      * End event and end handler will be called in specified context or in context of the element with following parameters:
3254      o event (object) DOM event object
3255      = (object) @Element
3256     \*/
3257     elproto.drag = function (onmove, onstart, onend, move_scope, start_scope, end_scope) {
3258         function start(e) {
3259             (e.originalEvent || e).preventDefault();
3260             var x = e.clientX,
3261                 y = e.clientY,
3262                 scrollY = g.doc.documentElement.scrollTop || g.doc.body.scrollTop,
3263                 scrollX = g.doc.documentElement.scrollLeft || g.doc.body.scrollLeft;
3264             this._drag.id = e.identifier;
3265             if (supportsTouch && e.touches) {
3266                 var i = e.touches.length, touch;
3267                 while (i--) {
3268                     touch = e.touches[i];
3269                     this._drag.id = touch.identifier;
3270                     if (touch.identifier == this._drag.id) {
3271                         x = touch.clientX;
3272                         y = touch.clientY;
3273                         break;
3274                     }
3275                 }
3276             }
3277             this._drag.x = x + scrollX;
3278             this._drag.y = y + scrollY;
3279             !drag.length && R.mousemove(dragMove).mouseup(dragUp);
3280             drag.push({el: this, move_scope: move_scope, start_scope: start_scope, end_scope: end_scope});
3281             onstart && eve.on("raphael.drag.start." + this.id, onstart);
3282             onmove && eve.on("raphael.drag.move." + this.id, onmove);
3283             onend && eve.on("raphael.drag.end." + this.id, onend);
3284             eve("raphael.drag.start." + this.id, start_scope || move_scope || this, e.clientX + scrollX, e.clientY + scrollY, e);
3285         }
3286         this._drag = {};
3287         draggable.push({el: this, start: start});
3288         this.mousedown(start);
3289         return this;
3290     };

3387     /*\
3388      * Paper.path
3389      [ method ]
3390      **
3391      * Creates a path element by given path data string.
3392      > Parameters
3393      - pathString (string) #optional path string in SVG format.
3394      * Path string consists of one-letter commands, followed by comma seprarated arguments in numercal form. Example:
3395      | "M10,20L30,40"
3396      * Here we can see two commands: “M”, with arguments `(10, 20)` and “L” with arguments `(30, 40)`. Upper case letter mean command is absolute, lower case—relative.
3397      *
3398      # <p>Here is short list of commands available, for more details see <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/paths.html#PathData" title="Details of a path's data attribute's format are described in the SVG specification.">SVG path string format</a>.</p>
3399      # <table><thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>Name</th><th>Parameters</th></tr></thead><tbody>
3400      # <tr><td>M</td><td>moveto</td><td>(x y)+</td></tr>
3401      # <tr><td>Z</td><td>closepath</td><td>(none)</td></tr>
3402      # <tr><td>L</td><td>lineto</td><td>(x y)+</td></tr>
3403      # <tr><td>H</td><td>horizontal lineto</td><td>x+</td></tr>
3404      # <tr><td>V</td><td>vertical lineto</td><td>y+</td></tr>
3405      # <tr><td>C</td><td>curveto</td><td>(x1 y1 x2 y2 x y)+</td></tr>
3406      # <tr><td>S</td><td>smooth curveto</td><td>(x2 y2 x y)+</td></tr>
3407      # <tr><td>Q</td><td>quadratic Bézier curveto</td><td>(x1 y1 x y)+</td></tr>
3408      # <tr><td>T</td><td>smooth quadratic Bézier curveto</td><td>(x y)+</td></tr>
3409      # <tr><td>A</td><td>elliptical arc</td><td>(rx ry x-axis-rotation large-arc-flag sweep-flag x y)+</td></tr>
3410      # <tr><td>R</td><td><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catmull–Rom_spline#Catmull.E2.80.93Rom_spline">Catmull-Rom curveto</a>*</td><td>x1 y1 (x y)+</td></tr></tbody></table>
3411      * * “Catmull-Rom curveto” is a not standard SVG command and added in 2.0 to make life easier.
3412      * Note: there is a special case when path consist of just three commands: “M10,10R…z”. In this case path will smoothly connects to its beginning.
3413      > Usage
3414      | var c = paper.path("M10 10L90 90");
3415      | // draw a diagonal line:
3416      | // move to 10,10, line to 90,90

3423         return out;

3878     getLengthFactory = function (istotal, subpath) {
3879         return function (path, length, onlystart) {
3880             path = path2curve(path);
3881             var x, y, p, l, sp = "", subpaths = {}, point,
3882                 len = 0;
3883             for (var i = 0, ii = path.length; i < ii; i++) {
3884                 p = path[i];
3885                 if (p[0] == "M") {
3886                     x = +p[1];
3887                     y = +p[2];
3888                 } else {
3889                     l = getPointAtSegmentLength(x, y, p[1], p[2], p[3], p[4], p[5], p[6]);
3890                     if (len + l > length) {
3891                         if (subpath && !subpaths.start) {
3892                             point = getPointAtSegmentLength(x, y, p[1], p[2], p[3], p[4], p[5], p[6], length - len);
3893                             sp += ["C" + point.start.x, point.start.y, point.m.x, point.m.y, point.x, point.y];
3894                             if (onlystart) {return sp;}
3895                             subpaths.start = sp;
3896                             sp = ["M" + point.x, point.y + "C" + point.n.x, point.n.y, point.end.x, point.end.y, p[5], p[6]].join();
3897                             len += l;
3898                             x = +p[5];
3899                             y = +p[6];
3900                             continue;
3901                         }
3902                         if (!istotal && !subpath) {
3903                             point = getPointAtSegmentLength(x, y, p[1], p[2], p[3], p[4], p[5], p[6], length - len);
3904                             return {x: point.x, y: point.y, alpha: point.alpha};
3905                         }
3906                     }
3907                     len += l;
3908                     x = +p[5];
3909                     y = +p[6];
3910                 }
3911                 sp += p.shift() + p;
3912             }
3913             subpaths.end = sp;
3914             point = istotal ? len : subpath ? subpaths : R.findDotsAtSegment(x, y, p[0], p[1], p[2], p[3], p[4], p[5], 1);
3915             point.alpha && (point = {x: point.x, y: point.y, alpha: point.alpha});
3916             return point;
3917         };
