4053     \*/
4054     elproto.getSubpath = function (from, to) {
4055         var path = this.getPath();
4056         if (!path) {
4057             return;
4058         }
4059 
4060         return R.getSubpath(path, from, to);
4061     };
4062     /*\
4063      * Raphael.easing_formulas
4064      [ property ]
4065      **
4066      * Object that contains easing formulas for animation. You could extend it with your own. By default it has following list of easing:
4067      # <ul>
4068      #     <li>“linear”</li>
4069      #     <li>“<” or “easeIn” or “ease-in”</li>
4070      #     <li>“>” or “easeOut” or “ease-out”</li>
4071      #     <li>“<>” or “easeInOut” or “ease-in-out”</li>
4072      #     <li>“backIn” or “back-in”</li>
4073      #     <li>“backOut” or “back-out”</li>
4074      #     <li>“elastic”</li>
4075      #     <li>“bounce”</li>
4076      # </ul>
4077      # <p>See also <a href="http://raphaeljs.com/easing.html">Easing demo</a>.</p>
4078     \*/
4079     var ef = R.easing_formulas = {
4080         linear: function (n) {
4081             return n;
4082         },
4083         "<": function (n) {
4084             return pow(n, 1.7);
4085         },
4086         ">": function (n) {
4087             return pow(n, .48);
4088         },
4089         "<>": function (n) {
4090             var q = .48 - n / 1.04,
4091                 Q = math.sqrt(.1734 + q * q),
4092                 x = Q - q,
4093                 X = pow(abs(x), 1 / 3) * (x < 0 ? -1 : 1),
4094                 y = -Q - q,
4095                 Y = pow(abs(y), 1 / 3) * (y < 0 ? -1 : 1),
4096                 t = X + Y + .5;
4097             return (1 - t) * 3 * t * t + t * t * t;
4098         },
4099         backIn: function (n) {
4100             var s = 1.70158;
4101             return n * n * ((s + 1) * n - s);
4102         },
4103         backOut: function (n) {
4104             n = n - 1;
4105             var s = 1.70158;
4106             return n * n * ((s + 1) * n + s) + 1;
4107         },
4108         elastic: function (n) {
4109             if (n == !!n) {
4110                 return n;
4111             }
4112             return pow(2, -10 * n) * math.sin((n - .075) * (2 * PI) / .3) + 1;
4113         },
4114         bounce: function (n) {
4115             var s = 7.5625,
4116                 p = 2.75,
4117                 l;
4118             if (n < (1 / p)) {
4119                 l = s * n * n;
4120             } else {
4121                 if (n < (2 / p)) {
4122                     n -= (1.5 / p);
4123                     l = s * n * n + .75;
4124                 } else {
4125                     if (n < (2.5 / p)) {
4126                         n -= (2.25 / p);
4127                         l = s * n * n + .9375;
4128                     } else {
4129                         n -= (2.625 / p);
4130                         l = s * n * n + .984375;
4131                     }
4132                 }
4133             }
4134             return l;
4135         }
4136     };
4137     ef.easeIn = ef["ease-in"] = ef["<"];
4138     ef.easeOut = ef["ease-out"] = ef[">"];
4139     ef.easeInOut = ef["ease-in-out"] = ef["<>"];
4140     ef["back-in"] = ef.backIn;
4141     ef["back-out"] = ef.backOut;

4143     var animationElements = [],
4144         requestAnimFrame = window.requestAnimationFrame       ||
4145                            window.webkitRequestAnimationFrame ||
4146                            window.mozRequestAnimationFrame    ||
4147                            window.oRequestAnimationFrame      ||
4148                            window.msRequestAnimationFrame     ||
4149                            function (callback) {
4150                                setTimeout(callback, 16);
4151                            },
4152         animation = function () {
4153             var Now = +new Date,
4154                 l = 0;
4155             for (; l < animationElements.length; l++) {
4156                 var e = animationElements[l];
4157                 if (e.el.removed || e.paused) {
4158                     continue;
4159                 }
4160                 var time = Now - e.start,
4161                     ms = e.ms,
4162                     easing = e.easing,
4163                     from = e.from,
4164                     diff = e.diff,
4165                     to = e.to,
4166                     t = e.t,
4167                     that = e.el,
4168                     set = {},
4169                     now,
4170                     init = {},
4171                     key;
4172                 if (e.initstatus) {
4173                     time = (e.initstatus * e.anim.top - e.prev) / (e.percent - e.prev) * ms;
4174                     e.status = e.initstatus;
4175                     delete e.initstatus;
4176                     e.stop && animationElements.splice(l--, 1);
4177                 } else {
4178                     e.status = (e.prev + (e.percent - e.prev) * (time / ms)) / e.anim.top;
4179                 }
4180                 if (time < 0) {
4181                     continue;
4182                 }
4183                 if (time < ms) {
4184                     var pos = easing(time / ms);
4185                     for (var attr in from) if (from[has](attr)) {
4186                         switch (availableAnimAttrs[attr]) {
4187                             case nu:
4188                                 now = +from[attr] + pos * ms * diff[attr];
4189                                 break;
4190                             case "colour":
4191                                 now = "rgb(" + [
4192                                     upto255(round(from[attr].r + pos * ms * diff[attr].r)),
4193                                     upto255(round(from[attr].g + pos * ms * diff[attr].g)),
4194                                     upto255(round(from[attr].b + pos * ms * diff[attr].b))
4195                                 ].join(",") + ")";
4196                                 break;
4197                             case "path":
4198                                 now = [];
4199                                 for (var i = 0, ii = from[attr].length; i < ii; i++) {
4200                                     now[i] = [from[attr][i][0]];
4201                                     for (var j = 1, jj = from[attr][i].length; j < jj; j++) {
4202                                         now[i][j] = +from[attr][i][j] + pos * ms * diff[attr][i][j];
4203                                     }
4204                                     now[i] = now[i].join(S);
4205                                 }
4206                                 now = now.join(S);
4207                                 break;
4208                             case "transform":
4209                                 if (diff[attr].real) {
4210                                     now = [];
4211                                     for (i = 0, ii = from[attr].length; i < ii; i++) {
4212                                         now[i] = [from[attr][i][0]];
4213                                         for (j = 1, jj = from[attr][i].length; j < jj; j++) {
4214                                             now[i][j] = from[attr][i][j] + pos * ms * diff[attr][i][j];
4215                                         }
4216                                     }
4217                                 } else {
4218                                     var get = function (i) {
4219                                         return +from[attr][i] + pos * ms * diff[attr][i];
4220                                     };
4221                                     // now = [["r", get(2), 0, 0], ["t", get(3), get(4)], ["s", get(0), get(1), 0, 0]];
4222                                     now = [["m", get(0), get(1), get(2), get(3), get(4), get(5)]];
4223                                 }
4224                                 break;
4225                             case "csv":
4226                                 if (attr == "clip-rect") {
4227                                     now = [];
4228                                     i = 4;
4229                                     while (i--) {
4230                                         now[i] = +from[attr][i] + pos * ms * diff[attr][i];
4231                                     }
4232                                 }
4233                                 break;
4234                             default:
4235                                 var from2 = [][concat](from[attr]);
4236                                 now = [];
4237                                 i = that.paper.customAttributes[attr].length;
4238                                 while (i--) {
4239                                     now[i] = +from2[i] + pos * ms * diff[attr][i];
4240                                 }
4241                                 break;
4242                         }
4243                         set[attr] = now;
4244                     }
4245                     that.attr(set);
4246                     (function (id, that, anim) {
4247                         setTimeout(function () {
4248                             eve("raphael.anim.frame." + id, that, anim);
4249                         });
4250                     })(that.id, that, e.anim);
4251                 } else {
4252                     (function(f, el, a) {
4253                         setTimeout(function() {
4254                             eve("raphael.anim.frame." + el.id, el, a);
4255                             eve("raphael.anim.finish." + el.id, el, a);
4256                             R.is(f, "function") && f.call(el);
4257                         });
4258                     })(e.callback, that, e.anim);
4259                     that.attr(to);
4260                     animationElements.splice(l--, 1);
4261                     if (e.repeat > 1 && !e.next) {
4262                         for (key in to) if (to[has](key)) {
4263                             init[key] = e.totalOrigin[key];
4264                         }
4265                         e.el.attr(init);
4266                         runAnimation(e.anim, e.el, e.anim.percents[0], null, e.totalOrigin, e.repeat - 1);
4267                     }
4268                     if (e.next && !e.stop) {
4269                         runAnimation(e.anim, e.el, e.next, null, e.totalOrigin, e.repeat);
4270                     }
4271                 }
4272             }
4273             R.svg && that && that.paper && that.paper.safari();
4274             animationElements.length && requestAnimFrame(animation);
4275         },
4276         upto255 = function (color) {
4277             return color > 255 ? 255 : color < 0 ? 0 : color;

4279     /*\
4280      * Element.animateWith
4281      [ method ]
4282      **
4283      * Acts similar to @Element.animate, but ensure that given animation runs in sync with another given element.
4284      **
4285      > Parameters
4286      **
4287      - el (object) element to sync with
4288      - anim (object) animation to sync with
4289      - params (object) #optional final attributes for the element, see also @Element.attr
4290      - ms (number) #optional number of milliseconds for animation to run
4291      - easing (string) #optional easing type. Accept on of @Raphael.easing_formulas or CSS format: `cubic‐bezier(XX, XX, XX, XX)`
4292      - callback (function) #optional callback function. Will be called at the end of animation.
4293      * or
4294      - element (object) element to sync with
4295      - anim (object) animation to sync with
4296      - animation (object) #optional animation object, see @Raphael.animation
4297      **
4298      = (object) original element
4299     \*/
4300     elproto.animateWith = function (el, anim, params, ms, easing, callback) {
4301         var element = this;
4302         if (element.removed) {
4303             callback && callback.call(element);
4304             return element;
4305         }
4306         var a = params instanceof Animation ? params : R.animation(params, ms, easing, callback),
4307             x, y;
4308         runAnimation(a, element, a.percents[0], null, element.attr());
4309         for (var i = 0, ii = animationElements.length; i < ii; i++) {
4310             if (animationElements[i].anim == anim && animationElements[i].el == el) {
4311                 animationElements[ii - 1].start = animationElements[i].start;
4312                 break;
4313             }
4314         }
4315         return element;
4316         //
4317         //
4318         // var a = params ? R.animation(params, ms, easing, callback) : anim,
4319         //     status = element.status(anim);
4320         // return this.animate(a).status(a, status * anim.ms / a.ms);
4321     };
4322     function CubicBezierAtTime(t, p1x, p1y, p2x, p2y, duration) {
4323         var cx = 3 * p1x,
4324             bx = 3 * (p2x - p1x) - cx,
4325             ax = 1 - cx - bx,
4326             cy = 3 * p1y,
4327             by = 3 * (p2y - p1y) - cy,
4328             ay = 1 - cy - by;
4329         function sampleCurveX(t) {
4330             return ((ax * t + bx) * t + cx) * t;
4331         }
4332         function solve(x, epsilon) {
4333             var t = solveCurveX(x, epsilon);
4334             return ((ay * t + by) * t + cy) * t;
4335         }
4336         function solveCurveX(x, epsilon) {
4337             var t0, t1, t2, x2, d2, i;
4338             for(t2 = x, i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
4339                 x2 = sampleCurveX(t2) - x;
4340                 if (abs(x2) < epsilon) {
4341                     return t2;
4342                 }
4343                 d2 = (3 * ax * t2 + 2 * bx) * t2 + cx;
4344                 if (abs(d2) < 1e-6) {
4345                     break;
4346                 }
4347                 t2 = t2 - x2 / d2;
4348             }
4349             t0 = 0;
4350             t1 = 1;
4351             t2 = x;
4352             if (t2 < t0) {
4353                 return t0;
4354             }
4355             if (t2 > t1) {
4356                 return t1;
4357             }
4358             while (t0 < t1) {
4359                 x2 = sampleCurveX(t2);
4360                 if (abs(x2 - x) < epsilon) {
4361                     return t2;
4362                 }
4363                 if (x > x2) {
4364                     t0 = t2;
4365                 } else {
4366                     t1 = t2;
4367                 }
4368                 t2 = (t1 - t0) / 2 + t0;
4369             }
4370             return t2;
4371         }
4372         return solve(t, 1 / (200 * duration));
4373     }
4374     elproto.onAnimation = function (f) {
4375         f ? eve.on("raphael.anim.frame." + this.id, f) : eve.unbind("raphael.anim.frame." + this.id);
4376         return this;
4377     };
4378     function Animation(anim, ms) {
4379         var percents = [],
4380             newAnim = {};
4381         this.ms = ms;
4382         this.times = 1;
4383         if (anim) {
4384             for (var attr in anim) if (anim[has](attr)) {
4385                 newAnim[toFloat(attr)] = anim[attr];
4386                 percents.push(toFloat(attr));
4387             }
4388             percents.sort(sortByNumber);
4389         }
4390         this.anim = newAnim;
4391         this.top = percents[percents.length - 1];
4392         this.percents = percents;
4393     }
4394     /*\
4395      * Animation.delay
4396      [ method ]
4397      **
4398      * Creates a copy of existing animation object with given delay.
4399      **
4400      > Parameters
4401      **
4402      - delay (number) number of ms to pass between animation start and actual animation
4403      **
4404      = (object) new altered Animation object
4405      | var anim = Raphael.animation({cx: 10, cy: 20}, 2e3);
4406      | circle1.animate(anim); // run the given animation immediately
4407      | circle2.animate(anim.delay(500)); // run the given animation after 500 ms
4408     \*/
4409     Animation.prototype.delay = function (delay) {
4410         var a = new Animation(this.anim, this.ms);
4411         a.times = this.times;
4412         a.del = +delay || 0;
4413         return a;
4414     };
4415     /*\
4416      * Animation.repeat
4417      [ method ]
4418      **
4419      * Creates a copy of existing animation object with given repetition.
4420      **
4421      > Parameters
4422      **
4423      - repeat (number) number iterations of animation. For infinite animation pass `Infinity`
4424      **
4425      = (object) new altered Animation object
4426     \*/
4427     Animation.prototype.repeat = function (times) {
4428         var a = new Animation(this.anim, this.ms);
4429         a.del = this.del;
4430         a.times = math.floor(mmax(times, 0)) || 1;
4431         return a;
4432     };
4433     function runAnimation(anim, element, percent, status, totalOrigin, times) {
4434         percent = toFloat(percent);
4435         var params,
4436             isInAnim,
4437             isInAnimSet,
4438             percents = [],
4439             next,
4440             prev,
4441             timestamp,
4442             ms = anim.ms,
4443             from = {},
4444             to = {},
4445             diff = {};
4446         if (status) {
4447             for (i = 0, ii = animationElements.length; i < ii; i++) {
4448                 var e = animationElements[i];
4449                 if (e.el.id == element.id && e.anim == anim) {
4450                     if (e.percent != percent) {
4451                         animationElements.splice(i, 1);
4452                         isInAnimSet = 1;
4453                     } else {
4454                         isInAnim = e;
4455                     }
4456                     element.attr(e.totalOrigin);
4457                     break;
4458                 }
4459             }
4460         } else {
4461             status = +to; // NaN
4462         }
4463         for (var i = 0, ii = anim.percents.length; i < ii; i++) {
4464             if (anim.percents[i] == percent || anim.percents[i] > status * anim.top) {
4465                 percent = anim.percents[i];
4466                 prev = anim.percents[i - 1] || 0;
4467                 ms = ms / anim.top * (percent - prev);
4468                 next = anim.percents[i + 1];
4469                 params = anim.anim[percent];
4470                 break;
4471             } else if (status) {
4472                 element.attr(anim.anim[anim.percents[i]]);
4473             }
4474         }
4475         if (!params) {
4476             return;
4477         }
4478         if (!isInAnim) {
4479             for (var attr in params) if (params[has](attr)) {
4480                 if (availableAnimAttrs[has](attr) || element.paper.customAttributes[has](attr)) {
4481                     from[attr] = element.attr(attr);
4482                     (from[attr] == null) && (from[attr] = availableAttrs[attr]);
4483                     to[attr] = params[attr];
4484                     switch (availableAnimAttrs[attr]) {
4485                         case nu:
4486                             diff[attr] = (to[attr] - from[attr]) / ms;
4487                             break;
4488                         case "colour":
4489                             from[attr] = R.getRGB(from[attr]);
4490                             var toColour = R.getRGB(to[attr]);
4491                             diff[attr] = {
4492                                 r: (toColour.r - from[attr].r) / ms,
4493                                 g: (toColour.g - from[attr].g) / ms,
4494                                 b: (toColour.b - from[attr].b) / ms
4495                             };
4496                             break;
4497                         case "path":
4498                             var pathes = path2curve(from[attr], to[attr]),
4499                                 toPath = pathes[1];
4500                             from[attr] = pathes[0];
4501                             diff[attr] = [];
4502                             for (i = 0, ii = from[attr].length; i < ii; i++) {
4503                                 diff[attr][i] = [0];
4504                                 for (var j = 1, jj = from[attr][i].length; j < jj; j++) {
4505                                     diff[attr][i][j] = (toPath[i][j] - from[attr][i][j]) / ms;
4506                                 }
4507                             }
4508                             break;
4509                         case "transform":
4510                             var _ = element._,
4511                                 eq = equaliseTransform(_[attr], to[attr]);
4512                             if (eq) {
4513                                 from[attr] = eq.from;
4514                                 to[attr] = eq.to;
4515                                 diff[attr] = [];
4516                                 diff[attr].real = true;
4517                                 for (i = 0, ii = from[attr].length; i < ii; i++) {
4518                                     diff[attr][i] = [from[attr][i][0]];
4519                                     for (j = 1, jj = from[attr][i].length; j < jj; j++) {
4520                                         diff[attr][i][j] = (to[attr][i][j] - from[attr][i][j]) / ms;
4521                                     }
4522                                 }
4523                             } else {
4524                                 var m = (element.matrix || new Matrix),
4525                                     to2 = {
4526                                         _: {transform: _.transform},
4527                                         getBBox: function () {
4528                                             return element.getBBox(1);
4529                                         }
4530                                     };
4531                                 from[attr] = [
4532                                     m.a,
4533                                     m.b,
4534                                     m.c,
4535                                     m.d,
4536                                     m.e,
4537                                     m.f
4538                                 ];
4539                                 extractTransform(to2, to[attr]);
4540                                 to[attr] = to2._.transform;
4541                                 diff[attr] = [
4542                                     (to2.matrix.a - m.a) / ms,
4543                                     (to2.matrix.b - m.b) / ms,
4544                                     (to2.matrix.c - m.c) / ms,
4545                                     (to2.matrix.d - m.d) / ms,
4546                                     (to2.matrix.e - m.e) / ms,
4547                                     (to2.matrix.f - m.f) / ms
4548                                 ];
4549                                 // from[attr] = [_.sx, _.sy, _.deg, _.dx, _.dy];
4550                                 // var to2 = {_:{}, getBBox: function () { return element.getBBox(); }};
4551                                 // extractTransform(to2, to[attr]);
4552                                 // diff[attr] = [
4553                                 //     (to2._.sx - _.sx) / ms,
4554                                 //     (to2._.sy - _.sy) / ms,
4555                                 //     (to2._.deg - _.deg) / ms,
4556                                 //     (to2._.dx - _.dx) / ms,
4557                                 //     (to2._.dy - _.dy) / ms
4558                                 // ];
4559                             }
4560                             break;
4561                         case "csv":
4562                             var values = Str(params[attr])[split](separator),
4563                                 from2 = Str(from[attr])[split](separator);
4564                             if (attr == "clip-rect") {
4565                                 from[attr] = from2;
4566                                 diff[attr] = [];
4567                                 i = from2.length;
4568                                 while (i--) {
4569                                     diff[attr][i] = (values[i] - from[attr][i]) / ms;
4570                                 }
4571                             }
4572                             to[attr] = values;
4573                             break;
4574                         default:
4575                             values = [][concat](params[attr]);
4576                             from2 = [][concat](from[attr]);
4577                             diff[attr] = [];
4578                             i = element.paper.customAttributes[attr].length;
4579                             while (i--) {
4580                                 diff[attr][i] = ((values[i] || 0) - (from2[i] || 0)) / ms;
4581                             }
4582                             break;
4583                     }
4584                 }
4585             }
4586             var easing = params.easing,
4587                 easyeasy = R.easing_formulas[easing];
4588             if (!easyeasy) {
4589                 easyeasy = Str(easing).match(bezierrg);
4590                 if (easyeasy && easyeasy.length == 5) {
4591                     var curve = easyeasy;
4592                     easyeasy = function (t) {
4593                         return CubicBezierAtTime(t, +curve[1], +curve[2], +curve[3], +curve[4], ms);
4594                     };
4595                 } else {
4596                     easyeasy = pipe;
4597                 }
4598             }
4599             timestamp = params.start || anim.start || +new Date;
4600             e = {
4601                 anim: anim,
4602                 percent: percent,
4603                 timestamp: timestamp,
4604                 start: timestamp + (anim.del || 0),
4605                 status: 0,
4606                 initstatus: status || 0,
4607                 stop: false,
4608                 ms: ms,
4609                 easing: easyeasy,
4610                 from: from,
4611                 diff: diff,
4612                 to: to,
4613                 el: element,
4614                 callback: params.callback,
4615                 prev: prev,
4616                 next: next,
4617                 repeat: times || anim.times,
4618                 origin: element.attr(),
4619                 totalOrigin: totalOrigin
4620             };
4621             animationElements.push(e);
4622             if (status && !isInAnim && !isInAnimSet) {
4623                 e.stop = true;
4624                 e.start = new Date - ms * status;
4625                 if (animationElements.length == 1) {
4626                     return animation();
4627                 }
4628             }
4629             if (isInAnimSet) {
4630                 e.start = new Date - e.ms * status;
4631             }
4632             animationElements.length == 1 && requestAnimFrame(animation);
4633         } else {
4634             isInAnim.initstatus = status;
4635             isInAnim.start = new Date - isInAnim.ms * status;
4636         }
4637         eve("raphael.anim.start." + element.id, element, anim);
4638     }
4639     /*\
4640      * Raphael.animation
4641      [ method ]
4642      **
4643      * Creates an animation object that can be passed to the @Element.animate or @Element.animateWith methods.
4644      * See also @Animation.delay and @Animation.repeat methods.
4645      **
4646      > Parameters
4647      **
4648      - params (object) final attributes for the element, see also @Element.attr
4649      - ms (number) number of milliseconds for animation to run
4650      - easing (string) #optional easing type. Accept one of @Raphael.easing_formulas or CSS format: `cubic‐bezier(XX, XX, XX, XX)`
4651      - callback (function) #optional callback function. Will be called at the end of animation.
4652      **
4653      = (object) @Animation
4654     \*/
4655     R.animation = function (params, ms, easing, callback) {
4656         if (params instanceof Animation) {
4657             return params;
4658         }
4659         if (R.is(easing, "function") || !easing) {
4660             callback = callback || easing || null;
4661             easing = null;
4662         }
4663         params = Object(params);
4664         ms = +ms || 0;
4665         var p = {},
4666             json,
4667             attr;
4668         for (attr in params) if (params[has](attr) && toFloat(attr) != attr && toFloat(attr) + "%" != attr) {
4669             json = true;
4670             p[attr] = params[attr];
4671         }
4672         if (!json) {
4673             // if percent-like syntax is used and end-of-all animation callback used
4674             if(callback){
4675                 // find the last one
4676                 var lastKey = 0;
4677                 for(var i in params){
4678                     var percent = toInt(i);
4679                     if(params[has](i) && percent > lastKey){
4680                         lastKey = percent;
4681                     }
4682                 }
4683                 lastKey += '%';
4684                 // if already defined callback in the last keyframe, skip
4685                 !params[lastKey].callback && (params[lastKey].callback = callback);
4686             }
4687           return new Animation(params, ms);
4688         } else {
4689             easing && (p.easing = easing);
4690             callback && (p.callback = callback);
4691             return new Animation({100: p}, ms);
4692         }
4693     };
4694     /*\
4695      * Element.animate
4696      [ method ]
4697      **
4698      * Creates and starts animation for given element.
4699      **
4700      > Parameters
4701      **
4702      - params (object) final attributes for the element, see also @Element.attr
4703      - ms (number) number of milliseconds for animation to run
4704      - easing (string) #optional easing type. Accept one of @Raphael.easing_formulas or CSS format: `cubic‐bezier(XX, XX, XX, XX)`
4705      - callback (function) #optional callback function. Will be called at the end of animation.
4706      * or
4707      - animation (object) animation object, see @Raphael.animation
4708      **
4709      = (object) original element
4710     \*/
4711     elproto.animate = function (params, ms, easing, callback) {
4712         var element = this;
4713         if (element.removed) {
4714             callback && callback.call(element);
4715             return element;
4716         }
4717         var anim = params instanceof Animation ? params : R.animation(params, ms, easing, callback);
4718         runAnimation(anim, element, anim.percents[0], null, element.attr());
4719         return element;
4720     };
4721     /*\
4722      * Element.setTime
4723      [ method ]
4724      **
4725      * Sets the status of animation of the element in milliseconds. Similar to @Element.status method.
4726      **
4727      > Parameters
4728      **
4729      - anim (object) animation object
4730      - value (number) number of milliseconds from the beginning of the animation
4731      **
4732      = (object) original element if `value` is specified
4733      * Note, that during animation following events are triggered:
4734      *
4735      * On each animation frame event `anim.frame.<id>`, on start `anim.start.<id>` and on end `anim.finish.<id>`.
4736     \*/
4737     elproto.setTime = function (anim, value) {
4738         if (anim && value != null) {
4739             this.status(anim, mmin(value, anim.ms) / anim.ms);
4740         }
4741         return this;
4742     };
4743     /*\
4744      * Element.status
4745      [ method ]
4746      **
4747      * Gets or sets the status of animation of the element.
4748      **
4749      > Parameters
4750      **
4751      - anim (object) #optional animation object
4752      - value (number) #optional 0 – 1. If specified, method works like a setter and sets the status of a given animation to the value. This will cause animation to jump to the given position.
4753      **
4754      = (number) status
4755      * or
4756      = (array) status if `anim` is not specified. Array of objects in format:
4757      o {
4758      o     anim: (object) animation object
4759      o     status: (number) status
4760      o }
4761      * or
4762      = (object) original element if `value` is specified
4763     \*/
4764     elproto.status = function (anim, value) {
4765         var out = [],
4766             i = 0,
4767             len,
4768             e;
4769         if (value != null) {
4770             runAnimation(anim, this, -1, mmin(value, 1));
4771             return this;
4772         } else {
4773             len = animationElements.length;
4774             for (; i < len; i++) {
4775                 e = animationElements[i];
4776                 if (e.el.id == this.id && (!anim || e.anim == anim)) {
4777                     if (anim) {
4778                         return e.status;
4779                     }
4780                     out.push({
4781                         anim: e.anim,
4782                         status: e.status
4783                     });
4784                 }
4785             }
4786             if (anim) {
4787                 return 0;
4788             }
4789             return out;
4790         }
4791     };

4801      **
4802      = (object) original element

4804     elproto.pause = function (anim) {

4806             if (eve("raphael.anim.pause." + this.id, this, animationElements[i].anim) !== false) {

4824     elproto.resume = function (anim) {

4826             var e = animationElements[i];

4828                 delete e.paused;

4830             }

4858     }

4865     // Set
4866     var Set = function (items) {
4867         this.items = [];
4868         this.length = 0;
4869         this.type = "set";
4870         if (items) {
4871             for (var i = 0, ii = items.length; i < ii; i++) {
4872                 if (items[i] && (items[i].constructor == elproto.constructor || items[i].constructor == Set)) {
4873                     this[this.items.length] = this.items[this.items.length] = items[i];
4874                     this.length++;
4875                 }
4876             }
4877         }
4878     },
4879     setproto = Set.prototype;
4880     /*\
4881      * Set.push
4882      [ method ]
4883      **
4884      * Adds each argument to the current set.
4885      = (object) original element
4886     \*/
4887     setproto.push = function () {
4888         var item,
4889             len;
4890         for (var i = 0, ii = arguments.length; i < ii; i++) {
4891             item = arguments[i];
4892             if (item && (item.constructor == elproto.constructor || item.constructor == Set)) {
4893                 len = this.items.length;
4894                 this[len] = this.items[len] = item;
4895                 this.length++;
4896             }
4897         }
4898         return this;
4899     };
4900     /*\
4901      * Set.pop
4902      [ method ]
4903      **
4904      * Removes last element and returns it.
4905      = (object) element
4906     \*/
4907     setproto.pop = function () {
4908         this.length && delete this[this.length--];
4909         return this.items.pop();
4910     };
4911     /*\
4912      * Set.forEach
4913      [ method ]
4914      **
4915      * Executes given function for each element in the set.
4916      *
4917      * If function returns `false` it will stop loop running.
4918      **
4919      > Parameters
4920      **
4921      - callback (function) function to run
4922      - thisArg (object) context object for the callback
4923      = (object) Set object
4924     \*/
4925     setproto.forEach = function (callback, thisArg) {
4926         for (var i = 0, ii = this.items.length; i < ii; i++) {
4927             if (callback.call(thisArg, this.items[i], i) === false) {
4928                 return this;
4929             }
4930         }
4931         return this;
4932     };
4933     for (var method in elproto) if (elproto[has](method)) {
4934         setproto[method] = (function (methodname) {
4935             return function () {
4936                 var arg = arguments;
4937                 return this.forEach(function (el) {
4938                     el[methodname][apply](el, arg);
4939                 });
4940             };
4941         })(method);
4942     }
4943     setproto.attr = function (name, value) {
4944         if (name && R.is(name, array) && R.is(name[0], "object")) {
4945             for (var j = 0, jj = name.length; j < jj; j++) {
4946                 this.items[j].attr(name[j]);
4947             }
4948         } else {
4949             for (var i = 0, ii = this.items.length; i < ii; i++) {
4950                 this.items[i].attr(name, value);
4951             }
4952         }
4953         return this;
4954     };
4955     /*\
4956      * Set.clear
4957      [ method ]
4958      **
4959      * Removes all elements from the set
4960     \*/
4961     setproto.clear = function () {
4962         while (this.length) {
4963             this.pop();
4964         }
4965     };
4966     /*\
4967      * Set.splice
4968      [ method ]
4969      **
4970      * Removes given element from the set
4971      **
4972      > Parameters
4973      **
4974      - index (number) position of the deletion
4975      - count (number) number of element to remove
4976      - insertion… (object) #optional elements to insert
4977      = (object) set elements that were deleted
4978     \*/
4979     setproto.splice = function (index, count, insertion) {
4980         index = index < 0 ? mmax(this.length + index, 0) : index;
4981         count = mmax(0, mmin(this.length - index, count));
4982         var tail = [],
4983             todel = [],
4984             args = [],
4985             i;
4986         for (i = 2; i < arguments.length; i++) {
4987             args.push(arguments[i]);
4988         }
4989         for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
4990             todel.push(this[index + i]);
4991         }
4992         for (; i < this.length - index; i++) {
4993             tail.push(this[index + i]);
4994         }
4995         var arglen = args.length;
4996         for (i = 0; i < arglen + tail.length; i++) {
4997             this.items[index + i] = this[index + i] = i < arglen ? args[i] : tail[i - arglen];
4998         }
4999         i = this.items.length = this.length -= count - arglen;
5000         while (this[i]) {
5001             delete this[i++];
5002         }
5003         return new Set(todel);
5004     };
5005     /*\
5006      * Set.exclude
5007      [ method ]
5008      **
5009      * Removes given element from the set
5010      **
5011      > Parameters
5012      **
5013      - element (object) element to remove
5014      = (boolean) `true` if object was found & removed from the set
5015     \*/
5016     setproto.exclude = function (el) {
5017         for (var i = 0, ii = this.length; i < ii; i++) if (this[i] == el) {
5018             this.splice(i, 1);
5019             return true;
5020         }
5021     };
5022     setproto.animate = function (params, ms, easing, callback) {
5023         (R.is(easing, "function") || !easing) && (callback = easing || null);
5024         var len = this.items.length,
5025             i = len,
5026             item,
5027             set = this,
5028             collector;
5029         if (!len) {
5030             return this;
5031         }
5032         callback && (collector = function () {
5033             !--len && callback.call(set);
5034         });
5035         easing = R.is(easing, string) ? easing : collector;
5036         var anim = R.animation(params, ms, easing, collector);
5037         item = this.items[--i].animate(anim);
5038         while (i--) {
5039             this.items[i] && !this.items[i].removed && this.items[i].animateWith(item, anim, anim);
5040             (this.items[i] && !this.items[i].removed) || len--;
5041         }
5042         return this;
5043     };
5044     setproto.insertAfter = function (el) {
5045         var i = this.items.length;
5046         while (i--) {
5047             this.items[i].insertAfter(el);
5048         }
5049         return this;
5050     };
5051     setproto.getBBox = function () {
5052         var x = [],
5053             y = [],
5054             x2 = [],
5055             y2 = [];
5056         for (var i = this.items.length; i--;) if (!this.items[i].removed) {
5057             var box = this.items[i].getBBox();
5058             x.push(box.x);
5059             y.push(box.y);
5060             x2.push(box.x + box.width);
5061             y2.push(box.y + box.height);
5062         }
5063         x = mmin[apply](0, x);
5064         y = mmin[apply](0, y);
5065         x2 = mmax[apply](0, x2);
5066         y2 = mmax[apply](0, y2);
5067         return {
5068             x: x,
5069             y: y,
5070             x2: x2,
5071             y2: y2,
5072             width: x2 - x,
5073             height: y2 - y
5074         };
5075     };
5076     setproto.clone = function (s) {
5077         s = this.paper.set();
5078         for (var i = 0, ii = this.items.length; i < ii; i++) {
5079             s.push(this.items[i].clone());
5080         }
5081         return s;
5082     };

5084         return "Rapha\xebl\u2018s set";
5085     };

5124     /*\
5125      * Raphael.registerFont
5126      [ method ]
5127      **
5128      * Adds given font to the registered set of fonts for Raphaël. Should be used as an internal call from within Cufón’s font file.
5129      * Returns original parameter, so it could be used with chaining.
5130      # <a href="http://wiki.github.com/sorccu/cufon/about">More about Cufón and how to convert your font form TTF, OTF, etc to JavaScript file.</a>
5131      **
5132      > Parameters
5133      **
5134      - font (object) the font to register
5135      = (object) the font you passed in
5136      > Usage
5137      | Cufon.registerFont(Raphael.registerFont({…}));
5138     \*/
5139     R.registerFont = function (font) {
5140         if (!font.face) {
5141             return font;
5142         }
5143         this.fonts = this.fonts || {};
5144         var fontcopy = {
5145                 w: font.w,
5146                 face: {},
5147                 glyphs: {}
5148             },
5149             family = font.face["font-family"];
5150         for (var prop in font.face) if (font.face[has](prop)) {
5151             fontcopy.face[prop] = font.face[prop];
5152         }
5153         if (this.fonts[family]) {
5154             this.fonts[family].push(fontcopy);
5155         } else {
5156             this.fonts[family] = [fontcopy];
5157         }
5158         if (!font.svg) {
5159             fontcopy.face["units-per-em"] = toInt(font.face["units-per-em"], 10);
5160             for (var glyph in font.glyphs) if (font.glyphs[has](glyph)) {
5161                 var path = font.glyphs[glyph];
5162                 fontcopy.glyphs[glyph] = {
5163                     w: path.w,
5164                     k: {},
5165                     d: path.d && "M" + path.d.replace(/[mlcxtrv]/g, function (command) {
5166                             return {l: "L", c: "C", x: "z", t: "m", r: "l", v: "c"}[command] || "M";
5167                         }) + "z"
5168                 };
5169                 if (path.k) {
5170                     for (var k in path.k) if (path[has](k)) {
5171                         fontcopy.glyphs[glyph].k[k] = path.k[k];
5172                     }
5173                 }
5174             }
5175         }
5176         return font;
5177     };
5178     /*\
5179      * Paper.getFont
5180      [ method ]
5181      **
5182      * Finds font object in the registered fonts by given parameters. You could specify only one word from the font name, like “Myriad” for “Myriad Pro”.
5183      **
5184      > Parameters
5185      **
5186      - family (string) font family name or any word from it
5187      - weight (string) #optional font weight
5188      - style (string) #optional font style
5189      - stretch (string) #optional font stretch
5190      = (object) the font object
5191      > Usage
5192      | paper.print(100, 100, "Test string", paper.getFont("Times", 800), 30);
5193     \*/
5194     paperproto.getFont = function (family, weight, style, stretch) {
5195         stretch = stretch || "normal";
5196         style = style || "normal";
5197         weight = +weight || {normal: 400, bold: 700, lighter: 300, bolder: 800}[weight] || 400;
5198         if (!R.fonts) {
5199             return;
5200         }
5201         var font = R.fonts[family];
5202         if (!font) {
5203             var name = new RegExp("(^|\\s)" + family.replace(/[^\w\d\s+!~.:_-]/g, E) + "(\\s|$)", "i");
5204             for (var fontName in R.fonts) if (R.fonts[has](fontName)) {
5205                 if (name.test(fontName)) {
5206                     font = R.fonts[fontName];
5207                     break;
5208                 }
5209             }
5210         }
5211         var thefont;
5212         if (font) {
5213             for (var i = 0, ii = font.length; i < ii; i++) {
5214                 thefont = font[i];
5215                 if (thefont.face["font-weight"] == weight && (thefont.face["font-style"] == style || !thefont.face["font-style"]) && thefont.face["font-stretch"] == stretch) {
5216                     break;
5217                 }
5218             }
5219         }
5220         return thefont;
5221     };
5222     /*\
5223      * Paper.print
5224      [ method ]
5225      **
5226      * Creates path that represent given text written using given font at given position with given size.
5227      * Result of the method is path element that contains whole text as a separate path.
5228      **
5229      > Parameters
5230      **
5231      - x (number) x position of the text
5232      - y (number) y position of the text
5233      - string (string) text to print
5234      - font (object) font object, see @Paper.getFont
5235      - size (number) #optional size of the font, default is `16`
5236      - origin (string) #optional could be `"baseline"` or `"middle"`, default is `"middle"`
5237      - letter_spacing (number) #optional number in range `-1..1`, default is `0`
5238      - line_spacing (number) #optional number in range `1..3`, default is `1`
5239      = (object) resulting path element, which consist of all letters
5240      > Usage
5241      | var txt = r.print(10, 50, "print", r.getFont("Museo"), 30).attr({fill: "#fff"});
5242     \*/
5243     paperproto.print = function (x, y, string, font, size, origin, letter_spacing, line_spacing) {
5244         origin = origin || "middle"; // baseline|middle
5245         letter_spacing = mmax(mmin(letter_spacing || 0, 1), -1);
5246         line_spacing = mmax(mmin(line_spacing || 1, 3), 1);
5247         var letters = Str(string)[split](E),
5248             shift = 0,
5249             notfirst = 0,
5250             path = E,
5251             scale;
5252         R.is(font, "string") && (font = this.getFont(font));
5253         if (font) {
5254             scale = (size || 16) / font.face["units-per-em"];
5255             var bb = font.face.bbox[split](separator),
5256                 top = +bb[0],
5257                 lineHeight = bb[3] - bb[1],
5258                 shifty = 0,
5259                 height = +bb[1] + (origin == "baseline" ? lineHeight + (+font.face.descent) : lineHeight / 2);
5260             for (var i = 0, ii = letters.length; i < ii; i++) {
5261                 if (letters[i] == "\n") {
5262                     shift = 0;
5263                     curr = 0;
5264                     notfirst = 0;
5265                     shifty += lineHeight * line_spacing;
5266                 } else {
5267                     var prev = notfirst && font.glyphs[letters[i - 1]] || {},
5268                         curr = font.glyphs[letters[i]];
5269                     shift += notfirst ? (prev.w || font.w) + (prev.k && prev.k[letters[i]] || 0) + (font.w * letter_spacing) : 0;
5270                     notfirst = 1;
5271                 }
5272                 if (curr && curr.d) {
5273                     path += R.transformPath(curr.d, ["t", shift * scale, shifty * scale, "s", scale, scale, top, height, "t", (x - top) / scale, (y - height) / scale]);
5274                 }
5275             }
5276         }
5277         return this.path(path).attr({
5278             fill: "#000",
5279             stroke: "none"
5280         });

5283     /*\
5284      * Paper.add
5285      [ method ]
5286      **
5287      * Imports elements in JSON array in format `{type: type, <attributes>}`
5288      **
5289      > Parameters
5290      **
5291      - json (array)
5292      = (object) resulting set of imported elements
5293      > Usage
5294      | paper.add([
5295      |     {
5296      |         type: "circle",
5297      |         cx: 10,
5298      |         cy: 10,
5299      |         r: 5
5300      |     },
5301      |     {
5302      |         type: "rect",
5303      |         x: 10,
5304      |         y: 10,
5305      |         width: 10,
5306      |         height: 10,
5307      |         fill: "#fc0"
5308      |     }
5309      | ]);
5310     \*/
5311     paperproto.add = function (json) {
5312         if (R.is(json, "array")) {
5313             var res = this.set(),
5314                 i = 0,
5315                 ii = json.length,
5316                 j;
5317             for (; i < ii; i++) {
5318                 j = json[i] || {};
5319                 elements[has](j.type) && res.push(this[j.type]().attr(j));
5320             }
5321         }
5322         return res;
5323     };
5324 
5325     /*\
5326      * Raphael.format
5327      [ method ]
5328      **
5329      * Simple format function. Replaces construction of type “`{<number>}`” to the corresponding argument.
5330      **
5331      > Parameters
5332      **
5333      - token (string) string to format
5334      - … (string) rest of arguments will be treated as parameters for replacement
5335      = (string) formated string
5336      > Usage
5337      | var x = 10,
5338      |     y = 20,
5339      |     width = 40,
5340      |     height = 50;
5341      | // this will draw a rectangular shape equivalent to "M10,20h40v50h-40z"
5342      | paper.path(Raphael.format("M{0},{1}h{2}v{3}h{4}z", x, y, width, height, -width));
5343     \*/
5344     R.format = function (token, params) {
5345         var args = R.is(params, array) ? [0][concat](params) : arguments;
5346         token && R.is(token, string) && args.length - 1 && (token = token.replace(formatrg, function (str, i) {
5347             return args[++i] == null ? E : args[i];
5348         }));
5349         return token || E;
5350     };
5351     /*\
5352      * Raphael.fullfill
5353      [ method ]
5354      **
5355      * A little bit more advanced format function than @Raphael.format. Replaces construction of type “`{<name>}`” to the corresponding argument.
5356      **
5357      > Parameters
5358      **
5359      - token (string) string to format
5360      - json (object) object which properties will be used as a replacement
5361      = (string) formated string
5362      > Usage
5363      | // this will draw a rectangular shape equivalent to "M10,20h40v50h-40z"
5364      | paper.path(Raphael.fullfill("M{x},{y}h{dim.width}v{dim.height}h{dim['negative width']}z", {
5365      |     x: 10,
5366      |     y: 20,
5367      |     dim: {
5368      |         width: 40,
5369      |         height: 50,
5370      |         "negative width": -40
5371      |     }
5372      | }));
5373     \*/
5374     R.fullfill = (function () {
5375         var tokenRegex = /\{([^\}]+)\}/g,
5376             objNotationRegex = /(?:(?:^|\.)(.+?)(?=\[|\.|$|\()|\[('|")(.+?)\2\])(\(\))?/g, // matches .xxxxx or ["xxxxx"] to run over object properties
5377             replacer = function (all, key, obj) {
5378                 var res = obj;
5379                 key.replace(objNotationRegex, function (all, name, quote, quotedName, isFunc) {
5380                     name = name || quotedName;
5381                     if (res) {
5382                         if (name in res) {
5383                             res = res[name];
5384                         }
5385                         typeof res == "function" && isFunc && (res = res());
5386                     }
5387                 });
5388                 res = (res == null || res == obj ? all : res) + "";
5389                 return res;
5390             };
5391         return function (str, obj) {
5392             return String(str).replace(tokenRegex, function (all, key) {
5393                 return replacer(all, key, obj);
5394             });
5395         };
5396     })();
5397     /*\
5398      * Raphael.ninja
5399      [ method ]
5400      **
5401      * If you want to leave no trace of Raphaël (Well, Raphaël creates only one global variable `Raphael`, but anyway.) You can use `ninja` method.
5402      * Beware, that in this case plugins could stop working, because they are depending on global variable existance.
5403      **
5404      = (object) Raphael object
5405      > Usage
5406      | (function (local_raphael) {
5407      |     var paper = local_raphael(10, 10, 320, 200);
5408      |     …
5409      | })(Raphael.ninja());
5410     \*/
5411     R.ninja = function () {
5412         oldRaphael.was ? (g.win.Raphael = oldRaphael.is) : delete Raphael;
5413         return R;
5414     };
5415     /*\
5416      * Raphael.st
5417      [ property (object) ]
5418      **
5419      * You can add your own method to elements and sets. It is wise to add a set method for each element method
5420      * you added, so you will be able to call the same method on sets too.
5421      **
5422      * See also @Raphael.el.
5423      > Usage
5424      | Raphael.el.red = function () {
5425      |     this.attr({fill: "#f00"});
5426      | };
5427      | Raphael.st.red = function () {
5428      |     this.forEach(function (el) {
5429      |         el.red();
5430      |     });
5431      | };
5432      | // then use it
5433      | paper.set(paper.circle(100, 100, 20), paper.circle(110, 100, 20)).red();
5434     \*/
5435     R.st = setproto;

5438         loaded = true;
5439     });

5442     (function (doc, loaded, f) {

5444             doc.addEventListener(loaded, f = function () {
5445                 doc.removeEventListener(loaded, f, false);
5446                 doc.readyState = "complete";
5447             }, false);
5448             doc.readyState = "loading";
5449         }
5450         function isLoaded() {
5451             (/in/).test(doc.readyState) ? setTimeout(isLoaded, 9) : R.eve("raphael.DOMload");

5494     var $ = function (el, attr) {
5495         if (attr) {
5496             if (typeof el == "string") {
5497                 el = $(el);
5498             }
5499             for (var key in attr) if (attr[has](key)) {
5500                 if (key.substring(0, 6) == "xlink:") {
5501                     el.setAttributeNS(xlink, key.substring(6), Str(attr[key]));
5502                 } else {
5503                     el.setAttribute(key, Str(attr[key]));
5504                 }
5505             }
5506         } else {
5507             el = R._g.doc.createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/svg", el);
5508             el.style && (el.style.webkitTapHighlightColor = "rgba(0,0,0,0)");
