5512     addGradientFill = function (element, gradient) {
5513         var type = "linear",
5514             id = element.id + gradient,
5515             fx = .5, fy = .5,
5516             o = element.node,
5517             SVG = element.paper,
5518             s = o.style,
5519             el = R._g.doc.getElementById(id);
5520         if (!el) {
5521             gradient = Str(gradient).replace(R._radial_gradient, function (all, _fx, _fy) {
5522                 type = "radial";
5523                 if (_fx && _fy) {
5524                     fx = toFloat(_fx);
5525                     fy = toFloat(_fy);
5526                     var dir = ((fy > .5) * 2 - 1);
5527                     pow(fx - .5, 2) + pow(fy - .5, 2) > .25 &&
5528                         (fy = math.sqrt(.25 - pow(fx - .5, 2)) * dir + .5) &&
5529                         fy != .5 &&
5530                         (fy = fy.toFixed(5) - 1e-5 * dir);
5531                 }
5532                 return E;
5533             });
5534             gradient = gradient.split(/\s*\-\s*/);
5535             if (type == "linear") {
5536                 var angle = gradient.shift();
5537                 angle = -toFloat(angle);
5538                 if (isNaN(angle)) {
5539                     return null;
5540                 }
5541                 var vector = [0, 0, math.cos(R.rad(angle)), math.sin(R.rad(angle))],
5542                     max = 1 / (mmax(abs(vector[2]), abs(vector[3])) || 1);
5543                 vector[2] *= max;
5544                 vector[3] *= max;
5545                 if (vector[2] < 0) {
5546                     vector[0] = -vector[2];
5547                     vector[2] = 0;
5548                 }
5549                 if (vector[3] < 0) {
5550                     vector[1] = -vector[3];
5551                     vector[3] = 0;
5552                 }
5553             }
5554             var dots = R._parseDots(gradient);
5555             if (!dots) {
5556                 return null;
5557             }
5558             id = id.replace(/[\(\)\s,\xb0#]/g, "_");
5559 
5560             if (element.gradient && id != element.gradient.id) {
5561                 SVG.defs.removeChild(element.gradient);
5562                 delete element.gradient;
5563             }
5564 
5565             if (!element.gradient) {
5566                 el = $(type + "Gradient", {id: id});
5567                 element.gradient = el;
5568                 $(el, type == "radial" ? {
5569                     fx: fx,
5570                     fy: fy
5571                 } : {
5572                     x1: vector[0],
5573                     y1: vector[1],
5574                     x2: vector[2],
5575                     y2: vector[3],
5576                     gradientTransform: element.matrix.invert()
5577                 });
5578                 SVG.defs.appendChild(el);
5579                 for (var i = 0, ii = dots.length; i < ii; i++) {
5580                     el.appendChild($("stop", {
5581                         offset: dots[i].offset ? dots[i].offset : i ? "100%" : "0%",
5582                         "stop-color": dots[i].color || "#fff"
5583                     }));
5584                 }
5585             }
5586         }
5587         $(o, {
5588             fill: "url('" + document.location + "#" + id + "')",
5589             opacity: 1,
5590             "fill-opacity": 1
5591         });
5592         s.fill = E;
5593         s.opacity = 1;
5594         s.fillOpacity = 1;
5595         return 1;
5596     },
5597     updatePosition = function (o) {
5598         var bbox = o.getBBox(1);
5599         $(o.pattern, {patternTransform: o.matrix.invert() + " translate(" + bbox.x + "," + bbox.y + ")"});
5600     },
5601     addArrow = function (o, value, isEnd) {
5602         if (o.type == "path") {
5603             var values = Str(value).toLowerCase().split("-"),
5604                 p = o.paper,
5605                 se = isEnd ? "end" : "start",
5606                 node = o.node,
5607                 attrs = o.attrs,
5608                 stroke = attrs["stroke-width"],
5609                 i = values.length,
5610                 type = "classic",
5611                 from,
5612                 to,
5613                 dx,
5614                 refX,
5615                 attr,
5616                 w = 3,
5617                 h = 3,
5618                 t = 5;
5619             while (i--) {
5620                 switch (values[i]) {
5621                     case "block":
5622                     case "classic":
5623                     case "oval":
5624                     case "diamond":
5625                     case "open":
5626                     case "none":
5627                         type = values[i];
5628                         break;
5629                     case "wide": h = 5; break;
5630                     case "narrow": h = 2; break;
5631                     case "long": w = 5; break;
5632                     case "short": w = 2; break;
5633                 }
5634             }
5635             if (type == "open") {
5636                 w += 2;
5637                 h += 2;
5638                 t += 2;
5639                 dx = 1;
5640                 refX = isEnd ? 4 : 1;
5641                 attr = {
5642                     fill: "none",
5643                     stroke: attrs.stroke
5644                 };
5645             } else {
5646                 refX = dx = w / 2;
5647                 attr = {
5648                     fill: attrs.stroke,
5649                     stroke: "none"
5650                 };
5651             }
5652             if (o._.arrows) {
5653                 if (isEnd) {
5654                     o._.arrows.endPath && markerCounter[o._.arrows.endPath]--;
5655                     o._.arrows.endMarker && markerCounter[o._.arrows.endMarker]--;
5656                 } else {
5657                     o._.arrows.startPath && markerCounter[o._.arrows.startPath]--;
5658                     o._.arrows.startMarker && markerCounter[o._.arrows.startMarker]--;
5659                 }
5660             } else {
5661                 o._.arrows = {};
5662             }
5663             if (type != "none") {
5664                 var pathId = "raphael-marker-" + type,
5665                     markerId = "raphael-marker-" + se + type + w + h + "-obj" + o.id;
5666                 if (!R._g.doc.getElementById(pathId)) {
5667                     p.defs.appendChild($($("path"), {
5668                         "stroke-linecap": "round",
5669                         d: markers[type],
5670                         id: pathId
5671                     }));
5672                     markerCounter[pathId] = 1;
5673                 } else {
5674                     markerCounter[pathId]++;
5675                 }
5676                 var marker = R._g.doc.getElementById(markerId),
5677                     use;
5678                 if (!marker) {
5679                     marker = $($("marker"), {
5680                         id: markerId,
5681                         markerHeight: h,
5682                         markerWidth: w,
5683                         orient: "auto",
5684                         refX: refX,
5685                         refY: h / 2
5686                     });
5687                     use = $($("use"), {
5688                         "xlink:href": "#" + pathId,
5689                         transform: (isEnd ? "rotate(180 " + w / 2 + " " + h / 2 + ") " : E) + "scale(" + w / t + "," + h / t + ")",
5690                         "stroke-width": (1 / ((w / t + h / t) / 2)).toFixed(4)
5691                     });
5692                     marker.appendChild(use);
5693                     p.defs.appendChild(marker);
5694                     markerCounter[markerId] = 1;
5695                 } else {
5696                     markerCounter[markerId]++;
5697                     use = marker.getElementsByTagName("use")[0];
5698                 }
5699                 $(use, attr);
5700                 var delta = dx * (type != "diamond" && type != "oval");
5701                 if (isEnd) {
5702                     from = o._.arrows.startdx * stroke || 0;
5703                     to = R.getTotalLength(attrs.path) - delta * stroke;
5704                 } else {
5705                     from = delta * stroke;
5706                     to = R.getTotalLength(attrs.path) - (o._.arrows.enddx * stroke || 0);
5707                 }
5708                 attr = {};
5709                 attr["marker-" + se] = "url(#" + markerId + ")";
5710                 if (to || from) {
5711                     attr.d = R.getSubpath(attrs.path, from, to);
5712                 }
5713                 $(node, attr);
5714                 o._.arrows[se + "Path"] = pathId;
5715                 o._.arrows[se + "Marker"] = markerId;
5716                 o._.arrows[se + "dx"] = delta;
5717                 o._.arrows[se + "Type"] = type;
5718                 o._.arrows[se + "String"] = value;
5719             } else {
5720                 if (isEnd) {
5721                     from = o._.arrows.startdx * stroke || 0;
5722                     to = R.getTotalLength(attrs.path) - from;
5723                 } else {
5724                     from = 0;
5725                     to = R.getTotalLength(attrs.path) - (o._.arrows.enddx * stroke || 0);
5726                 }
5727                 o._.arrows[se + "Path"] && $(node, {d: R.getSubpath(attrs.path, from, to)});
5728                 delete o._.arrows[se + "Path"];
5729                 delete o._.arrows[se + "Marker"];
5730                 delete o._.arrows[se + "dx"];
5731                 delete o._.arrows[se + "Type"];
5732                 delete o._.arrows[se + "String"];
5733             }
5734             for (attr in markerCounter) if (markerCounter[has](attr) && !markerCounter[attr]) {
5735                 var item = R._g.doc.getElementById(attr);
5736                 item && item.parentNode.removeChild(item);
5737             }
5738         }
5739     },
5740     dasharray = {
5741         "": [0],
5742         "none": [0],
5743         "-": [3, 1],
5744         ".": [1, 1],
5745         "-.": [3, 1, 1, 1],
5746         "-..": [3, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1],
5747         ". ": [1, 3],
5748         "- ": [4, 3],
5749         "--": [8, 3],
5750         "- .": [4, 3, 1, 3],
5751         "--.": [8, 3, 1, 3],
5752         "--..": [8, 3, 1, 3, 1, 3]
5753     },
5754     addDashes = function (o, value, params) {
5755         value = dasharray[Str(value).toLowerCase()];
5756         if (value) {
5757             var width = o.attrs["stroke-width"] || "1",
5758                 butt = {round: width, square: width, butt: 0}[o.attrs["stroke-linecap"] || params["stroke-linecap"]] || 0,
5759                 dashes = [],
5760                 i = value.length;
5761             while (i--) {
5762                 dashes[i] = value[i] * width + ((i % 2) ? 1 : -1) * butt;
5763             }
5764             $(o.node, {"stroke-dasharray": dashes.join(",")});
5765         }
5766     },
5767     setFillAndStroke = function (o, params) {
5768         var node = o.node,
5769             attrs = o.attrs,
5770             vis = node.style.visibility;
5771         node.style.visibility = "hidden";
5772         for (var att in params) {
5773             if (params[has](att)) {
5774                 if (!R._availableAttrs[has](att)) {
5775                     continue;
5776                 }
5777                 var value = params[att];
5778                 attrs[att] = value;
5779                 switch (att) {
5780                     case "blur":
5781                         o.blur(value);
5782                         break;
5783                     case "title":
5784                         var title = node.getElementsByTagName("title");
5785 
5786                         // Use the existing <title>.
5787                         if (title.length && (title = title[0])) {
5788                           title.firstChild.nodeValue = value;
5789                         } else {
5790                           title = $("title");
5791                           var val = R._g.doc.createTextNode(value);
5792                           title.appendChild(val);
5793                           node.appendChild(title);
5794                         }
5795                         break;
5796                     case "href":
5797                     case "target":
5798                         var pn = node.parentNode;
5799                         if (pn.tagName.toLowerCase() != "a") {
5800                             var hl = $("a");
5801                             pn.insertBefore(hl, node);
5802                             hl.appendChild(node);
5803                             pn = hl;
5804                         }
5805                         if (att == "target") {
5806                             pn.setAttributeNS(xlink, "show", value == "blank" ? "new" : value);
5807                         } else {
5808                             pn.setAttributeNS(xlink, att, value);
5809                         }
5810                         break;
5811                     case "cursor":
5812                         node.style.cursor = value;
5813                         break;
5814                     case "transform":
5815                         o.transform(value);
5816                         break;
5817                     case "arrow-start":
5818                         addArrow(o, value);
5819                         break;
5820                     case "arrow-end":
5821                         addArrow(o, value, 1);
5822                         break;
5823                     case "clip-rect":
5824                         var rect = Str(value).split(separator);
5825                         if (rect.length == 4) {
5826                             o.clip && o.clip.parentNode.parentNode.removeChild(o.clip.parentNode);
5827                             var el = $("clipPath"),
5828                                 rc = $("rect");
5829                             el.id = R.createUUID();
5830                             $(rc, {
5831                                 x: rect[0],
5832                                 y: rect[1],
5833                                 width: rect[2],
5834                                 height: rect[3]
5835                             });
5836                             el.appendChild(rc);
5837                             o.paper.defs.appendChild(el);
5838                             $(node, {"clip-path": "url(#" + el.id + ")"});
5839                             o.clip = rc;
5840                         }
5841                         if (!value) {
5842                             var path = node.getAttribute("clip-path");
5843                             if (path) {
5844                                 var clip = R._g.doc.getElementById(path.replace(/(^url\(#|\)$)/g, E));
5845                                 clip && clip.parentNode.removeChild(clip);
5846                                 $(node, {"clip-path": E});
5847                                 delete o.clip;
5848                             }
5849                         }
5850                     break;
5851                     case "path":
5852                         if (o.type == "path") {
5853                             $(node, {d: value ? attrs.path = R._pathToAbsolute(value) : "M0,0"});
5854                             o._.dirty = 1;
5855                             if (o._.arrows) {
5856                                 "startString" in o._.arrows && addArrow(o, o._.arrows.startString);
5857                                 "endString" in o._.arrows && addArrow(o, o._.arrows.endString, 1);
5858                             }
5859                         }
5860                         break;
5861                     case "width":
5862                         node.setAttribute(att, value);
5863                         o._.dirty = 1;
5864                         if (attrs.fx) {
5865                             att = "x";
5866                             value = attrs.x;
5867                         } else {
5868                             break;
5869                         }
5870                     case "x":
5871                         if (attrs.fx) {
5872                             value = -attrs.x - (attrs.width || 0);
5873                         }
5874                     case "rx":
5875                         if (att == "rx" && o.type == "rect") {
5876                             break;
5877                         }
5878                     case "cx":
5879                         node.setAttribute(att, value);
5880                         o.pattern && updatePosition(o);
5881                         o._.dirty = 1;
5882                         break;
5883                     case "height":
5884                         node.setAttribute(att, value);
5885                         o._.dirty = 1;
5886                         if (attrs.fy) {
5887                             att = "y";
5888                             value = attrs.y;
5889                         } else {
5890                             break;
5891                         }
5892                     case "y":
5893                         if (attrs.fy) {
5894                             value = -attrs.y - (attrs.height || 0);
5895                         }
5896                     case "ry":
5897                         if (att == "ry" && o.type == "rect") {
5898                             break;
5899                         }
5900                     case "cy":
5901                         node.setAttribute(att, value);
5902                         o.pattern && updatePosition(o);
5903                         o._.dirty = 1;
5904                         break;
5905                     case "r":
5906                         if (o.type == "rect") {
5907                             $(node, {rx: value, ry: value});
5908                         } else {
5909                             node.setAttribute(att, value);
5910                         }
5911                         o._.dirty = 1;
5912                         break;
5913                     case "src":
5914                         if (o.type == "image") {
5915                             node.setAttributeNS(xlink, "href", value);
5916                         }
5917                         break;
5918                     case "stroke-width":
5919                         if (o._.sx != 1 || o._.sy != 1) {
5920                             value /= mmax(abs(o._.sx), abs(o._.sy)) || 1;
5921                         }
5922                         node.setAttribute(att, value);
5923                         if (attrs["stroke-dasharray"]) {
5924                             addDashes(o, attrs["stroke-dasharray"], params);
5925                         }
5926                         if (o._.arrows) {
5927                             "startString" in o._.arrows && addArrow(o, o._.arrows.startString);
5928                             "endString" in o._.arrows && addArrow(o, o._.arrows.endString, 1);
5929                         }
5930                         break;
5931                     case "stroke-dasharray":
5932                         addDashes(o, value, params);
5933                         break;
5934                     case "fill":
5935                         var isURL = Str(value).match(R._ISURL);
5936                         if (isURL) {
5937                             el = $("pattern");
5938                             var ig = $("image");
5939                             el.id = R.createUUID();
5940                             $(el, {x: 0, y: 0, patternUnits: "userSpaceOnUse", height: 1, width: 1});
5941                             $(ig, {x: 0, y: 0, "xlink:href": isURL[1]});
5942                             el.appendChild(ig);
5943 
5944                             (function (el) {
5945                                 R._preload(isURL[1], function () {
5946                                     var w = this.offsetWidth,
5947                                         h = this.offsetHeight;
5948                                     $(el, {width: w, height: h});
5949                                     $(ig, {width: w, height: h});
5950                                     o.paper.safari();
5951                                 });
5952                             })(el);
5953                             o.paper.defs.appendChild(el);
5954                             $(node, {fill: "url(#" + el.id + ")"});
5955                             o.pattern = el;
5956                             o.pattern && updatePosition(o);
5957                             break;
5958                         }
5959                         var clr = R.getRGB(value);
5960                         if (!clr.error) {
5961                             delete params.gradient;
5962                             delete attrs.gradient;
5963                             !R.is(attrs.opacity, "undefined") &&
5964                                 R.is(params.opacity, "undefined") &&
5965                                 $(node, {opacity: attrs.opacity});
5966                             !R.is(attrs["fill-opacity"], "undefined") &&
5967                                 R.is(params["fill-opacity"], "undefined") &&
5968                                 $(node, {"fill-opacity": attrs["fill-opacity"]});
5969                         } else if ((o.type == "circle" || o.type == "ellipse" || Str(value).charAt() != "r") && addGradientFill(o, value)) {
5970                             if ("opacity" in attrs || "fill-opacity" in attrs) {
5971                                 var gradient = R._g.doc.getElementById(node.getAttribute("fill").replace(/^url\(#|\)$/g, E));
5972                                 if (gradient) {
5973                                     var stops = gradient.getElementsByTagName("stop");
5974                                     $(stops[stops.length - 1], {"stop-opacity": ("opacity" in attrs ? attrs.opacity : 1) * ("fill-opacity" in attrs ? attrs["fill-opacity"] : 1)});
5975                                 }
5976                             }
5977                             attrs.gradient = value;
5978                             attrs.fill = "none";
5979                             break;
5980                         }
5981                         clr[has]("opacity") && $(node, {"fill-opacity": clr.opacity > 1 ? clr.opacity / 100 : clr.opacity});
5982                     case "stroke":
5983                         clr = R.getRGB(value);
5984                         node.setAttribute(att, clr.hex);
5985                         att == "stroke" && clr[has]("opacity") && $(node, {"stroke-opacity": clr.opacity > 1 ? clr.opacity / 100 : clr.opacity});
5986                         if (att == "stroke" && o._.arrows) {
5987                             "startString" in o._.arrows && addArrow(o, o._.arrows.startString);
5988                             "endString" in o._.arrows && addArrow(o, o._.arrows.endString, 1);
5989                         }
5990                         break;
5991                     case "gradient":
5992                         (o.type == "circle" || o.type == "ellipse" || Str(value).charAt() != "r") && addGradientFill(o, value);
5993                         break;
5994                     case "opacity":
5995                         if (attrs.gradient && !attrs[has]("stroke-opacity")) {
5996                             $(node, {"stroke-opacity": value > 1 ? value / 100 : value});
5997                         }
5998                         // fall
5999                     case "fill-opacity":
6000                         if (attrs.gradient) {
6001                             gradient = R._g.doc.getElementById(node.getAttribute("fill").replace(/^url\(#|\)$/g, E));
6002                             if (gradient) {
6003                                 stops = gradient.getElementsByTagName("stop");
6004                                 $(stops[stops.length - 1], {"stop-opacity": value});
6005                             }
6006                             break;
6007                         }
6008                     default:
6009                         att == "font-size" && (value = toInt(value, 10) + "px");
6010                         var cssrule = att.replace(/(\-.)/g, function (w) {
6011                             return w.substring(1).toUpperCase();
6012                         });
6013                         node.style[cssrule] = value;
6014                         o._.dirty = 1;
6015                         node.setAttribute(att, value);
6016                         break;
6017                 }
6018             }
6019         }
6020 
6021         tuneText(o, params);
6022         node.style.visibility = vis;
6023     },
6024     leading = 1.2,
6025     tuneText = function (el, params) {
6026         if (el.type != "text" || !(params[has]("text") || params[has]("font") || params[has]("font-size") || params[has]("x") || params[has]("y"))) {
6027             return;
6028         }
6029         var a = el.attrs,
6030             node = el.node,
6031             fontSize = node.firstChild ? toInt(R._g.doc.defaultView.getComputedStyle(node.firstChild, E).getPropertyValue("font-size"), 10) : 10;
6032 
6033         if (params[has]("text")) {
6034             a.text = params.text;
6035             while (node.firstChild) {
6036                 node.removeChild(node.firstChild);
6037             }
6038             var texts = Str(params.text).split("\n"),
6039                 tspans = [],
6040                 tspan;
6041             for (var i = 0, ii = texts.length; i < ii; i++) {
6042                 tspan = $("tspan");
6043                 i && $(tspan, {dy: fontSize * leading, x: a.x});
6044                 tspan.appendChild(R._g.doc.createTextNode(texts[i]));
6045                 node.appendChild(tspan);
6046                 tspans[i] = tspan;
6047             }
6048         } else {
6049             tspans = node.getElementsByTagName("tspan");
6050             for (i = 0, ii = tspans.length; i < ii; i++) if (i) {
6051                 $(tspans[i], {dy: fontSize * leading, x: a.x});
6052             } else {
6053                 $(tspans[0], {dy: 0});
6054             }
6055         }
6056         $(node, {x: a.x, y: a.y});
6057         el._.dirty = 1;
6058         var bb = el._getBBox(),
6059             dif = a.y - (bb.y + bb.height / 2);
6060         dif && R.is(dif, "finite") && $(tspans[0], {dy: dif});
6061     },
6062     getRealNode = function (node) {

6064             return node.parentNode;
6065         } else {
6066             return node;
6067         }

6169     /*\
6170      * Element.rotate
6171      [ method ]
6172      **
6173      * Deprecated! Use @Element.transform instead.
6174      * Adds rotation by given angle around given point to the list of
6175      * transformations of the element.
6176      > Parameters
6177      - deg (number) angle in degrees
6178      - cx (number) #optional x coordinate of the centre of rotation
6179      - cy (number) #optional y coordinate of the centre of rotation
6180      * If cx & cy aren’t specified centre of the shape is used as a point of rotation.
6181      = (object) @Element
6182     \*/
6183     elproto.rotate = function (deg, cx, cy) {
6184         if (this.removed) {
6185             return this;
6186         }
6187         deg = Str(deg).split(separator);
6188         if (deg.length - 1) {
6189             cx = toFloat(deg[1]);
6190             cy = toFloat(deg[2]);
6191         }
6192         deg = toFloat(deg[0]);
6193         (cy == null) && (cx = cy);
6194         if (cx == null || cy == null) {
6195             var bbox = this.getBBox(1);
6196             cx = bbox.x + bbox.width / 2;
6197             cy = bbox.y + bbox.height / 2;
6198         }
6199         this.transform(this._.transform.concat([["r", deg, cx, cy]]));
6200         return this;
6201     };
6202     /*\
6203      * Element.scale
6204      [ method ]
6205      **
6206      * Deprecated! Use @Element.transform instead.
6207      * Adds scale by given amount relative to given point to the list of
6208      * transformations of the element.
6209      > Parameters
6210      - sx (number) horisontal scale amount
6211      - sy (number) vertical scale amount
6212      - cx (number) #optional x coordinate of the centre of scale
6213      - cy (number) #optional y coordinate of the centre of scale
6214      * If cx & cy aren’t specified centre of the shape is used instead.
6215      = (object) @Element
6216     \*/
6217     elproto.scale = function (sx, sy, cx, cy) {
6218         if (this.removed) {
6219             return this;
6220         }
6221         sx = Str(sx).split(separator);
6222         if (sx.length - 1) {
6223             sy = toFloat(sx[1]);
6224             cx = toFloat(sx[2]);
6225             cy = toFloat(sx[3]);
6226         }
6227         sx = toFloat(sx[0]);
6228         (sy == null) && (sy = sx);
6229         (cy == null) && (cx = cy);
6230         if (cx == null || cy == null) {
6231             var bbox = this.getBBox(1);
6232         }
6233         cx = cx == null ? bbox.x + bbox.width / 2 : cx;
6234         cy = cy == null ? bbox.y + bbox.height / 2 : cy;
6235         this.transform(this._.transform.concat([["s", sx, sy, cx, cy]]));
6236         return this;
6237     };
6238     /*\
6239      * Element.translate
6240      [ method ]
6241      **
6242      * Deprecated! Use @Element.transform instead.
6243      * Adds translation by given amount to the list of transformations of the element.
6244      > Parameters
6245      - dx (number) horisontal shift
6246      - dy (number) vertical shift
6247      = (object) @Element
6248     \*/
6249     elproto.translate = function (dx, dy) {
6250         if (this.removed) {
6251             return this;
6252         }
6253         dx = Str(dx).split(separator);
6254         if (dx.length - 1) {
6255             dy = toFloat(dx[1]);
6256         }
6257         dx = toFloat(dx[0]) || 0;
6258         dy = +dy || 0;
6259         this.transform(this._.transform.concat([["t", dx, dy]]));
6260         return this;
6261     };
6262     /*\
6263      * Element.transform
6264      [ method ]
6265      **
6266      * Adds transformation to the element which is separate to other attributes,
6267      * i.e. translation doesn’t change `x` or `y` of the rectange. The format
6268      * of transformation string is similar to the path string syntax:
6269      | "t100,100r30,100,100s2,2,100,100r45s1.5"
6270      * Each letter is a command. There are four commands: `t` is for translate, `r` is for rotate, `s` is for
6271      * scale and `m` is for matrix.
6272      *
6273      * There are also alternative “absolute” translation, rotation and scale: `T`, `R` and `S`. They will not take previous transformation into account. For example, `...T100,0` will always move element 100 px horisontally, while `...t100,0` could move it vertically if there is `r90` before. Just compare results of `r90t100,0` and `r90T100,0`.
6274      *
6275      * So, the example line above could be read like “translate by 100, 100; rotate 30° around 100, 100; scale twice around 100, 100;
6276      * rotate 45° around centre; scale 1.5 times relative to centre”. As you can see rotate and scale commands have origin
6277      * coordinates as optional parameters, the default is the centre point of the element.
6278      * Matrix accepts six parameters.
6279      > Usage
6280      | var el = paper.rect(10, 20, 300, 200);
6281      | // translate 100, 100, rotate 45°, translate -100, 0
6282      | el.transform("t100,100r45t-100,0");
6283      | // if you want you can append or prepend transformations
6284      | el.transform("...t50,50");
6285      | el.transform("s2...");
6286      | // or even wrap
6287      | el.transform("t50,50...t-50-50");
6288      | // to reset transformation call method with empty string
6289      | el.transform("");
6290      | // to get current value call it without parameters
6291      | console.log(el.transform());
6292      > Parameters
6293      - tstr (string) #optional transformation string
6294      * If tstr isn’t specified
6295      = (string) current transformation string
6296      * else
6297      = (object) @Element
6298     \*/
6299     elproto.transform = function (tstr) {
6300         var _ = this._;
6301         if (tstr == null) {
6302             return _.transform;
6303         }
6304         R._extractTransform(this, tstr);
6305 
6306         this.clip && $(this.clip, {transform: this.matrix.invert()});
6307         this.pattern && updatePosition(this);
6308         this.node && $(this.node, {transform: this.matrix});
6309 
6310         if (_.sx != 1 || _.sy != 1) {
6311             var sw = this.attrs[has]("stroke-width") ? this.attrs["stroke-width"] : 1;
6312             this.attr({"stroke-width": sw});
6313         }
6314 
6315         return this;
6316     };

6326         return this;

6337         return this;
6338     };
6339     /*\
6340      * Element.remove

6343      * Removes element from the paper.

6345     elproto.remove = function () {
6346         var node = getRealNode(this.node);
6347         if (this.removed || !node.parentNode) {
6348             return;
6349         }
6350         var paper = this.paper;
6351         paper.__set__ && paper.__set__.exclude(this);
6352         eve.unbind("raphael.*.*." + this.id);
6353         if (this.gradient) {
6354             paper.defs.removeChild(this.gradient);
6355         }
6356         R._tear(this, paper);
6357 
6358         node.parentNode.removeChild(node);
6359 
6360         // Remove custom data for element
6361         this.removeData();
6362 
6363         for (var i in this) {
6364             this[i] = typeof this[i] == "function" ? R._removedFactory(i) : null;
6365         }
6366         this.removed = true;
6367     };
6368     elproto._getBBox = function () {
6369         if (this.node.style.display == "none") {
6370             this.show();
6371             var hide = true;
6372         }
6373         var canvasHidden = false,
6374             containerStyle;
6375         if (this.paper.canvas.parentElement) {
6376           containerStyle = this.paper.canvas.parentElement.style;
6377         } //IE10+ can't find parentElement
6378         else if (this.paper.canvas.parentNode) {
6379           containerStyle = this.paper.canvas.parentNode.style;
6380         }
6381 
6382         if(containerStyle && containerStyle.display == "none") {
6383           canvasHidden = true;
6384           containerStyle.display = "";
6385         }
6386         var bbox = {};
6387         try {
6388             bbox = this.node.getBBox();
6389         } catch(e) {
6390             // Firefox 3.0.x, 25.0.1 (probably more versions affected) play badly here - possible fix
6391             bbox = {
6392                 x: this.node.clientLeft,
6393                 y: this.node.clientTop,
6394                 width: this.node.clientWidth,
6395                 height: this.node.clientHeight
6396             }
6397         } finally {
6398             bbox = bbox || {};
6399             if(canvasHidden){
6400               containerStyle.display = "none";
6401             }
6402         }
6403         hide && this.hide();
6404         return bbox;
6405     };
6406     /*\
6407      * Element.attr
6408      [ method ]
6409      **
6410      * Sets the attributes of the element.
6411      > Parameters
6412      - attrName (string) attribute’s name
6413      - value (string) value
6414      * or
6415      - params (object) object of name/value pairs
6416      * or
6417      - attrName (string) attribute’s name
6418      * or
6419      - attrNames (array) in this case method returns array of current values for given attribute names
6420      = (object) @Element if attrsName & value or params are passed in.
6421      = (...) value of the attribute if only attrsName is passed in.
6422      = (array) array of values of the attribute if attrsNames is passed in.
6423      = (object) object of attributes if nothing is passed in.
6424      > Possible parameters
6425      # <p>Please refer to the <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/" title="The W3C Recommendation for the SVG language describes these properties in detail.">SVG specification</a> for an explanation of these parameters.</p>
6426      o arrow-end (string) arrowhead on the end of the path. The format for string is `<type>[-<width>[-<length>]]`. Possible types: `classic`, `block`, `open`, `oval`, `diamond`, `none`, width: `wide`, `narrow`, `medium`, length: `long`, `short`, `midium`.
6427      o clip-rect (string) comma or space separated values: x, y, width and height
6428      o cursor (string) CSS type of the cursor
6429      o cx (number) the x-axis coordinate of the center of the circle, or ellipse
6430      o cy (number) the y-axis coordinate of the center of the circle, or ellipse
6431      o fill (string) colour, gradient or image
6432      o fill-opacity (number)
6433      o font (string)
6434      o font-family (string)
6435      o font-size (number) font size in pixels
6436      o font-weight (string)
6437      o height (number)
6438      o href (string) URL, if specified element behaves as hyperlink
6439      o opacity (number)
6440      o path (string) SVG path string format
6441      o r (number) radius of the circle, ellipse or rounded corner on the rect
6442      o rx (number) horisontal radius of the ellipse
6443      o ry (number) vertical radius of the ellipse
6444      o src (string) image URL, only works for @Element.image element
6445      o stroke (string) stroke colour
6446      o stroke-dasharray (string) [“”, “`-`”, “`.`”, “`-.`”, “`-..`”, “`. `”, “`- `”, “`--`”, “`- .`”, “`--.`”, “`--..`”]
6447      o stroke-linecap (string) [“`butt`”, “`square`”, “`round`”]
6448      o stroke-linejoin (string) [“`bevel`”, “`round`”, “`miter`”]
6449      o stroke-miterlimit (number)
6450      o stroke-opacity (number)
6451      o stroke-width (number) stroke width in pixels, default is '1'
6452      o target (string) used with href
6453      o text (string) contents of the text element. Use `\n` for multiline text
6454      o text-anchor (string) [“`start`”, “`middle`”, “`end`”], default is “`middle`”
6455      o title (string) will create tooltip with a given text
6456      o transform (string) see @Element.transform
6457      o width (number)
6458      o x (number)
6459      o y (number)
6460      > Gradients
6461      * Linear gradient format: “`‹angle›-‹colour›[-‹colour›[:‹offset›]]*-‹colour›`”, example: “`90-#fff-#000`” – 90°
6462      * gradient from white to black or “`0-#fff-#f00:20-#000`” – 0° gradient from white via red (at 20%) to black.
6463      *
6464      * radial gradient: “`r[(‹fx›, ‹fy›)]‹colour›[-‹colour›[:‹offset›]]*-‹colour›`”, example: “`r#fff-#000`” –
6465      * gradient from white to black or “`r(0.25, 0.75)#fff-#000`” – gradient from white to black with focus point
6466      * at 0.25, 0.75. Focus point coordinates are in 0..1 range. Radial gradients can only be applied to circles and ellipses.
6467      > Path String
6468      # <p>Please refer to <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/paths.html#PathData" title="Details of a path’s data attribute’s format are described in the SVG specification.">SVG documentation regarding path string</a>. Raphaël fully supports it.</p>
6469      > Colour Parsing
6470      # <ul>
6471      #     <li>Colour name (“<code>red</code>”, “<code>green</code>”, “<code>cornflowerblue</code>”, etc)</li>
6472      #     <li>#••• — shortened HTML colour: (“<code>#000</code>”, “<code>#fc0</code>”, etc)</li>
6473      #     <li>#•••••• — full length HTML colour: (“<code>#000000</code>”, “<code>#bd2300</code>”)</li>
6474      #     <li>rgb(•••, •••, •••) — red, green and blue channels’ values: (“<code>rgb(200, 100, 0)</code>”)</li>
6475      #     <li>rgb(•••%, •••%, •••%) — same as above, but in %: (“<code>rgb(100%, 175%, 0%)</code>”)</li>
6476      #     <li>rgba(•••, •••, •••, •••) — red, green and blue channels’ values: (“<code>rgba(200, 100, 0, .5)</code>”)</li>
6477      #     <li>rgba(•••%, •••%, •••%, •••%) — same as above, but in %: (“<code>rgba(100%, 175%, 0%, 50%)</code>”)</li>
6478      #     <li>hsb(•••, •••, •••) — hue, saturation and brightness values: (“<code>hsb(0.5, 0.25, 1)</code>”)</li>
6479      #     <li>hsb(•••%, •••%, •••%) — same as above, but in %</li>
6480      #     <li>hsba(•••, •••, •••, •••) — same as above, but with opacity</li>
6481      #     <li>hsl(•••, •••, •••) — almost the same as hsb, see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HSL_and_HSV" title="HSL and HSV - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia">Wikipedia page</a></li>
6482      #     <li>hsl(•••%, •••%, •••%) — same as above, but in %</li>
6483      #     <li>hsla(•••, •••, •••, •••) — same as above, but with opacity</li>
6484      #     <li>Optionally for hsb and hsl you could specify hue as a degree: “<code>hsl(240deg, 1, .5)</code>” or, if you want to go fancy, “<code>hsl(240°, 1, .5)</code>”</li>
6485      # </ul>
6486     \*/
6487     elproto.attr = function (name, value) {
6488         if (this.removed) {
6489             return this;
6490         }
6491         if (name == null) {
6492             var res = {};
6493             for (var a in this.attrs) if (this.attrs[has](a)) {
6494                 res[a] = this.attrs[a];
6495             }
6496             res.gradient && res.fill == "none" && (res.fill = res.gradient) && delete res.gradient;
6497             res.transform = this._.transform;
6498             return res;
6499         }
6500         if (value == null && R.is(name, "string")) {
6501             if (name == "fill" && this.attrs.fill == "none" && this.attrs.gradient) {
6502                 return this.attrs.gradient;
6503             }
6504             if (name == "transform") {
6505                 return this._.transform;
6506             }
6507             var names = name.split(separator),
6508                 out = {};
6509             for (var i = 0, ii = names.length; i < ii; i++) {
6510                 name = names[i];
6511                 if (name in this.attrs) {
6512                     out[name] = this.attrs[name];
6513                 } else if (R.is(this.paper.customAttributes[name], "function")) {
6514                     out[name] = this.paper.customAttributes[name].def;
6515                 } else {
6516                     out[name] = R._availableAttrs[name];
6517                 }
6518             }
6519             return ii - 1 ? out : out[names[0]];
6520         }
6521         if (value == null && R.is(name, "array")) {
6522             out = {};
6523             for (i = 0, ii = name.length; i < ii; i++) {
6524                 out[name[i]] = this.attr(name[i]);
6525             }
6526             return out;
6527         }
6528         if (value != null) {
6529             var params = {};
6530             params[name] = value;
6531         } else if (name != null && R.is(name, "object")) {
6532             params = name;
6533         }
6534         for (var key in params) {
6535             eve("raphael.attr." + key + "." + this.id, this, params[key]);
6536         }
6537         for (key in this.paper.customAttributes) if (this.paper.customAttributes[has](key) && params[has](key) && R.is(this.paper.customAttributes[key], "function")) {
6538             var par = this.paper.customAttributes[key].apply(this, [].concat(params[key]));
6539             this.attrs[key] = params[key];
6540             for (var subkey in par) if (par[has](subkey)) {
6541                 params[subkey] = par[subkey];
6542             }
6543         }
6544         setFillAndStroke(this, params);
6545         return this;
6546     };
6547     /*\
6548      * Element.toFront
6549      [ method ]
6550      **
6551      * Moves the element so it is the closest to the viewer’s eyes, on top of other elements.
6552      = (object) @Element
6553     \*/
6554     elproto.toFront = function () {
6555         if (this.removed) {
6556             return this;
6557         }
6558         var node = getRealNode(this.node);
6559         node.parentNode.appendChild(node);
6560         var svg = this.paper;
6561         svg.top != this && R._tofront(this, svg);
6562         return this;
6563     };
6564     /*\
6565      * Element.toBack
6566      [ method ]
6567      **
6568      * Moves the element so it is the furthest from the viewer’s eyes, behind other elements.
6569      = (object) @Element
6570     \*/
6571     elproto.toBack = function () {
6572         if (this.removed) {
6573             return this;
6574         }
6575         var node = getRealNode(this.node);
6576         var parentNode = node.parentNode;
6577         parentNode.insertBefore(node, parentNode.firstChild);
6578         R._toback(this, this.paper);
6579         var svg = this.paper;
6580         return this;
6581     };
6582     /*\
6583      * Element.insertAfter
6584      [ method ]
6585      **
6586      * Inserts current object after the given one.
6587      = (object) @Element
6588     \*/
6589     elproto.insertAfter = function (element) {
6590         if (this.removed || !element) {
6591             return this;
6592         }
6593 
6594         var node = getRealNode(this.node);
6595         var afterNode = getRealNode(element.node || element[element.length - 1].node);
6596         if (afterNode.nextSibling) {
6597             afterNode.parentNode.insertBefore(node, afterNode.nextSibling);
6598         } else {
6599             afterNode.parentNode.appendChild(node);
6600         }
6601         R._insertafter(this, element, this.paper);
6602         return this;
6603     };
6604     /*\
6605      * Element.insertBefore
6606      [ method ]
6607      **
6608      * Inserts current object before the given one.
6609      = (object) @Element
6610     \*/
6611     elproto.insertBefore = function (element) {
6612         if (this.removed || !element) {
6613             return this;
6614         }
6615 
6616         var node = getRealNode(this.node);
6617         var beforeNode = getRealNode(element.node || element[0].node);
6618         beforeNode.parentNode.insertBefore(node, beforeNode);
6619         R._insertbefore(this, element, this.paper);
6620         return this;
6621     };
6622     elproto.blur = function (size) {
6623         // Experimental. No Safari support. Use it on your own risk.
6624         var t = this;
6625         if (+size !== 0) {
6626             var fltr = $("filter"),
6627                 blur = $("feGaussianBlur");
6628             t.attrs.blur = size;
6629             fltr.id = R.createUUID();
6630             $(blur, {stdDeviation: +size || 1.5});
6631             fltr.appendChild(blur);
6632             t.paper.defs.appendChild(fltr);
6633             t._blur = fltr;
6634             $(t.node, {filter: "url(#" + fltr.id + ")"});
6635         } else {
6636             if (t._blur) {
6637                 t._blur.parentNode.removeChild(t._blur);
6638                 delete t._blur;
6639                 delete t.attrs.blur;
6640             }
6641             t.node.removeAttribute("filter");
6642         }
6643         return t;
6644     };

6700     R._engine.setSize = function (width, height) {
6701         this.width = width || this.width;
6702         this.height = height || this.height;
6703         this.canvas.setAttribute("width", this.width);
6704         this.canvas.setAttribute("height", this.height);
6705         if (this._viewBox) {
6706             this.setViewBox.apply(this, this._viewBox);

6710     R._engine.create = function () {
6711         var con = R._getContainer.apply(0, arguments),
6712             container = con && con.container,
6713             x = con.x,
6714             y = con.y,
6715             width = con.width,
6716             height = con.height;
6717         if (!container) {
6718             throw new Error("SVG container not found.");
6719         }
6720         var cnvs = $("svg"),
6721             css = "overflow:hidden;",
6722             isFloating;
6723         x = x || 0;
6724         y = y || 0;
6725         width = width || 512;
6726         height = height || 342;
6727         $(cnvs, {
6728             height: height,
6729             version: 1.1,
6730             width: width,
6731             xmlns: "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
6732             "xmlns:xlink": "http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
6733         });
6734         if (container == 1) {
6735             cnvs.style.cssText = css + "position:absolute;left:" + x + "px;top:" + y + "px";
6736             R._g.doc.body.appendChild(cnvs);
6737             isFloating = 1;
6738         } else {
6739             cnvs.style.cssText = css + "position:relative";
6740             if (container.firstChild) {
6741                 container.insertBefore(cnvs, container.firstChild);
6742             } else {
6743                 container.appendChild(cnvs);
6744             }
6745         }
6746         container = new R._Paper;
6747         container.width = width;
6748         container.height = height;
6749         container.canvas = cnvs;
6750         container.clear();
6751         container._left = container._top = 0;
6752         isFloating && (container.renderfix = function () {});
6753         container.renderfix();
6754         return container;
6755     };
6756     R._engine.setViewBox = function (x, y, w, h, fit) {
6757         eve("raphael.setViewBox", this, this._viewBox, [x, y, w, h, fit]);
6758         var paperSize = this.getSize(),
6759             size = mmax(w / paperSize.width, h / paperSize.height),
6760             top = this.top,
6761             aspectRatio = fit ? "xMidYMid meet" : "xMinYMin",
6762             vb,
6763             sw;
6764         if (x == null) {
6765             if (this._vbSize) {
6766                 size = 1;
6767             }
6768             delete this._vbSize;
6769             vb = "0 0 " + this.width + S + this.height;
6770         } else {
6771             this._vbSize = size;
6772             vb = x + S + y + S + w + S + h;
6773         }
6774         $(this.canvas, {
6775             viewBox: vb,
6776             preserveAspectRatio: aspectRatio
6777         });
6778         while (size && top) {
6779             sw = "stroke-width" in top.attrs ? top.attrs["stroke-width"] : 1;
6780             top.attr({"stroke-width": sw});
6781             top._.dirty = 1;
6782             top._.dirtyT = 1;
6783             top = top.prev;
6784         }
6785         this._viewBox = [x, y, w, h, !!fit];
6786         return this;
6787     };
6788     /*\
6789      * Paper.renderfix
6790      [ method ]
6791      **
6792      * Fixes the issue of Firefox and IE9 regarding subpixel rendering. If paper is dependant
6793      * on other elements after reflow it could shift half pixel which cause for lines to lost their crispness.
6794      * This method fixes the issue.
6795      **
6796        Special thanks to Mariusz Nowak (http://www.medikoo.com/) for this method.
6797     \*/
6798     R.prototype.renderfix = function () {
6799         var cnvs = this.canvas,
6800             s = cnvs.style,
6801             pos;
6802         try {
6803             pos = cnvs.getScreenCTM() || cnvs.createSVGMatrix();
6804         } catch (e) {
6805             pos = cnvs.createSVGMatrix();
6806         }
6807         var left = -pos.e % 1,
6808             top = -pos.f % 1;
6809         if (left || top) {
6810             if (left) {
6811                 this._left = (this._left + left) % 1;
6812                 s.left = this._left + "px";
6813             }
6814             if (top) {
6815                 this._top = (this._top + top) % 1;
6816                 s.top = this._top + "px";
6817             }
6818         }
6819     };
6820     /*\
6821      * Paper.clear
6822      [ method ]
6823      **
6824      * Clears the paper, i.e. removes all the elements.
6825     \*/
6826     R.prototype.clear = function () {
6827         R.eve("raphael.clear", this);
6828         var c = this.canvas;
6829         while (c.firstChild) {
6830             c.removeChild(c.firstChild);
6831         }
6832         this.bottom = this.top = null;
6833         (this.desc = $("desc")).appendChild(R._g.doc.createTextNode("Created with Rapha\xebl " + R.version));
6834         c.appendChild(this.desc);
6835         c.appendChild(this.defs = $("defs"));
6836     };
6837     /*\
6838      * Paper.remove
6839      [ method ]
6840      **
6841      * Removes the paper from the DOM.
6842     \*/
6843     R.prototype.remove = function () {
6844         eve("raphael.remove", this);
6845         this.canvas.parentNode && this.canvas.parentNode.removeChild(this.canvas);
6846         for (var i in this) {
6847             this[i] = typeof this[i] == "function" ? R._removedFactory(i) : null;
6848         }
6849     };
6850     var setproto = R.st;
6851     for (var method in elproto) if (elproto[has](method) && !setproto[has](method)) {
6852         setproto[method] = (function (methodname) {
6853             return function () {
6854                 var arg = arguments;
6855                 return this.forEach(function (el) {
6856                     el[methodname].apply(el, arg);
6857                 });
6858             };
6859         })(method);
6860     }

6873 (function(){
6874     if (!R.vml) {
6875         return;
6876     }
6877     var has = "hasOwnProperty",
6878         Str = String,
6879         toFloat = parseFloat,
6880         math = Math,
6881         round = math.round,
6882         mmax = math.max,
6883         mmin = math.min,
6884         abs = math.abs,
6885         fillString = "fill",
6886         separator = /[, ]+/,
6887         eve = R.eve,
6888         ms = " progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft",
6889         S = " ",
6890         E = "",
6891         map = {M: "m", L: "l", C: "c", Z: "x", m: "t", l: "r", c: "v", z: "x"},
6892         bites = /([clmz]),?([^clmz]*)/gi,
6893         blurregexp = / progid:\S+Blur\([^\)]+\)/g,
6894         val = /-?[^,\s-]+/g,
6895         cssDot = "position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:1px;height:1px;behavior:url(#default#VML)",
6896         zoom = 21600,
6897         pathTypes = {path: 1, rect: 1, image: 1},
6898         ovalTypes = {circle: 1, ellipse: 1},
6899         path2vml = function (path) {
6900             var total =  /[ahqstv]/ig,
6901                 command = R._pathToAbsolute;
6902             Str(path).match(total) && (command = R._path2curve);
6903             total = /[clmz]/g;
6904             if (command == R._pathToAbsolute && !Str(path).match(total)) {
6905                 var res = Str(path).replace(bites, function (all, command, args) {
6906                     var vals = [],
6907                         isMove = command.toLowerCase() == "m",
6908                         res = map[command];
6909                     args.replace(val, function (value) {
6910                         if (isMove && vals.length == 2) {
6911                             res += vals + map[command == "m" ? "l" : "L"];
6912                             vals = [];
6913                         }
6914                         vals.push(round(value * zoom));
6915                     });
6916                     return res + vals;
6917                 });
6918                 return res;
6919             }
6920             var pa = command(path), p, r;
6921             res = [];
6922             for (var i = 0, ii = pa.length; i < ii; i++) {
6923                 p = pa[i];
6924                 r = pa[i][0].toLowerCase();
6925                 r == "z" && (r = "x");
6926                 for (var j = 1, jj = p.length; j < jj; j++) {
6927                     r += round(p[j] * zoom) + (j != jj - 1 ? "," : E);
6928                 }
6929                 res.push(r);
6930             }
6931             return res.join(S);
6932         },
6933         compensation = function (deg, dx, dy) {
6934             var m = R.matrix();
6935             m.rotate(-deg, .5, .5);
6936             return {
6937                 dx: m.x(dx, dy),
6938                 dy: m.y(dx, dy)
6939             };
6940         },
6941         setCoords = function (p, sx, sy, dx, dy, deg) {
6942             var _ = p._,
6943                 m = p.matrix,
6944                 fillpos = _.fillpos,
6945                 o = p.node,
6946                 s = o.style,
6947                 y = 1,
6948                 flip = "",
6949                 dxdy,
6950                 kx = zoom / sx,
6951                 ky = zoom / sy;
6952             s.visibility = "hidden";
6953             if (!sx || !sy) {
6954                 return;
6955             }
6956             o.coordsize = abs(kx) + S + abs(ky);
6957             s.rotation = deg * (sx * sy < 0 ? -1 : 1);
6958             if (deg) {
6959                 var c = compensation(deg, dx, dy);
6960                 dx = c.dx;
6961                 dy = c.dy;
6962             }
6963             sx < 0 && (flip += "x");
6964             sy < 0 && (flip += " y") && (y = -1);
6965             s.flip = flip;
6966             o.coordorigin = (dx * -kx) + S + (dy * -ky);
6967             if (fillpos || _.fillsize) {
6968                 var fill = o.getElementsByTagName(fillString);
6969                 fill = fill && fill[0];
6970                 o.removeChild(fill);
6971                 if (fillpos) {
6972                     c = compensation(deg, m.x(fillpos[0], fillpos[1]), m.y(fillpos[0], fillpos[1]));
6973                     fill.position = c.dx * y + S + c.dy * y;
6974                 }
6975                 if (_.fillsize) {
6976                     fill.size = _.fillsize[0] * abs(sx) + S + _.fillsize[1] * abs(sy);
6977                 }
6978                 o.appendChild(fill);
6979             }
6980             s.visibility = "visible";
6981         };
6982     R.toString = function () {
6983         return  "Your browser doesn\u2019t support SVG. Falling down to VML.\nYou are running Rapha\xebl " + this.version;
6984     };
6985     var addArrow = function (o, value, isEnd) {
6986         var values = Str(value).toLowerCase().split("-"),
6987             se = isEnd ? "end" : "start",
6988             i = values.length,
6989             type = "classic",
6990             w = "medium",
6991             h = "medium";
6992         while (i--) {
6993             switch (values[i]) {
6994                 case "block":
6995                 case "classic":
6996                 case "oval":
6997                 case "diamond":
6998                 case "open":
6999                 case "none":
7000                     type = values[i];
7001                     break;
7002                 case "wide":
7003                 case "narrow": h = values[i]; break;
7004                 case "long":
7005                 case "short": w = values[i]; break;
7006             }
7007         }
7008         var stroke = o.node.getElementsByTagName("stroke")[0];
7009         stroke[se + "arrow"] = type;
7010         stroke[se + "arrowlength"] = w;
7011         stroke[se + "arrowwidth"] = h;
7012     },
7013     setFillAndStroke = function (o, params) {

7238     addGradientFill = function (o, gradient, fill) {
7239         o.attrs = o.attrs || {};
7240         var attrs = o.attrs,
7241             pow = Math.pow,
7242             opacity,
7243             oindex,
7244             type = "linear",
7245             fxfy = ".5 .5";
7246         o.attrs.gradient = gradient;
7247         gradient = Str(gradient).replace(R._radial_gradient, function (all, fx, fy) {
7248             type = "radial";
7249             if (fx && fy) {
7250                 fx = toFloat(fx);
7251                 fy = toFloat(fy);
7252                 pow(fx - .5, 2) + pow(fy - .5, 2) > .25 && (fy = math.sqrt(.25 - pow(fx - .5, 2)) * ((fy > .5) * 2 - 1) + .5);
7253                 fxfy = fx + S + fy;
7254             }
7255             return E;
7256         });
7257         gradient = gradient.split(/\s*\-\s*/);
7258         if (type == "linear") {
7259             var angle = gradient.shift();
7260             angle = -toFloat(angle);
7261             if (isNaN(angle)) {
7262                 return null;
7263             }
7264         }
7265         var dots = R._parseDots(gradient);
7266         if (!dots) {
7267             return null;
7268         }
7269         o = o.shape || o.node;
7270         if (dots.length) {
7271             o.removeChild(fill);
7272             fill.on = true;
7273             fill.method = "none";
7274             fill.color = dots[0].color;
7275             fill.color2 = dots[dots.length - 1].color;
7276             var clrs = [];
7277             for (var i = 0, ii = dots.length; i < ii; i++) {
7278                 dots[i].offset && clrs.push(dots[i].offset + S + dots[i].color);
7279             }
7280             fill.colors = clrs.length ? clrs.join() : "0% " + fill.color;
7281             if (type == "radial") {
7282                 fill.type = "gradientTitle";
7283                 fill.focus = "100%";
7284                 fill.focussize = "0 0";
7285                 fill.focusposition = fxfy;
7286                 fill.angle = 0;
7287             } else {
7288                 // fill.rotate= true;
7289                 fill.type = "gradient";
7290                 fill.angle = (270 - angle) % 360;
7291             }
7292             o.appendChild(fill);
7293         }
7294         return 1;
7295     },

7326     elproto.transform = function (tstr) {
7327         if (tstr == null) {
7328             return this._.transform;
7329         }
7330         var vbs = this.paper._viewBoxShift,
7331             vbt = vbs ? "s" + [vbs.scale, vbs.scale] + "-1-1t" + [vbs.dx, vbs.dy] : E,
7332             oldt;
7333         if (vbs) {
7334             oldt = tstr = Str(tstr).replace(/\.{3}|\u2026/g, this._.transform || E);
7335         }
7336         R._extractTransform(this, vbt + tstr);
7337         var matrix = this.matrix.clone(),
7338             skew = this.skew,
7339             o = this.node,
7340             split,
7341             isGrad = ~Str(this.attrs.fill).indexOf("-"),
7342             isPatt = !Str(this.attrs.fill).indexOf("url(");
7343         matrix.translate(1, 1);
7344         if (isPatt || isGrad || this.type == "image") {
7345             skew.matrix = "1 0 0 1";
7346             skew.offset = "0 0";
7347             split = matrix.split();
7348             if ((isGrad && split.noRotation) || !split.isSimple) {
7349                 o.style.filter = matrix.toFilter();
7350                 var bb = this.getBBox(),
7351                     bbt = this.getBBox(1),
7352                     dx = bb.x - bbt.x,
7353                     dy = bb.y - bbt.y;
7354                 o.coordorigin = (dx * -zoom) + S + (dy * -zoom);
7355                 setCoords(this, 1, 1, dx, dy, 0);
7356             } else {
7357                 o.style.filter = E;
7358                 setCoords(this, split.scalex, split.scaley, split.dx, split.dy, split.rotate);
7359             }
7360         } else {
7361             o.style.filter = E;
7362             skew.matrix = Str(matrix);
7363             skew.offset = matrix.offset();
7364         }
7365         if (oldt !== null) { // empty string value is true as well
7366             this._.transform = oldt;
7367             R._extractTransform(this, oldt);
7368         }
7369         return this;

7371     elproto.rotate = function (deg, cx, cy) {
7372         if (this.removed) {
7373             return this;
7374         }
7375         if (deg == null) {
7376             return;
7377         }
7378         deg = Str(deg).split(separator);
7379         if (deg.length - 1) {
7380             cx = toFloat(deg[1]);
7381             cy = toFloat(deg[2]);
7382         }
7383         deg = toFloat(deg[0]);
7384         (cy == null) && (cx = cy);
7385         if (cx == null || cy == null) {
7386             var bbox = this.getBBox(1);
7387             cx = bbox.x + bbox.width / 2;
7388             cy = bbox.y + bbox.height / 2;
7389         }
7390         this._.dirtyT = 1;
7391         this.transform(this._.transform.concat([["r", deg, cx, cy]]));
7392         return this;

7394     elproto.translate = function (dx, dy) {
7395         if (this.removed) {
7396             return this;
7397         }
7398         dx = Str(dx).split(separator);
7399         if (dx.length - 1) {
7400             dy = toFloat(dx[1]);
7401         }
7402         dx = toFloat(dx[0]) || 0;
7403         dy = +dy || 0;
7404         if (this._.bbox) {
7405             this._.bbox.x += dx;
7406             this._.bbox.y += dy;
7407         }
7408         this.transform(this._.transform.concat([["t", dx, dy]]));
7409         return this;
7410     };
7411     elproto.scale = function (sx, sy, cx, cy) {
7412         if (this.removed) {
7413             return this;
7414         }
7415         sx = Str(sx).split(separator);
7416         if (sx.length - 1) {
7417             sy = toFloat(sx[1]);
7418             cx = toFloat(sx[2]);
7419             cy = toFloat(sx[3]);
7420             isNaN(cx) && (cx = null);
7421             isNaN(cy) && (cy = null);
7422         }
7423         sx = toFloat(sx[0]);
7424         (sy == null) && (sy = sx);
7425         (cy == null) && (cx = cy);
7426         if (cx == null || cy == null) {
7427             var bbox = this.getBBox(1);
7428         }
7429         cx = cx == null ? bbox.x + bbox.width / 2 : cx;
7430         cy = cy == null ? bbox.y + bbox.height / 2 : cy;
7431     
7432         this.transform(this._.transform.concat([["s", sx, sy, cx, cy]]));
7433         this._.dirtyT = 1;
7434         return this;

7445     elproto.auxGetBBox = R.el.getBBox;
7446     elproto.getBBox = function(){
7447       var b = this.auxGetBBox();
7448       if (this.paper && this.paper._viewBoxShift)
7449       {
7450         var c = {};
7451         var z = 1/this.paper._viewBoxShift.scale;
7452         c.x = b.x - this.paper._viewBoxShift.dx;
7453         c.x *= z;
7454         c.y = b.y - this.paper._viewBoxShift.dy;
7455         c.y *= z;
7456         c.width  = b.width  * z;
7457         c.height = b.height * z;
7458         c.x2 = c.x + c.width;
7459         c.y2 = c.y + c.height;
7460         return c;
7461       }
7462       return b;
7463     };
7464     elproto._getBBox = function () {

7470             y: this.Y - this.H,
7471             width: this.W,
7472             height: this.H
7473         };

7475     elproto.remove = function () {

7477             return;

7479         this.paper.__set__ && this.paper.__set__.exclude(this);
7480         R.eve.unbind("raphael.*.*." + this.id);
